47 // Scoped class tracking context objects created by the visitor. Represents
48 // mutations of the context chain within the function body, allowing pushing and
49 // popping of the current {context_register} during visitation.
50 class V8_NODISCARD BytecodeGenerator::ContextScope {
51  public:
52  ContextScope(BytecodeGenerator* generator, Scope* scope,
53  Register outer_context_reg = Register())
54  : generator_(generator),
55  scope_(scope),
56  outer_(generator_->execution_context()),
57  register_(Register::current_context()),
58  depth_(0) {
59  DCHECK(scope->NeedsContext() || outer_ == nullptr);
60  if (outer_) {
61  depth_ = outer_->depth_ + 1;
62 
63  // Push the outer context into a new context register.
64  if (!outer_context_reg.is_valid()) {
65  outer_context_reg = generator_->register_allocator()->NewRegister();
66  }
67  outer_->set_register(outer_context_reg);
68  generator_->builder()->PushContext(outer_context_reg);
69  }
70  generator_->set_execution_context(this);
71  }
72 
73  ~ContextScope() {
74  if (outer_) {
75  DCHECK_EQ(register_.index(), Register::current_context().index());
76  generator_->builder()->PopContext(outer_->reg());
77  outer_->set_register(register_);
78  }
79  generator_->set_execution_context(outer_);
80  }
81 
82  ContextScope(const ContextScope&) = delete;
83  ContextScope& operator=(const ContextScope&) = delete;
84 
85  // Returns the depth of the given |scope| for the current execution context.
86  int ContextChainDepth(Scope* scope) {
87  return scope_->ContextChainLength(scope);
88  }
89 
90  // Returns the execution context at |depth| in the current context chain if it
91  // is a function local execution context, otherwise returns nullptr.
92  ContextScope* Previous(int depth) {
93  if (depth > depth_) {
94  return nullptr;
95  }
96 
97  ContextScope* previous = this;
98  for (int i = depth; i > 0; --i) {
99  previous = previous->outer_;
100  }
101  return previous;
102  }
103 
104  Register reg() const { return register_; }
105 
106  private:
107  const BytecodeArrayBuilder* builder() const { return generator_->builder(); }
108 
109  void set_register(Register reg) { register_ = reg; }
110 
111  BytecodeGenerator* generator_;
112  Scope* scope_;
113  ContextScope* outer_;
114  Register register_;
115  int depth_;
116 };
117 
118 // Scoped class for tracking control statements entered by the
119 // visitor.
120 class V8_NODISCARD BytecodeGenerator::ControlScope {
121  public:
122  explicit ControlScope(BytecodeGenerator* generator)
123  : generator_(generator),
124  outer_(generator->execution_control()),
125  context_(generator->execution_context()) {
126  generator_->set_execution_control(this);
127  }
128  ~ControlScope() { generator_->set_execution_control(outer()); }
129  ControlScope(const ControlScope&) = delete;
130  ControlScope& operator=(const ControlScope&) = delete;
131 
132  void Break(Statement* stmt) {
133  PerformCommand(CMD_BREAK, stmt, kNoSourcePosition);
134  }
135  void Continue(Statement* stmt) {
136  PerformCommand(CMD_CONTINUE, stmt, kNoSourcePosition);
137  }
138  void ReturnAccumulator(int source_position) {
139  PerformCommand(CMD_RETURN, nullptr, source_position);
140  }
141  void AsyncReturnAccumulator(int source_position) {
142  PerformCommand(CMD_ASYNC_RETURN, nullptr, source_position);
143  }
144 
145  class DeferredCommands;
146 
147  protected:
148  enum Command {
149  CMD_BREAK,
150  CMD_CONTINUE,
151  CMD_RETURN,
152  CMD_ASYNC_RETURN,
153  CMD_RETHROW
154  };
155  static constexpr bool CommandUsesAccumulator(Command command) {
156  return command != CMD_BREAK && command != CMD_CONTINUE;
157  }
158 
159  void PerformCommand(Command command, Statement* statement,
160  int source_position);
161  virtual bool Execute(Command command, Statement* statement,
162  int source_position) = 0;
163 
164  // Helper to pop the context chain to a depth expected by this control scope.
165  // Note that it is the responsibility of each individual {Execute} method to
166  // trigger this when commands are handled and control-flow continues locally.
167  void PopContextToExpectedDepth();
168 
169  BytecodeGenerator* generator() const { return generator_; }
170  ControlScope* outer() const { return outer_; }
171  ContextScope* context() const { return context_; }
172 
173  private:
174  BytecodeGenerator* generator_;
175  ControlScope* outer_;
176  ContextScope* context_;
177 };
178 
179 // Helper class for a try-finally control scope. It can record intercepted
180 // control-flow commands that cause entry into a finally-block, and re-apply
181 // them after again leaving that block. Special tokens are used to identify
182 // paths going through the finally-block to dispatch after leaving the block.
183 class V8_NODISCARD BytecodeGenerator::ControlScope::DeferredCommands final {
184  public:
185  DeferredCommands(BytecodeGenerator* generator, Register token_register,
186  Register result_register, Register message_register)
187  : generator_(generator),
188  deferred_(generator->zone()),
189  token_register_(token_register),
190  result_register_(result_register),
191  message_register_(message_register),
192  return_token_(-1),
193  async_return_token_(-1),
194  fallthrough_from_try_block_needed_(false) {
195  // There's always a rethrow path.
196  // TODO(leszeks): We could decouple deferred_ index and token to allow us
197  // to still push this lazily.
198  static_assert(
199  static_cast<int>(TryFinallyContinuationToken::kRethrowToken) == 0);
200  deferred_.push_back(
201  {CMD_RETHROW, nullptr,
202  static_cast<int>(TryFinallyContinuationToken::kRethrowToken)});
203  }
204 
205  // One recorded control-flow command.
206  struct Entry {
207  Command command; // The command type being applied on this path.
208  Statement* statement; // The target statement for the command or {nullptr}.
209  int token; // A token identifying this particular path.
210  };
211 
212  // Records a control-flow command while entering the finally-block. This also
213  // generates a new dispatch token that identifies one particular path. This
214  // expects the result to be in the accumulator.
215  void RecordCommand(Command command, Statement* statement) {
216  int token = GetTokenForCommand(command, statement);
217 
218  DCHECK_LT(token, deferred_.size());
219  DCHECK_EQ(deferred_[token].command, command);
220  DCHECK_EQ(deferred_[token].statement, statement);
221  DCHECK_EQ(deferred_[token].token, token);
222 
223  if (CommandUsesAccumulator(command)) {
224  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(result_register_);
225  }
226  builder()->LoadLiteral(Smi::FromInt(token));
227  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(token_register_);
228  if (!CommandUsesAccumulator(command)) {
229  // If we're not saving the accumulator in the result register, shove a
230  // harmless value there instead so that it is still considered "killed" in
231  // the liveness analysis. Normally we would LdaUndefined first, but the
232  // Smi token value is just as good, and by reusing it we save a bytecode.
233  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(result_register_);
234  }
235  if (command == CMD_RETHROW) {
236  // Clear message object as we enter the catch block. It will be restored
237  // if we rethrow.
238  builder()->LoadTheHole().SetPendingMessage().StoreAccumulatorInRegister(
239  message_register_);
240  }
241  }
242 
243  // Records the dispatch token to be used to identify the re-throw path when
244  // the finally-block has been entered through the exception handler. This
245  // expects the exception to be in the accumulator.
246  void RecordHandlerReThrowPath() {
247  // The accumulator contains the exception object.
248  RecordCommand(CMD_RETHROW, nullptr);
249  }
250 
251  // Records the dispatch token to be used to identify the implicit fall-through
252  // path at the end of a try-block into the corresponding finally-block.
253  void RecordFallThroughPath() {
254  fallthrough_from_try_block_needed_ = true;
255  builder()->LoadLiteral(Smi::FromInt(
256  static_cast<int>(TryFinallyContinuationToken::kFallthroughToken)));
257  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(token_register_);
258  // Since we're not saving the accumulator in the result register, shove a
259  // harmless value there instead so that it is still considered "killed" in
260  // the liveness analysis. Normally we would LdaUndefined first, but the Smi
261  // token value is just as good, and by reusing it we save a bytecode.
262  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(result_register_);
263  }
264 
265  void ApplyDeferredCommand(const Entry& entry) {
266  if (entry.command == CMD_RETHROW) {
267  // Pending message object is restored on exit.
268  builder()
269  ->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(message_register_)
270  .SetPendingMessage();
271  }
272 
273  if (CommandUsesAccumulator(entry.command)) {
274  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(result_register_);
275  }
276  execution_control()->PerformCommand(entry.command, entry.statement,
277  kNoSourcePosition);
278  }
279 
280  // Applies all recorded control-flow commands after the finally-block again.
281  // This generates a dynamic dispatch on the token from the entry point.
282  void ApplyDeferredCommands() {
283  if (deferred_.empty()) return;
284 
285  BytecodeLabel fall_through_from_try_block;
286 
287  if (deferred_.size() == 1) {
288  // For a single entry, just jump to the fallthrough if we don't match the
289  // entry token.
290  const Entry& entry = deferred_[0];
291 
292  if (fallthrough_from_try_block_needed_) {
293  builder()
294  ->LoadLiteral(Smi::FromInt(entry.token))
295  .CompareReference(token_register_)
296  .JumpIfFalse(ToBooleanMode::kAlreadyBoolean,
297  &fall_through_from_try_block);
298  }
299 
300  ApplyDeferredCommand(entry);
301  } else {
302  // For multiple entries, build a jump table and switch on the token,
303  // jumping to the fallthrough if none of them match.
304  //
305  // If fallthrough from the try block is not needed, generate a jump table
306  // with one (1) fewer entries and reuse the fallthrough path for the final
307  // entry.
308  const int jump_table_base_value =
309  fallthrough_from_try_block_needed_ ? 0 : 1;
310  const int jump_table_size =
311  static_cast<int>(deferred_.size() - jump_table_base_value);
312 
313  if (jump_table_size == 1) {
314  DCHECK_EQ(2, deferred_.size());
315  BytecodeLabel fall_through_to_final_entry;
316  const Entry& first_entry = deferred_[0];
317  const Entry& final_entry = deferred_[1];
318  builder()
319  ->LoadLiteral(Smi::FromInt(first_entry.token))
320  .CompareReference(token_register_)
321  .JumpIfFalse(ToBooleanMode::kAlreadyBoolean,
322  &fall_through_to_final_entry);
323  ApplyDeferredCommand(first_entry);
324  builder()->Bind(&fall_through_to_final_entry);
325  ApplyDeferredCommand(final_entry);
326  } else {
327  BytecodeJumpTable* jump_table = builder()->AllocateJumpTable(
328  jump_table_size, jump_table_base_value);
329  builder()
330  ->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(token_register_)
331  .SwitchOnSmiNoFeedback(jump_table);
332 
333  const Entry& first_entry = deferred_.front();
334  if (fallthrough_from_try_block_needed_) {
335  builder()->Jump(&fall_through_from_try_block);
336  builder()->Bind(jump_table, first_entry.token);
337  }
338  ApplyDeferredCommand(first_entry);
339 
340  for (const Entry& entry : base::IterateWithoutFirst(deferred_)) {
341  builder()->Bind(jump_table, entry.token);
342  ApplyDeferredCommand(entry);
343  }
344  }
345  }
346 
347  if (fallthrough_from_try_block_needed_) {
348  builder()->Bind(&fall_through_from_try_block);
349  }
350  }
351 
352  BytecodeArrayBuilder* builder() { return generator_->builder(); }
353  ControlScope* execution_control() { return generator_->execution_control(); }
354 
355  private:
356  int GetTokenForCommand(Command command, Statement* statement) {
357  switch (command) {
358  case CMD_RETURN:
359  return GetReturnToken();
360  case CMD_ASYNC_RETURN:
361  return GetAsyncReturnToken();
362  case CMD_RETHROW:
363  return static_cast<int>(TryFinallyContinuationToken::kRethrowToken);
364  default:
365  // TODO(leszeks): We could also search for entries with the same
366  // command and statement.
367  return GetNewTokenForCommand(command, statement);
368  }
369  }
370 
371  int GetReturnToken() {
372  if (return_token_ == -1) {
373  return_token_ = GetNewTokenForCommand(CMD_RETURN, nullptr);
374  }
375  return return_token_;
376  }
377 
378  int GetAsyncReturnToken() {
379  if (async_return_token_ == -1) {
380  async_return_token_ = GetNewTokenForCommand(CMD_ASYNC_RETURN, nullptr);
381  }
382  return async_return_token_;
383  }
384 
385  int GetNewTokenForCommand(Command command, Statement* statement) {
386  int token = static_cast<int>(deferred_.size());
387  deferred_.push_back({command, statement, token});
388  return token;
389  }
390 
391  BytecodeGenerator* generator_;
392  ZoneVector<Entry> deferred_;
393  Register token_register_;
394  Register result_register_;
395  Register message_register_;
396 
397  // Tokens for commands that don't need a statement.
398  int return_token_;
399  int async_return_token_;
400 
401  // Whether a fallthrough is possible.
402  bool fallthrough_from_try_block_needed_;
403 };
404 
405 // Scoped class for dealing with control flow reaching the function level.
406 class BytecodeGenerator::ControlScopeForTopLevel final
407  : public BytecodeGenerator::ControlScope {
408  public:
409  explicit ControlScopeForTopLevel(BytecodeGenerator* generator)
410  : ControlScope(generator) {}
411 
412  protected:
413  bool Execute(Command command, Statement* statement,
414  int source_position) override {
415  switch (command) {
416  case CMD_BREAK: // We should never see break/continue in top-level.
417  case CMD_CONTINUE:
418  UNREACHABLE();
419  case CMD_RETURN:
420  // No need to pop contexts, execution leaves the method body.
421  generator()->BuildReturn(source_position);
422  return true;
423  case CMD_ASYNC_RETURN:
424  // No need to pop contexts, execution leaves the method body.
425  generator()->BuildAsyncReturn(source_position);
426  return true;
427  case CMD_RETHROW:
428  // No need to pop contexts, execution leaves the method body.
429  generator()->BuildReThrow();
430  return true;
431  }
432  return false;
433  }
434 };
435 
436 // Scoped class for enabling break inside blocks and switch blocks.
437 class BytecodeGenerator::ControlScopeForBreakable final
438  : public BytecodeGenerator::ControlScope {
439  public:
440  ControlScopeForBreakable(BytecodeGenerator* generator,
441  BreakableStatement* statement,
442  BreakableControlFlowBuilder* control_builder)
443  : ControlScope(generator),
444  statement_(statement),
445  control_builder_(control_builder) {}
446 
447  protected:
448  bool Execute(Command command, Statement* statement,
449  int source_position) override {
450  if (statement != statement_) return false;
451  switch (command) {
452  case CMD_BREAK:
453  PopContextToExpectedDepth();
454  control_builder_->Break();
455  return true;
456  case CMD_CONTINUE:
457  case CMD_RETURN:
458  case CMD_ASYNC_RETURN:
459  case CMD_RETHROW:
460  break;
461  }
462  return false;
463  }
464 
465  private:
466  Statement* statement_;
467  BreakableControlFlowBuilder* control_builder_;
468 };
469 
470 // Scoped class for enabling 'break' and 'continue' in iteration
471 // constructs, e.g. do...while, while..., for...
472 class BytecodeGenerator::ControlScopeForIteration final
473  : public BytecodeGenerator::ControlScope {
474  public:
475  ControlScopeForIteration(BytecodeGenerator* generator,
476  IterationStatement* statement,
477  LoopBuilder* loop_builder)
478  : ControlScope(generator),
479  statement_(statement),
480  loop_builder_(loop_builder) {}
481 
482  protected:
483  bool Execute(Command command, Statement* statement,
484  int source_position) override {
485  if (statement != statement_) return false;
486  switch (command) {
487  case CMD_BREAK:
488  PopContextToExpectedDepth();
489  loop_builder_->Break();
490  return true;
491  case CMD_CONTINUE:
492  PopContextToExpectedDepth();
493  loop_builder_->Continue();
494  return true;
495  case CMD_RETURN:
496  case CMD_ASYNC_RETURN:
497  case CMD_RETHROW:
498  break;
499  }
500  return false;
501  }
502 
503  private:
504  Statement* statement_;
505  LoopBuilder* loop_builder_;
506 };

508 // Scoped class for enabling 'throw' in try-catch constructs.
509 class BytecodeGenerator::ControlScopeForTryCatch final
510  : public BytecodeGenerator::ControlScope {
511  public:
512  ControlScopeForTryCatch(BytecodeGenerator* generator,
513  TryCatchBuilder* try_catch_builder)
514  : ControlScope(generator) {}
515 
516  protected:
517  bool Execute(Command command, Statement* statement,
518  int source_position) override {
519  switch (command) {
520  case CMD_BREAK:
521  case CMD_CONTINUE:
522  case CMD_RETURN:
523  case CMD_ASYNC_RETURN:
524  break;
525  case CMD_RETHROW:
526  // No need to pop contexts, execution re-enters the method body via the
527  // stack unwinding mechanism which itself restores contexts correctly.
528  generator()->BuildReThrow();
529  return true;
530  }
531  return false;
532  }
533 };
534 
535 // Scoped class for enabling control flow through try-finally constructs.
536 class BytecodeGenerator::ControlScopeForTryFinally final
537  : public BytecodeGenerator::ControlScope {
538  public:
539  ControlScopeForTryFinally(BytecodeGenerator* generator,
540  TryFinallyBuilder* try_finally_builder,
541  DeferredCommands* commands)
542  : ControlScope(generator),
543  try_finally_builder_(try_finally_builder),
544  commands_(commands) {}
545 
546  protected:
547  bool Execute(Command command, Statement* statement,
548  int source_position) override {
549  switch (command) {
550  case CMD_BREAK:
551  case CMD_CONTINUE:
552  case CMD_RETURN:
553  case CMD_ASYNC_RETURN:
554  case CMD_RETHROW:
555  PopContextToExpectedDepth();
556  // We don't record source_position here since we don't generate return
557  // bytecode right here and will generate it later as part of finally
558  // block. Each return bytecode generated in finally block will get own
559  // return source position from corresponded return statement or we'll
560  // use end of function if no return statement is presented.
561  commands_->RecordCommand(command, statement);
562  try_finally_builder_->LeaveTry();
563  return true;
564  }
565  return false;
566  }
567 
568  private:
569  TryFinallyBuilder* try_finally_builder_;
570  DeferredCommands* commands_;
571 };
572 
573 // Scoped class for collecting 'return' statements in a derived constructor.
574 // Derived constructors can only return undefined or objects, and this check
575 // must occur right before return (e.g., after `finally` blocks execute).
576 class BytecodeGenerator::ControlScopeForDerivedConstructor final
577  : public BytecodeGenerator::ControlScope {
578  public:
579  ControlScopeForDerivedConstructor(BytecodeGenerator* generator,
580  Register result_register,
581  BytecodeLabels* check_return_value_labels)
582  : ControlScope(generator),
583  result_register_(result_register),
584  check_return_value_labels_(check_return_value_labels) {}
585 
586  protected:
587  bool Execute(Command command, Statement* statement,
588  int source_position) override {
589  // Constructors are never async.
590  DCHECK_NE(CMD_ASYNC_RETURN, command);
591  if (command == CMD_RETURN) {
592  PopContextToExpectedDepth();
593  generator()->builder()->SetStatementPosition(source_position);
594  generator()->builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(result_register_);
595  generator()->builder()->Jump(check_return_value_labels_->New());
596  return true;
597  }
598  return false;
599  }
600 
601  private:
602  Register result_register_;
603  BytecodeLabels* check_return_value_labels_;
604 };
605 
606 // Allocate and fetch the coverage indices tracking NaryLogical Expressions.
607 class BytecodeGenerator::NaryCodeCoverageSlots {
608  public:
609  NaryCodeCoverageSlots(BytecodeGenerator* generator, NaryOperation* expr)
610  : generator_(generator) {
611  if (generator_->block_coverage_builder_ == nullptr) return;
612  for (size_t i = 0; i < expr->subsequent_length(); i++) {
613  coverage_slots_.push_back(
614  generator_->AllocateNaryBlockCoverageSlotIfEnabled(expr, i));
615  }
616  }
617 
618  int GetSlotFor(size_t subsequent_expr_index) const {
619  if (generator_->block_coverage_builder_ == nullptr) {
620  return BlockCoverageBuilder::kNoCoverageArraySlot;
621  }
622  DCHECK(coverage_slots_.size() > subsequent_expr_index);
623  return coverage_slots_[subsequent_expr_index];
624  }
625 
626  private:
627  BytecodeGenerator* generator_;
628  std::vector<int> coverage_slots_;
629 };
630 
631 void BytecodeGenerator::ControlScope::PerformCommand(Command command,
632  Statement* statement,
633  int source_position) {
634  ControlScope* current = this;
635  do {
636  if (current->Execute(command, statement, source_position)) {
637  return;
638  }
639  current = current->outer();
640  } while (current != nullptr);
641  UNREACHABLE();
642 }
643 
644 void BytecodeGenerator::ControlScope::PopContextToExpectedDepth() {
645  // Pop context to the expected depth. Note that this can in fact pop multiple
646  // contexts at once because the {PopContext} bytecode takes a saved register.
647  if (generator()->execution_context() != context()) {
648  generator()->builder()->PopContext(context()->reg());
649  }
650 }

652 class V8_NODISCARD BytecodeGenerator::RegisterAllocationScope final {
653  public:
654  explicit RegisterAllocationScope(BytecodeGenerator* generator)
655  : generator_(generator),
656  outer_next_register_index_(
657  generator->register_allocator()->next_register_index()) {}
658 
659  ~RegisterAllocationScope() {
660  generator_->register_allocator()->ReleaseRegisters(
661  outer_next_register_index_);
662  }
663 
664  RegisterAllocationScope(const RegisterAllocationScope&) = delete;
665  RegisterAllocationScope& operator=(const RegisterAllocationScope&) = delete;
666 
667  BytecodeGenerator* generator() const { return generator_; }
668 
669  private:
670  BytecodeGenerator* generator_;
671  int outer_next_register_index_;
672 };
673 
674 class V8_NODISCARD BytecodeGenerator::AccumulatorPreservingScope final {
675  public:
676  explicit AccumulatorPreservingScope(BytecodeGenerator* generator,
677  AccumulatorPreservingMode mode)
678  : generator_(generator) {
679  if (mode == AccumulatorPreservingMode::kPreserve) {
680  saved_accumulator_register_ =
681  generator_->register_allocator()->NewRegister();
682  generator_->builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(
683  saved_accumulator_register_);
684  }
685  }
686 
687  ~AccumulatorPreservingScope() {
688  if (saved_accumulator_register_.is_valid()) {
689  generator_->builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(
690  saved_accumulator_register_);
691  }
692  }
693 
694  AccumulatorPreservingScope(const AccumulatorPreservingScope&) = delete;
695  AccumulatorPreservingScope& operator=(const AccumulatorPreservingScope&) =
696  delete;
697 
698  private:
699  BytecodeGenerator* generator_;
700  Register saved_accumulator_register_;
701 };

703 // Scoped base class for determining how the result of an expression will be
704 // used.
705 class V8_NODISCARD BytecodeGenerator::ExpressionResultScope {
706  public:
707  enum Kind : uint8_t {
708  // Evaluated for its side effects.
709  kEffect,
710  // Evaluated for its value (and side effects).
711  kValue,
712  kValueAsPropertyKey,
713  // Evaluated for control flow (and side effects).
714  kTest,
715  };
716 
717  ExpressionResultScope(BytecodeGenerator* generator, Kind kind)
718  : outer_(generator->execution_result()),
719  allocator_(generator),
720  kind_(kind),
721  type_hint_(TypeHint::kUnknown) {
722  generator->set_execution_result(this);
723  }
724 
725  ~ExpressionResultScope() {
726  allocator_.generator()->set_execution_result(outer_);
727  }
728 
729  ExpressionResultScope(const ExpressionResultScope&) = delete;
730  ExpressionResultScope& operator=(const ExpressionResultScope&) = delete;
731 
732  bool IsEffect() const { return kind_ == kEffect; }
733  bool IsValue() const { return kind_ == kValue; }
734  bool IsValueAsPropertyKey() const { return kind_ == kValueAsPropertyKey; }
735  bool IsTest() const { return kind_ == kTest; }
736 
737  TestResultScope* AsTest() {
738  DCHECK(IsTest());
739  return reinterpret_cast<TestResultScope*>(this);
740  }
741 
742  // Specify expression always returns a Boolean result value.
743  void SetResultIsBoolean() {
744  DCHECK_EQ(type_hint_, TypeHint::kUnknown);
745  type_hint_ = TypeHint::kBoolean;
746  }
747 
748  void SetResultIsString() {
749  DCHECK_EQ(type_hint_, TypeHint::kUnknown);
750  type_hint_ = TypeHint::kString;
751  }
752 
753  void SetResultIsInternalizedString() {
754  DCHECK_EQ(type_hint_, TypeHint::kUnknown);
755  type_hint_ = TypeHint::kInternalizedString;
756  }
757 
758  TypeHint type_hint() const { return type_hint_; }
759 
760  private:
761  ExpressionResultScope* outer_;
762  RegisterAllocationScope allocator_;
763  Kind kind_;
764  TypeHint type_hint_;
765 };

767 // Scoped class used when the result of the current expression is not
768 // expected to produce a result.
769 class BytecodeGenerator::EffectResultScope final
770  : public ExpressionResultScope {
771  public:

773  : ExpressionResultScope(generator, kEffect) {}

776 // Scoped class used when the result of the current expression to be
777 // evaluated should go into the interpreter's accumulator.
778 class V8_NODISCARD BytecodeGenerator::ValueResultScope final
779  : public ExpressionResultScope {

782  : ValueResultScope(generator, kValue) {}

789 // Scoped class used when the result of the current expression to be
790 // evaluated is only tested with jumps to two branches.
791 class V8_NODISCARD BytecodeGenerator::TestResultScope final
792  : public ExpressionResultScope {
793  public:
794  TestResultScope(BytecodeGenerator* generator, BytecodeLabels* then_labels,
795  BytecodeLabels* else_labels, TestFallthrough fallthrough)
796  : ExpressionResultScope(generator, kTest),
797  result_consumed_by_test_(false),
798  fallthrough_(fallthrough),
799  then_labels_(then_labels),
800  else_labels_(else_labels) {}
801 
802  TestResultScope(const TestResultScope&) = delete;
803  TestResultScope& operator=(const TestResultScope&) = delete;
804 
805  // Used when code special cases for TestResultScope and consumes any
806  // possible value by testing and jumping to a then/else label.
807  void SetResultConsumedByTest() { result_consumed_by_test_ = true; }
808  bool result_consumed_by_test() { return result_consumed_by_test_; }
809 
810  // Inverts the control flow of the operation, swapping the then and else
811  // labels and the fallthrough.
812  void InvertControlFlow() {
813  std::swap(then_labels_, else_labels_);
814  fallthrough_ = inverted_fallthrough();
815  }
816 
817  BytecodeLabel* NewThenLabel() { return then_labels_->New(); }
818  BytecodeLabel* NewElseLabel() { return else_labels_->New(); }
819 
820  BytecodeLabels* then_labels() const { return then_labels_; }
821  BytecodeLabels* else_labels() const { return else_labels_; }
822 
823  void set_then_labels(BytecodeLabels* then_labels) {
824  then_labels_ = then_labels;
825  }
826  void set_else_labels(BytecodeLabels* else_labels) {
827  else_labels_ = else_labels;
828  }
829 
830  TestFallthrough fallthrough() const { return fallthrough_; }
831  TestFallthrough inverted_fallthrough() const {
832  switch (fallthrough_) {
833  case TestFallthrough::kThen:
834  return TestFallthrough::kElse;
835  case TestFallthrough::kElse:
836  return TestFallthrough::kThen;
837  default:
838  return TestFallthrough::kNone;
839  }
840  }
841  void set_fallthrough(TestFallthrough fallthrough) {
842  fallthrough_ = fallthrough;
843  }
844 
845  private:
846  bool result_consumed_by_test_;
847  TestFallthrough fallthrough_;
848  BytecodeLabels* then_labels_;
849  BytecodeLabels* else_labels_;
850 };
851 
852 // Used to build a list of toplevel declaration data.
853 class BytecodeGenerator::TopLevelDeclarationsBuilder final : public ZoneObject {
854  public:
855  template <typename IsolateT>
856  Handle<FixedArray> AllocateDeclarations(UnoptimizedCompilationInfo* info,
857  BytecodeGenerator* generator,
858  Handle<Script> script,
859  IsolateT* isolate) {
860  DCHECK(has_constant_pool_entry_);
861 
862  Handle<FixedArray> data =
863  isolate->factory()->NewFixedArray(entry_slots_, AllocationType::kOld);
864 
865  int array_index = 0;
866  if (info->scope()->is_module_scope()) {
867  for (Declaration* decl : *info->scope()->declarations()) {
868  Variable* var = decl->var();
869  if (!var->is_used()) continue;
870  if (var->location() != VariableLocation::MODULE) continue;
871 #ifdef DEBUG
872  int start = array_index;
873 #endif
874  if (decl->IsFunctionDeclaration()) {
875  FunctionLiteral* f = static_cast<FunctionDeclaration*>(decl)->fun();
876  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> sfi(
877  Compiler::GetSharedFunctionInfo(f, script, isolate));
878  // Return a null handle if any initial values can't be created. Caller
879  // will set stack overflow.
880  if (sfi.is_null()) return Handle<FixedArray>();
881  data->set(array_index++, *sfi);
882  int literal_index = generator->GetCachedCreateClosureSlot(f);
883  data->set(array_index++, Smi::FromInt(literal_index));
884  DCHECK(var->IsExport());
885  data->set(array_index++, Smi::FromInt(var->index()));
886  DCHECK_EQ(start + kModuleFunctionDeclarationSize, array_index);
887  } else if (var->IsExport() && var->binding_needs_init()) {
888  data->set(array_index++, Smi::FromInt(var->index()));
889  DCHECK_EQ(start + kModuleVariableDeclarationSize, array_index);
890  }
891  }
892  } else {
893  for (Declaration* decl : *info->scope()->declarations()) {
894  Variable* var = decl->var();
895  if (!var->is_used()) continue;
896  if (var->location() != VariableLocation::UNALLOCATED) continue;
897 #ifdef DEBUG
898  int start = array_index;
899 #endif
900  if (decl->IsVariableDeclaration()) {
901  data->set(array_index++, *var->raw_name()->string());
902  DCHECK_EQ(start + kGlobalVariableDeclarationSize, array_index);
903  } else {
904  FunctionLiteral* f = static_cast<FunctionDeclaration*>(decl)->fun();
905  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> sfi(
906  Compiler::GetSharedFunctionInfo(f, script, isolate));
907  // Return a null handle if any initial values can't be created. Caller
908  // will set stack overflow.
909  if (sfi.is_null()) return Handle<FixedArray>();
910  data->set(array_index++, *sfi);
911  int literal_index = generator->GetCachedCreateClosureSlot(f);
912  data->set(array_index++, Smi::FromInt(literal_index));
913  DCHECK_EQ(start + kGlobalFunctionDeclarationSize, array_index);
914  }
915  }
916  }
917  DCHECK_EQ(array_index, data->length());
918  return data;
919  }
920 
921  size_t constant_pool_entry() {
922  DCHECK(has_constant_pool_entry_);
923  return constant_pool_entry_;
924  }
925 
926  void set_constant_pool_entry(size_t constant_pool_entry) {
927  DCHECK(has_top_level_declaration());
928  DCHECK(!has_constant_pool_entry_);
929  constant_pool_entry_ = constant_pool_entry;
930  has_constant_pool_entry_ = true;
931  }
932 
933  void record_global_variable_declaration() {
934  entry_slots_ += kGlobalVariableDeclarationSize;
935  }
936  void record_global_function_declaration() {
937  entry_slots_ += kGlobalFunctionDeclarationSize;
938  }
939  void record_module_variable_declaration() {
940  entry_slots_ += kModuleVariableDeclarationSize;
941  }
942  void record_module_function_declaration() {
943  entry_slots_ += kModuleFunctionDeclarationSize;
944  }
945  bool has_top_level_declaration() { return entry_slots_ > 0; }
946  bool processed() { return processed_; }
947  void mark_processed() { processed_ = true; }
948 
949  private:
950  const int kGlobalVariableDeclarationSize = 1;
951  const int kGlobalFunctionDeclarationSize = 2;
952  const int kModuleVariableDeclarationSize = 1;
953  const int kModuleFunctionDeclarationSize = 3;
954 
955  size_t constant_pool_entry_ = 0;
956  int entry_slots_ = 0;
957  bool has_constant_pool_entry_ = false;
958  bool processed_ = false;
959 };
960 
961 class V8_NODISCARD BytecodeGenerator::CurrentScope final {
962  public:
963  CurrentScope(BytecodeGenerator* generator, Scope* scope)
964  : generator_(generator), outer_scope_(generator->current_scope()) {
965  if (scope != nullptr) {
966  DCHECK_EQ(outer_scope_, scope->outer_scope());
967  generator_->set_current_scope(scope);
968  }
969  }
970  ~CurrentScope() {
971  if (outer_scope_ != generator_->current_scope()) {
972  generator_->set_current_scope(outer_scope_);
973  }
974  }
975  CurrentScope(const CurrentScope&) = delete;
976  CurrentScope& operator=(const CurrentScope&) = delete;
977 
978  private:
979  BytecodeGenerator* generator_;
980  Scope* outer_scope_;
981 };
982 
983 class V8_NODISCARD BytecodeGenerator::MultipleEntryBlockContextScope {
984  public:
985  MultipleEntryBlockContextScope(BytecodeGenerator* generator, Scope* scope)
986  : generator_(generator), scope_(scope), is_in_scope_(false) {
987  if (scope) {
988  inner_context_ = generator->register_allocator()->NewRegister();
989  outer_context_ = generator->register_allocator()->NewRegister();
990  generator->BuildNewLocalBlockContext(scope_);
991  generator->builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(inner_context_);
992  }
993  }
994 
995  void SetEnteredIf(bool condition) {
996  RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(generator_);
997  if (condition && scope_ != nullptr && !is_in_scope_) {
998  EnterScope();
999  } else if (!condition && is_in_scope_) {
1000  ExitScope();
1001  }
1002  }
1003 
1004  ~MultipleEntryBlockContextScope() { DCHECK(!is_in_scope_); }
1005 
1006  MultipleEntryBlockContextScope(const MultipleEntryBlockContextScope&) =
1007  delete;
1008  MultipleEntryBlockContextScope& operator=(
1009  const MultipleEntryBlockContextScope&) = delete;
1010 
1011  private:
1012  void EnterScope() {
1013  DCHECK(inner_context_.is_valid());
1014  DCHECK(outer_context_.is_valid());
1015  DCHECK(!is_in_scope_);
1016  generator_->builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(inner_context_);
1017  current_scope_.emplace(generator_, scope_);
1018  context_scope_.emplace(generator_, scope_, outer_context_);
1019  is_in_scope_ = true;
1020  }
1021 
1022  void ExitScope() {
1023  DCHECK(inner_context_.is_valid());
1024  DCHECK(outer_context_.is_valid());
1025  DCHECK(is_in_scope_);
1026  context_scope_ = std::nullopt;
1027  current_scope_ = std::nullopt;
1028  is_in_scope_ = false;
1029  }
1030 
1031  BytecodeGenerator* generator_;
1032  Scope* scope_;
1033  Register inner_context_;
1034  Register outer_context_;
1035  bool is_in_scope_;
1036  std::optional<CurrentScope> current_scope_;
1037  std::optional<ContextScope> context_scope_;
1038 };

1040 class BytecodeGenerator::FeedbackSlotCache : public ZoneObject {
1041  public:
1042  enum class SlotKind {
1043  kStoreGlobalSloppy,
1044  kStoreGlobalStrict,
1045  kSetNamedStrict,
1046  kSetNamedSloppy,
1047  kLoadProperty,
1048  kLoadSuperProperty,
1049  kLoadGlobalNotInsideTypeof,
1050  kLoadGlobalInsideTypeof,
1051  kClosureFeedbackCell
1052  };
1053 
1054  explicit FeedbackSlotCache(Zone* zone) : map_(zone) {}
1055 
1056  void Put(SlotKind slot_kind, Variable* variable, int slot_index) {
1057  PutImpl(slot_kind, 0, variable, slot_index);
1058  }
1059  void Put(SlotKind slot_kind, AstNode* node, int slot_index) {
1060  PutImpl(slot_kind, 0, node, slot_index);
1061  }
1062  void Put(SlotKind slot_kind, int variable_index, const AstRawString* name,
1063  int slot_index) {
1064  PutImpl(slot_kind, variable_index, name, slot_index);
1065  }
1066  void Put(SlotKind slot_kind, const AstRawString* name, int slot_index) {
1067  PutImpl(slot_kind, 0, name, slot_index);
1068  }
1069 
1070  int Get(SlotKind slot_kind, Variable* variable) const {
1071  return GetImpl(slot_kind, 0, variable);
1072  }
1073  int Get(SlotKind slot_kind, AstNode* node) const {
1074  return GetImpl(slot_kind, 0, node);
1075  }
1076  int Get(SlotKind slot_kind, int variable_index,
1077  const AstRawString* name) const {
1078  return GetImpl(slot_kind, variable_index, name);
1079  }
1080  int Get(SlotKind slot_kind, const AstRawString* name) const {
1081  return GetImpl(slot_kind, 0, name);
1082  }
1083 
1084  private:
1085  using Key = std::tuple<SlotKind, int, const void*>;
1086 
1087  void PutImpl(SlotKind slot_kind, int index, const void* node,
1088  int slot_index) {
1089  Key key = std::make_tuple(slot_kind, index, node);
1090  auto entry = std::make_pair(key, slot_index);
1091  map_.insert(entry);
1092  }
1093 
1094  int GetImpl(SlotKind slot_kind, int index, const void* node) const {
1095  Key key = std::make_tuple(slot_kind, index, node);
1096  auto iter = map_.find(key);
1097  if (iter != map_.end()) {
1098  return iter->second;
1099  }
1100  return -1;
1101  }
1102 
1103  ZoneMap<Key, int> map_;
1104 };
1105 
1106 // Scoped class to help elide hole checks within a conditionally executed basic
1107 // block. Each conditionally executed basic block must have a scope to emit
1108 // hole checks correctly.
1109 //
1110 // The duration of the scope must correspond to a basic block. Numbered
1111 // Variables (see Variable::HoleCheckBitmap) are remembered in the bitmap when
1112 // the first hole check is emitted. Subsequent hole checks are elided.
1113 //
1114 // On scope exit, the hole check state at construction time is restored.
1115 class V8_NODISCARD BytecodeGenerator::HoleCheckElisionScope {
1116  public:
1117  explicit HoleCheckElisionScope(BytecodeGenerator* bytecode_generator)
1118  : HoleCheckElisionScope(&bytecode_generator->hole_check_bitmap_) {}
1119 
1120  ~HoleCheckElisionScope() { *bitmap_ = prev_bitmap_value_; }
1121 
1122  protected:
1123  explicit HoleCheckElisionScope(Variable::HoleCheckBitmap* bitmap)
1124  : bitmap_(bitmap), prev_bitmap_value_(*bitmap) {}
1125 
1126  Variable::HoleCheckBitmap* bitmap_;
1127  Variable::HoleCheckBitmap prev_bitmap_value_;
1128 };
1129 
1130 // Scoped class to help elide hole checks within control flow that branch and
1131 // merge.
1132 //
1133 // Each such control flow construct (e.g., if-else, ternary expressions) must
1134 // have a scope to emit hole checks correctly. Additionally, each branch must
1135 // have a Branch.
1136 //
1137 // The Merge or MergeIf method must be called to merge variables that have been
1138 // hole-checked along every branch are marked as no longer needing a hole check.
1139 //
1140 // Example:
1141 //
1142 // HoleCheckElisionMergeScope merge_elider(this);
1143 // {
1144 // HoleCheckElisionMergeScope::Branch branch_elider(merge_elider);
1145 // Visit(then_branch);
1146 // }
1147 // {
1148 // HoleCheckElisionMergeScope::Branch branch_elider(merge_elider);
1149 // Visit(else_branch);
1150 // }
1151 // merge_elider.Merge();
1152 //
1153 // Conversely, it is incorrect to use this class for control flow constructs
1154 // that do not merge (e.g., if without else). HoleCheckElisionScope should be
1155 // used for those cases.
1156 class V8_NODISCARD BytecodeGenerator::HoleCheckElisionMergeScope final {
1157  public:
1158  explicit HoleCheckElisionMergeScope(BytecodeGenerator* bytecode_generator)
1159  : bitmap_(&bytecode_generator->hole_check_bitmap_) {}
1160 
1161  ~HoleCheckElisionMergeScope() {
1162  // Did you forget to call Merge or MergeIf?
1163  DCHECK(merge_called_);
1164  }
1165 
1166  void Merge() {
1167  DCHECK_NE(UINT64_MAX, merge_value_);
1168  *bitmap_ = merge_value_;
1169 #ifdef DEBUG
1170  merge_called_ = true;
1171 #endif
1172  }
1173 
1174  void MergeIf(bool cond) {
1175  if (cond) Merge();
1176 #ifdef DEBUG
1177  merge_called_ = true;
1178 #endif
1179  }
1180 
1181  class V8_NODISCARD Branch final : public HoleCheckElisionScope {
1182  public:
1183  explicit Branch(HoleCheckElisionMergeScope& merge_into)
1184  : HoleCheckElisionScope(merge_into.bitmap_),
1185  merge_into_bitmap_(&merge_into.merge_value_) {}
1186 
1187  ~Branch() { *merge_into_bitmap_ &= *bitmap_; }
1188 
1189  private:
1190  Variable::HoleCheckBitmap* merge_into_bitmap_;
1191  };
1192 
1193  private:
1194  Variable::HoleCheckBitmap* bitmap_;
1195  Variable::HoleCheckBitmap merge_value_ = UINT64_MAX;
1196 
1197 #ifdef DEBUG
1198  bool merge_called_ = false;
1199 #endif
1200 };

1241 // LoopScope delimits the scope of {loop}, from its header to its final jump.
1242 // It should be constructed iff a (conceptual) back edge should be produced. In
1243 // the case of creating a LoopBuilder but never emitting the loop, it is valid
1244 // to skip the creation of LoopScope.
1245 class V8_NODISCARD BytecodeGenerator::LoopScope final {
1246  public:
1247  explicit LoopScope(BytecodeGenerator* bytecode_generator, LoopBuilder* loop)
1248  : bytecode_generator_(bytecode_generator),
1249  parent_loop_scope_(bytecode_generator_->current_loop_scope()),
1250  loop_builder_(loop) {
1251  loop_builder_->LoopHeader();
1252  bytecode_generator_->set_current_loop_scope(this);
1253  bytecode_generator_->loop_depth_++;
1254  }
1255 
1256  ~LoopScope() {
1257  bytecode_generator_->loop_depth_--;
1258  bytecode_generator_->set_current_loop_scope(parent_loop_scope_);
1259  DCHECK_GE(bytecode_generator_->loop_depth_, 0);
1260  loop_builder_->JumpToHeader(
1261  bytecode_generator_->loop_depth_,
1262  parent_loop_scope_ ? parent_loop_scope_->loop_builder_ : nullptr);
1263  }
1264 
1265  private:
1266  BytecodeGenerator* const bytecode_generator_;
1267  LoopScope* const parent_loop_scope_;
1268  LoopBuilder* const loop_builder_;
1269 };

1271 class V8_NODISCARD BytecodeGenerator::ForInScope final {
1272  public:
1273  explicit ForInScope(BytecodeGenerator* bytecode_generator,
1274  ForInStatement* stmt, Register enum_index,
1275  Register cache_type)
1276  : bytecode_generator_(bytecode_generator),
1277  parent_for_in_scope_(bytecode_generator_->current_for_in_scope()),
1278  each_var_(nullptr),
1279  enum_index_(enum_index),
1280  cache_type_(cache_type) {
1281  if (v8_flags.enable_enumerated_keyed_access_bytecode) {
1282  Expression* each = stmt->each();
1283  if (each->IsVariableProxy()) {
1284  Variable* each_var = each->AsVariableProxy()->var();
1285  if (each_var->IsStackLocal()) {
1286  each_var_ = each_var;
1287  bytecode_generator_->SetVariableInRegister(
1288  each_var_,
1289  bytecode_generator_->builder()->Local(each_var_->index()));
1290  }
1291  }
1292  bytecode_generator_->set_current_for_in_scope(this);
1293  }
1294  }
1295 
1296  ~ForInScope() {
1297  if (v8_flags.enable_enumerated_keyed_access_bytecode) {
1298  bytecode_generator_->set_current_for_in_scope(parent_for_in_scope_);
1299  }
1300  }
1301 
1302  // Get corresponding {ForInScope} for a given {each} variable.
1303  ForInScope* GetForInScope(Variable* each) {
1304  DCHECK(v8_flags.enable_enumerated_keyed_access_bytecode);
1305  ForInScope* scope = this;
1306  do {
1307  if (each == scope->each_var_) break;
1308  scope = scope->parent_for_in_scope_;
1309  } while (scope != nullptr);
1310  return scope;
1311  }
1312 
1313  Register enum_index() { return enum_index_; }
1314  Register cache_type() { return cache_type_; }
1315 
1316  private:
1317  BytecodeGenerator* const bytecode_generator_;
1318  ForInScope* const parent_for_in_scope_;
1319  Variable* each_var_;
1320  Register enum_index_;
1321  Register cache_type_;
1322 };

1324 class V8_NODISCARD BytecodeGenerator::DisposablesStackScope final {
1325  public:
1326  explicit DisposablesStackScope(BytecodeGenerator* bytecode_generator)
1327  : bytecode_generator_(bytecode_generator),
1328  prev_disposables_stack_(
1329  bytecode_generator_->current_disposables_stack_) {
1330  bytecode_generator_->set_current_disposables_stack(
1331  bytecode_generator->register_allocator()->NewRegister());
1332  bytecode_generator->builder()->CallRuntime(
1333  Runtime::kInitializeDisposableStack);
1334  bytecode_generator->builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(
1335  bytecode_generator_->current_disposables_stack());
1336  }
1337 
1338  ~DisposablesStackScope() {
1339  bytecode_generator_->set_current_disposables_stack(prev_disposables_stack_);
1340  }
1341 
1342  private:
1343  BytecodeGenerator* const bytecode_generator_;
1344  Register prev_disposables_stack_;
1345 };

1347 namespace {

1349 template <typename PropertyT>
1350 struct Accessors : public ZoneObject {
1351  Accessors() : getter(nullptr), setter(nullptr) {}
1352  PropertyT* getter;
1353  PropertyT* setter;
1354 };
1355 
1356 // A map from property names to getter/setter pairs allocated in the zone that
1357 // also provides a way of accessing the pairs in the order they were first
1358 // added so that the generated bytecode is always the same.
1359 template <typename PropertyT>
1360 class AccessorTable
1361  : public base::TemplateHashMap<Literal, Accessors<PropertyT>,
1362  bool (*)(void*, void*),
1363  ZoneAllocationPolicy> {
1364  public:
1365  explicit AccessorTable(Zone* zone)
1366  : base::TemplateHashMap<Literal, Accessors<PropertyT>,
1367  bool (*)(void*, void*), ZoneAllocationPolicy>(
1368  Literal::Match, ZoneAllocationPolicy(zone)),
1369  zone_(zone) {}
1370 
1371  Accessors<PropertyT>* LookupOrInsert(Literal* key) {
1372  auto it = this->find(key, true);
1373  if (it->second == nullptr) {
1374  it->second = zone_->New<Accessors<PropertyT>>();
1375  ordered_accessors_.push_back({key, it->second});
1376  }
1377  return it->second;
1378  }
1379 
1380  const std::vector<std::pair<Literal*, Accessors<PropertyT>*>>&
1381  ordered_accessors() {
1382  return ordered_accessors_;
1383  }
1384 
1385  private:
1386  std::vector<std::pair<Literal*, Accessors<PropertyT>*>> ordered_accessors_;
1387 
1388  Zone* zone_;
1389 };
1390 
1391 } // namespace

1396  FunctionLiteral* literal,
1397  const std::vector<FunctionLiteral*>& eager_literals) {
1398  for (FunctionLiteral* eager_literal : eager_literals) {
1399  if (literal == eager_literal) return true;
1400  }
1401  return false;
1402 }

1478 template <typename IsolateT>
1479 Handle<BytecodeArray> BytecodeGenerator::FinalizeBytecode(
1480  IsolateT* isolate, Handle<Script> script) {
1481  DCHECK_EQ(ThreadId::Current(), isolate->thread_id());
1482 #ifdef DEBUG
1483  // Unoptimized compilation should be context-independent. Verify that we don't
1484  // access the native context by nulling it out during finalization.
1485  NullContextScopeFor<IsolateT> null_context_scope(isolate);
1486 #endif
1487 
1488  AllocateDeferredConstants(isolate, script);
1489 
1490  if (block_coverage_builder_) {
1491  Handle<CoverageInfo> coverage_info =
1492  isolate->factory()->NewCoverageInfo(block_coverage_builder_->slots());
1493  info()->set_coverage_info(coverage_info);
1494  if (v8_flags.trace_block_coverage) {
1495  StdoutStream os;
1496  coverage_info->CoverageInfoPrint(os, info()->literal()->GetDebugName());
1497  }
1498  }
1499 
1500  if (HasStackOverflow()) return Handle<BytecodeArray>();
1501  Handle<BytecodeArray> bytecode_array = builder()->ToBytecodeArray(isolate);
1502 
1503  if (incoming_new_target_or_generator_.is_valid()) {
1504  bytecode_array->set_incoming_new_target_or_generator_register(
1505  incoming_new_target_or_generator_);
1506  }
1507 
1508  return bytecode_array;
1509 }

1512  Isolate* isolate, Handle<Script> script);
1513 template Handle<BytecodeArray> BytecodeGenerator::FinalizeBytecode(
1514  LocalIsolate* isolate, Handle<Script> script);

1520 #ifdef DEBUG

1522  // access the native context by nulling it out during finalization.

1547 
1548 template <typename IsolateT>
1549 void BytecodeGenerator::AllocateDeferredConstants(IsolateT* isolate,
1550  Handle<Script> script) {
1551  if (top_level_builder()->has_top_level_declaration()) {
1552  // Build global declaration pair array.
1553  Handle<FixedArray> declarations = top_level_builder()->AllocateDeclarations(
1554  info(), this, script, isolate);
1555  if (declarations.is_null()) return SetStackOverflow();
1556  builder()->SetDeferredConstantPoolEntry(
1557  top_level_builder()->constant_pool_entry(), declarations);
1558  }
1559 
1560  // Find or build shared function infos.
1561  for (std::pair<FunctionLiteral*, size_t> literal : function_literals_) {
1562  FunctionLiteral* expr = literal.first;
1563  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info =
1564  Compiler::GetSharedFunctionInfo(expr, script, isolate);
1565  if (shared_info.is_null()) return SetStackOverflow();
1566  builder()->SetDeferredConstantPoolEntry(
1567  literal.second, indirect_handle(shared_info, isolate));
1568  }
1569 
1570  // Find or build shared function infos for the native function templates.
1571  for (std::pair<NativeFunctionLiteral*, size_t> literal :
1572  native_function_literals_) {
1573  // This should only happen for main-thread compilations.
1574  DCHECK((std::is_same_v<Isolate, v8::internal::Isolate>));
1575 
1576  NativeFunctionLiteral* expr = literal.first;
1577  v8::Isolate* v8_isolate = reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(isolate);
1578 
1579  // Compute the function template for the native function.
1580  v8::Local<v8::FunctionTemplate> info =
1581  expr->extension()->GetNativeFunctionTemplate(
1582  v8_isolate, Utils::ToLocal(expr->name()));
1583  DCHECK(!info.IsEmpty());
1584 
1585  Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info =
1586  FunctionTemplateInfo::GetOrCreateSharedFunctionInfo(
1587  isolate, Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*info), expr->name());
1588  DCHECK(!shared_info.is_null());
1589  builder()->SetDeferredConstantPoolEntry(literal.second, shared_info);
1590  }
1591 
1592  for (std::pair<Call*, Scope*> call : eval_calls_) {
1593  Tagged<ScopeInfo> current;
1594  int index = call.first->eval_scope_info_index();
1595  if (script->infos()->get(index).GetHeapObjectIfWeak(&current) &&
1596  v8_flags.reuse_scope_infos) {
1597  CHECK_EQ(current, *call.second->scope_info());
1598  } else {
1599  script->infos()->set(call.first->eval_scope_info_index(),
1600  MakeWeak(*call.second->scope_info()));
1601  }
1602  }
1603 
1604  // Build object literal constant properties
1605  for (std::pair<ObjectLiteralBoilerplateBuilder*, size_t> literal :
1606  object_literals_) {
1607  ObjectLiteralBoilerplateBuilder* object_literal_builder = literal.first;
1608  if (object_literal_builder->properties_count() > 0) {
1609  // If constant properties is an empty fixed array, we've already added it
1610  // to the constant pool when visiting the object literal.
1611  Handle<ObjectBoilerplateDescription> constant_properties =
1612  object_literal_builder->GetOrBuildBoilerplateDescription(isolate);
1613 
1614  builder()->SetDeferredConstantPoolEntry(literal.second,
1615  constant_properties);
1616  }
1617  }
1618 
1619  // Build array literal constant elements
1620  for (std::pair<ArrayLiteralBoilerplateBuilder*, size_t> literal :
1621  array_literals_) {
1622  ArrayLiteralBoilerplateBuilder* array_literal_builder = literal.first;
1623  Handle<ArrayBoilerplateDescription> constant_elements =
1624  array_literal_builder->GetOrBuildBoilerplateDescription(isolate);
1625  builder()->SetDeferredConstantPoolEntry(literal.second, constant_elements);
1626  }
1627 
1628  // Build class literal boilerplates.
1629  for (std::pair<ClassLiteral*, size_t> literal : class_literals_) {
1630  ClassLiteral* class_literal = literal.first;
1631  Handle<ClassBoilerplate> class_boilerplate =
1632  ClassBoilerplate::New(isolate, class_literal, AllocationType::kOld);
1633  builder()->SetDeferredConstantPoolEntry(literal.second, class_boilerplate);
1634  }
1635 
1636  // Build template literals.
1637  for (std::pair<GetTemplateObject*, size_t> literal : template_objects_) {
1638  GetTemplateObject* get_template_object = literal.first;
1639  Handle<TemplateObjectDescription> description =
1640  get_template_object->GetOrBuildDescription(isolate);
1641  builder()->SetDeferredConstantPoolEntry(literal.second, description);
1642  }
1643 }
1644 
1645 template void BytecodeGenerator::AllocateDeferredConstants(
1646  Isolate* isolate, Handle<Script> script);
1647 template void BytecodeGenerator::AllocateDeferredConstants(
1648  LocalIsolate* isolate, Handle<Script> script);
1649 
1650 namespace {
1651 bool NeedsContextInitialization(DeclarationScope* scope) {
1652  return scope->NeedsContext() && !scope->is_script_scope() &&
1653  !scope->is_module_scope();
1654 }
1655 } // namespace
1656 
1657 void BytecodeGenerator::GenerateBytecode(uintptr_t stack_limit) {
1658  InitializeAstVisitor(stack_limit);
1659  if (v8_flags.stress_lazy_compilation && local_isolate_->is_main_thread() &&
1660  !local_isolate_->AsIsolate()->bootstrapper()->IsActive()) {
1661  // Trigger stack overflow with 1/stress_lazy_compilation probability.
1662  // Do this only for the main thread compilations because querying random
1663  // numbers from background threads will make the random values dependent
1664  // on the thread scheduling and thus non-deterministic.
1665  stack_overflow_ = local_isolate_->fuzzer_rng()->NextInt(
1666  v8_flags.stress_lazy_compilation) == 0;
1667  }
1668 
1669  // Initialize the incoming context.
1670  ContextScope incoming_context(this, closure_scope());
1671 
1672  // Initialize control scope.
1673  ControlScopeForTopLevel control(this);
1674 
1675  RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
1676 
1677  AllocateTopLevelRegisters();
1678 
1679  builder()->EmitFunctionStartSourcePosition(
1680  info()->literal()->start_position());
1681 
1682  if (info()->literal()->CanSuspend()) {
1683  BuildGeneratorPrologue();
1684  }
1685 
1686  if (NeedsContextInitialization(closure_scope())) {
1687  // Push a new inner context scope for the function.
1688  BuildNewLocalActivationContext();
1689  ContextScope local_function_context(this, closure_scope());
1690  BuildLocalActivationContextInitialization();
1691  GenerateBytecodeBody();
1692  } else {
1693  GenerateBytecodeBody();
1694  }
1695 
1696  // Reset variables with hole check bitmap indices for subsequent compilations
1697  // in the same parsing zone.
1698  for (Variable* var : vars_in_hole_check_bitmap_) {
1699  var->ResetHoleCheckBitmapIndex();
1700  }
1701 
1702  // Check that we are not falling off the end.
1703  DCHECK(builder()->RemainderOfBlockIsDead());
1704 }
1705 
1706 void BytecodeGenerator::GenerateBytecodeBody() {
1707  GenerateBodyPrologue();
1708 
1709  if (IsBaseConstructor(function_kind())) {
1710  GenerateBaseConstructorBody();
1711  } else if (function_kind() == FunctionKind::kDerivedConstructor) {
1712  GenerateDerivedConstructorBody();
1713  } else if (IsAsyncFunction(function_kind()) ||
1714  IsModuleWithTopLevelAwait(function_kind())) {
1715  if (IsAsyncGeneratorFunction(function_kind())) {
1716  GenerateAsyncGeneratorFunctionBody();
1717  } else {
1718  GenerateAsyncFunctionBody();
1719  }
1720  } else {
1721  int start = 0;
1722  if (BuildInitializationBlockForParametersIfExist()) {
1723  start = 1;
1724  }
1725  if (IsResumableFunction(info()->literal()->kind())) {
1726  BuildGeneratorObjectVariableInitialization();
1727  }
1728 
1729  GenerateBodyStatements(start);
1730  }
1731 }
1732 
1733 void BytecodeGenerator::GenerateBodyPrologue() {
1734  // Build the arguments object if it is used.
1735  VisitArgumentsObject(closure_scope()->arguments());
1736 
1737  // Build rest arguments array if it is used.
1738  Variable* rest_parameter = closure_scope()->rest_parameter();
1739  VisitRestArgumentsArray(rest_parameter);
1740 
1741  // Build assignment to the function name or {.this_function}
1742  // variables if used.
1743  VisitThisFunctionVariable(closure_scope()->function_var());
1744  VisitThisFunctionVariable(closure_scope()->this_function_var());
1745 
1746  // Build assignment to {new.target} variable if it is used.
1747  VisitNewTargetVariable(closure_scope()->new_target_var());
1748 
1749  FunctionLiteral* literal = info()->literal();
1750  // Emit tracing call if requested to do so.
1751  if (v8_flags.trace) builder()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kTraceEnter);
1752 
1753  // Increment the function-scope block coverage counter.
1754  BuildIncrementBlockCoverageCounterIfEnabled(literal, SourceRangeKind::kBody);
1755 
1756  // Visit declarations within the function scope.
1757  if (closure_scope()->is_script_scope()) {
1758  VisitGlobalDeclarations(closure_scope()->declarations());
1759  } else if (closure_scope()->is_module_scope()) {
1760  VisitModuleDeclarations(closure_scope()->declarations());
1761  } else {
1762  VisitDeclarations(closure_scope()->declarations());
1763  }
1764 
1765  // Emit initializing assignments for module namespace imports (if any).
1766  VisitModuleNamespaceImports();
1767 }
1768 
1769 void BytecodeGenerator::GenerateBaseConstructorBody() {
1770  DCHECK(IsBaseConstructor(function_kind()));
1771 
1772  FunctionLiteral* literal = info()->literal();
1773 
1774  // The derived constructor case is handled in VisitCallSuper.
1775  if (literal->class_scope_has_private_brand()) {
1776  ClassScope* scope = info()->scope()->outer_scope()->AsClassScope();
1777  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(scope->brand());
1778  BuildPrivateBrandInitialization(builder()->Receiver(), scope->brand());
1779  }
1780 
1781  if (literal->requires_instance_members_initializer()) {
1782  BuildInstanceMemberInitialization(Register::function_closure(),
1783  builder()->Receiver());
1784  }
1785 
1786  GenerateBodyStatements();
1787 }
1788 
1789 void BytecodeGenerator::GenerateDerivedConstructorBody() {
1790  DCHECK_EQ(FunctionKind::kDerivedConstructor, function_kind());
1791 
1792  FunctionLiteral* literal = info()->literal();
1793 
1794  // Per spec, derived constructors can only return undefined or an object;
1795  // other primitives trigger an exception in ConstructStub.
1796  //
1797  // Since the receiver is popped by the callee, derived constructors return
1798  // <this> if the original return value was undefined.
1799  //
1800  // Also per spec, this return value check is done after all user code (e.g.,
1801  // finally blocks) are executed. For example, the following code does not
1802  // throw.
1803  //
1804  // class C extends class {} {
1805  // constructor() {
1806  // try { throw 42; }
1807  // catch(e) { return; }
1808  // finally { super(); }
1809  // }
1810  // }
1811  // new C();
1812  //
1813  // This check is implemented by jumping to the check instead of emitting a
1814  // return bytecode in-place inside derived constructors.
1815  //
1816  // Note that default derived constructors do not need this check as they
1817  // just forward a super call.
1818 
1819  BytecodeLabels check_return_value(zone());
1820  Register result = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
1821  ControlScopeForDerivedConstructor control(this, result, &check_return_value);
1822 
1823  {
1824  HoleCheckElisionScope elider(this);
1825  GenerateBodyStatementsWithoutImplicitFinalReturn();
1826  }
1827 
1828  if (check_return_value.empty()) {
1829  if (!builder()->RemainderOfBlockIsDead()) {
1830  BuildThisVariableLoad();
1831  BuildReturn(literal->return_position());
1832  }
1833  } else {
1834  BytecodeLabels return_this(zone());
1835 
1836  if (!builder()->RemainderOfBlockIsDead()) {
1837  builder()->Jump(return_this.New());
1838  }
1839 
1840  check_return_value.Bind(builder());
1841  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(result);
1842  builder()->JumpIfUndefined(return_this.New());
1843  BuildReturn(literal->return_position());
1844 
1845  {
1846  return_this.Bind(builder());
1847  BuildThisVariableLoad();
1848  BuildReturn(literal->return_position());
1849  }
1850  }
1851 }
1852 
1853 void BytecodeGenerator::GenerateAsyncFunctionBody() {
1854  DCHECK((IsAsyncFunction(function_kind()) &&
1855  !IsAsyncGeneratorFunction(function_kind())) ||
1856  IsModuleWithTopLevelAwait(function_kind()));
1857 
1858  // Async functions always return promises. Return values fulfill that promise,
1859  // while synchronously thrown exceptions reject that promise. This is handled
1860  // by surrounding the body statements in a try-catch block as follows:
1861  //
1862  // try {
1863  // <inner_block>
1864  // } catch (.catch) {
1865  // return %_AsyncFunctionReject(.generator_object, .catch);
1866  // }
1867 
1868  FunctionLiteral* literal = info()->literal();
1869  BuildGeneratorObjectVariableInitialization();
1870 
1871  HandlerTable::CatchPrediction outer_catch_prediction = catch_prediction();
1872  // When compiling a REPL script, use UNCAUGHT_ASYNC_AWAIT to preserve the
1873  // pending message so DevTools can inspect it.
1874  set_catch_prediction(literal->scope()->is_repl_mode_scope()
1875  ? HandlerTable::UNCAUGHT_ASYNC_AWAIT
1876  : HandlerTable::ASYNC_AWAIT);
1877 
1878  BuildTryCatch(
1879  [&]() {
1880  GenerateBodyStatements();
1881  set_catch_prediction(outer_catch_prediction);
1882  },
1883  [&](Register context) {
1884  RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
1885  builder()
1886  ->MoveRegister(generator_object(), args[0])
1887  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[1]); // exception
1888  if (!literal->scope()->is_repl_mode_scope()) {
1889  builder()->LoadTheHole().SetPendingMessage();
1890  }
1891  builder()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kInlineAsyncFunctionReject, args);
1892  // TODO(358404372): Should this return have a statement position?
1893  // Without one it is not possible to apply a debugger breakpoint.
1894  BuildReturn(kNoSourcePosition);
1895  },
1896  catch_prediction());
1897 }
1898 
1899 bool BytecodeGenerator::BuildInitializationBlockForParametersIfExist() {
1900  ZonePtrList<Statement>* body = info()->literal()->body();
1901  if (body->length() > 0 && body->at(0)->IsBlock()) {
1902  Block* block = body->at(0)->AsBlock();
1903  if (block->is_initialization_block_for_parameters()) {
1904  RegisterAllocationScope allocation_scope(this);
1905  VisitBlockDeclarationsAndStatements(block);
1906  return true;
1907  }
1908  }
1909  return false;
1910 }
1911 
1912 void BytecodeGenerator::GenerateAsyncGeneratorFunctionBody() {
1913  DCHECK(IsAsyncGeneratorFunction(function_kind()));
1914  set_catch_prediction(HandlerTable::ASYNC_AWAIT);
1915 
1916  // For ES2017 Async Generators, we produce:
1917  //
1918  // try {
1919  // InitialYield;
1920  // ...body...;
1921  // } catch (.catch) {
1922  // %AsyncGeneratorReject(generator, .catch);
1923  // } finally {
1924  // %_GeneratorClose(generator);
1925  // }
1926  //
1927  // - InitialYield yields the actual generator object.
1928  // - Any return statement inside the body will have its argument wrapped
1929  // in an iterator result object with a "done" property set to `true`.
1930  // - If the generator terminates for whatever reason, we must close it.
1931  // Hence the finally clause.
1932  // - BytecodeGenerator performs special handling for ReturnStatements in
1933  // async generator functions, resolving the appropriate Promise with an
1934  // "done" iterator result object containing a Promise-unwrapped value.
1935 
1936  // In async generator functions, when parameters are not simple,
1937  // a parameter initialization block will be added as the first block to the
1938  // AST. Since this block can throw synchronously, it should not be wrapped
1939  // in the following try-finally. We visit this block outside the try-finally
1940  // and remove it from the AST.
1941  int start = 0;
1942  if (BuildInitializationBlockForParametersIfExist()) {
1943  start = 1;
1944  }
1945  BuildGeneratorObjectVariableInitialization();
1946 
1947  BuildTryFinally(
1948  [&]() {
1949  BuildTryCatch(
1950  [&]() { GenerateBodyStatements(start); },
1951  [&](Register context) {
1952  RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
1953  RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
1954  builder()
1955  ->MoveRegister(generator_object(), args[0])
1956  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[1]) // exception
1957  .LoadTheHole()
1958  .SetPendingMessage()
1959  .CallRuntime(Runtime::kInlineAsyncGeneratorReject, args);
1960  execution_control()->ReturnAccumulator(kNoSourcePosition);
1961  },
1962  catch_prediction());
1963  },
1964  [&](Register body_continuation_token, Register body_continuation_result,
1965  Register message) {
1966  RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
1967  Register arg = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
1968  builder()
1969  ->MoveRegister(generator_object(), arg)
1970  .CallRuntime(Runtime::kInlineGeneratorClose, arg);
1971  },
1972  catch_prediction());
1973 }
1974 
1975 void BytecodeGenerator::GenerateBodyStatements(int start) {
1976  GenerateBodyStatementsWithoutImplicitFinalReturn(start);
1977 
1978  // Emit an implicit return instruction in case control flow can fall off the
1979  // end of the function without an explicit return being present on all paths.
1980  //
1981  // ControlScope is used instead of building the Return bytecode directly, as
1982  // the entire body is wrapped in a try-finally block for async generators.
1983  if (!builder()->RemainderOfBlockIsDead()) {
1984  builder()->LoadUndefined();
1985  const int pos = info()->literal()->return_position();
1986  if (IsAsyncFunction(function_kind()) ||
1987  IsModuleWithTopLevelAwait(function_kind())) {
1988  execution_control()->AsyncReturnAccumulator(pos);
1989  } else {
1990  execution_control()->ReturnAccumulator(pos);
1991  }
1992  }
1993 }
1994 
1995 void BytecodeGenerator::GenerateBodyStatementsWithoutImplicitFinalReturn(
1996  int start) {
1997  ZonePtrList<Statement>* body = info()->literal()->body();
1998  if (v8_flags.js_explicit_resource_management && closure_scope() != nullptr &&
1999  (closure_scope()->has_using_declaration() ||
2000  closure_scope()->has_await_using_declaration())) {
2001  BuildDisposeScope([&]() { VisitStatements(body, start); },
2002  closure_scope()->has_await_using_declaration());
2003  } else {
2004  VisitStatements(body, start);
2005  }
2006 }
2007 
2008 void BytecodeGenerator::AllocateTopLevelRegisters() {
2009  if (IsResumableFunction(info()->literal()->kind())) {
2010  // Either directly use generator_object_var or allocate a new register for
2011  // the incoming generator object.
2012  Variable* generator_object_var = closure_scope()->generator_object_var();
2013  if (generator_object_var->location() == VariableLocation::LOCAL) {
2014  incoming_new_target_or_generator_ =
2015  GetRegisterForLocalVariable(generator_object_var);
2016  } else {
2017  incoming_new_target_or_generator_ = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
2018  }
2019  } else if (closure_scope()->new_target_var()) {
2020  // Either directly use new_target_var or allocate a new register for
2021  // the incoming new target object.
2022  Variable* new_target_var = closure_scope()->new_target_var();
2023  if (new_target_var->location() == VariableLocation::LOCAL) {
2024  incoming_new_target_or_generator_ =
2025  GetRegisterForLocalVariable(new_target_var);
2026  } else {
2027  incoming_new_target_or_generator_ = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
2028  }
2029  }
2030 }
2031 
2032 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildGeneratorPrologue() {
2033  DCHECK_GT(info()->literal()->suspend_count(), 0);
2034  generator_jump_table_ =
2035  builder()->AllocateJumpTable(info()->literal()->suspend_count(), 0);
2036 
2037  // If the generator is not undefined, this is a resume, so perform state
2038  // dispatch.
2039  builder()->SwitchOnGeneratorState(generator_object(), generator_jump_table_);
2040 
2041  // Otherwise, fall-through to the ordinary function prologue, after which we
2042  // will run into the generator object creation and other extra code inserted
2043  // by the parser.
2044 }

2046 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitBlock(Block* stmt) {
2047  // Visit declarations and statements.
2048  CurrentScope current_scope(this, stmt->scope());
2049  if (stmt->scope() != nullptr && stmt->scope()->NeedsContext()) {
2050  BuildNewLocalBlockContext(stmt->scope());
2051  ContextScope scope(this, stmt->scope());
2052  VisitBlockMaybeDispose(stmt);
2053  } else {
2054  VisitBlockMaybeDispose(stmt);
2055  }
2056 }
2057 
2058 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitBlockMaybeDispose(Block* stmt) {
2059  if (v8_flags.js_explicit_resource_management && stmt->scope() != nullptr &&
2060  (stmt->scope()->has_using_declaration() ||
2061  stmt->scope()->has_await_using_declaration())) {
2062  BuildDisposeScope([&]() { VisitBlockDeclarationsAndStatements(stmt); },
2063  stmt->scope()->has_await_using_declaration());
2064  } else {
2065  VisitBlockDeclarationsAndStatements(stmt);
2066  }
2067 }
2068 
2069 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitBlockDeclarationsAndStatements(Block* stmt) {
2070  BlockBuilder block_builder(builder(), block_coverage_builder_, stmt);
2071  ControlScopeForBreakable execution_control(this, stmt, &block_builder);
2072  if (stmt->scope() != nullptr) {
2073  VisitDeclarations(stmt->scope()->declarations());
2074  }
2075  if (V8_UNLIKELY(stmt->is_breakable())) {
2076  // Loathsome labeled blocks can be the target of break statements, which
2077  // causes unconditional blocks to act conditionally, and therefore to
2078  // require their own elision scope.
2079  //
2080  // lbl: {
2081  // if (cond) break lbl;
2082  // x;
2083  // }
2084  // x; <-- Cannot elide TDZ check
2085  HoleCheckElisionScope elider(this);
2086  VisitStatements(stmt->statements());
2087  } else {
2088  VisitStatements(stmt->statements());
2089  }
2090 }
2091 
2092 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitVariableDeclaration(VariableDeclaration* decl) {
2093  Variable* variable = decl->var();
2094  // Unused variables don't need to be visited.
2095  if (!variable->is_used()) return;
2096 
2097  switch (variable->location()) {
2098  case VariableLocation::UNALLOCATED:
2099  case VariableLocation::MODULE:
2100  UNREACHABLE();
2101  case VariableLocation::LOCAL:
2102  if (variable->binding_needs_init()) {
2103  Register destination(builder()->Local(variable->index()));
2104  builder()->LoadTheHole().StoreAccumulatorInRegister(destination);
2105  }
2106  break;
2107  case VariableLocation::PARAMETER:
2108  if (variable->binding_needs_init()) {
2109  Register destination(builder()->Parameter(variable->index()));
2110  builder()->LoadTheHole().StoreAccumulatorInRegister(destination);
2111  }
2112  break;
2113  case VariableLocation::REPL_GLOBAL:
2114  // REPL let's are stored in script contexts. They get initialized
2115  // with the hole the same way as normal context allocated variables.
2116  case VariableLocation::CONTEXT:
2117  if (variable->binding_needs_init()) {
2118  DCHECK_EQ(0, execution_context()->ContextChainDepth(variable->scope()));
2119  builder()->LoadTheHole().StoreContextSlot(execution_context()->reg(),
2120  variable, 0);
2121  }
2122  break;
2123  case VariableLocation::LOOKUP: {
2124  DCHECK_EQ(VariableMode::kDynamic, variable->mode());
2125  DCHECK(!variable->binding_needs_init());
2126 
2127  Register name = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
2128 
2129  builder()
2130  ->LoadLiteral(variable->raw_name())
2131  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(name)
2132  .CallRuntime(Runtime::kDeclareEvalVar, name);
2133  break;
2134  }
2135  }
2136 }
2137 
2138 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitFunctionDeclaration(FunctionDeclaration* decl) {
2139  Variable* variable = decl->var();
2140  DCHECK(variable->mode() == VariableMode::kLet ||
2141  variable->mode() == VariableMode::kVar ||
2142  variable->mode() == VariableMode::kDynamic);
2143  // Unused variables don't need to be visited.
2144  if (!variable->is_used()) return;
2145 
2146  switch (variable->location()) {
2147  case VariableLocation::UNALLOCATED:
2148  case VariableLocation::MODULE:
2149  UNREACHABLE();
2150  case VariableLocation::PARAMETER:
2151  case VariableLocation::LOCAL: {
2152  VisitFunctionLiteral(decl->fun());
2153  BuildVariableAssignment(variable, Token::kInit, HoleCheckMode::kElided);
2154  break;
2155  }
2156  case VariableLocation::REPL_GLOBAL:
2157  case VariableLocation::CONTEXT: {
2158  DCHECK_EQ(0, execution_context()->ContextChainDepth(variable->scope()));
2159  VisitFunctionLiteral(decl->fun());
2160  builder()->StoreContextSlot(execution_context()->reg(), variable, 0);
2161  break;
2162  }
2163  case VariableLocation::LOOKUP: {
2164  RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
2165  builder()
2166  ->LoadLiteral(variable->raw_name())
2167  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[0]);
2168  VisitFunctionLiteral(decl->fun());
2169  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[1]).CallRuntime(
2170  Runtime::kDeclareEvalFunction, args);
2171  break;
2172  }
2173  }
2174  DCHECK_IMPLIES(
2175  eager_inner_literals_ != nullptr && decl->fun()->ShouldEagerCompile(),
2176  IsInEagerLiterals(decl->fun(), *eager_inner_literals_));
2177 }
2178 
2179 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitModuleNamespaceImports() {
2180  if (!closure_scope()->is_module_scope()) return;
2181 
2182  RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
2183  Register module_request = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
2184 
2185  SourceTextModuleDescriptor* descriptor =
2186  closure_scope()->AsModuleScope()->module();
2187  for (auto entry : descriptor->namespace_imports()) {
2188  builder()
2189  ->LoadLiteral(Smi::FromInt(entry->module_request))
2190  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(module_request)
2191  .CallRuntime(Runtime::kGetModuleNamespace, module_request);
2192  Variable* var = closure_scope()->LookupInModule(entry->local_name);
2193  BuildVariableAssignment(var, Token::kInit, HoleCheckMode::kElided);
2194  }
2195 }
2196 
2197 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildDeclareCall(Runtime::FunctionId id) {
2198  if (!top_level_builder()->has_top_level_declaration()) return;
2199  DCHECK(!top_level_builder()->processed());
2200 
2201  top_level_builder()->set_constant_pool_entry(
2202  builder()->AllocateDeferredConstantPoolEntry());
2203 
2204  // Emit code to declare globals.
2205  RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
2206  builder()
2207  ->LoadConstantPoolEntry(top_level_builder()->constant_pool_entry())
2208  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[0])
2209  .MoveRegister(Register::function_closure(), args[1])
2210  .CallRuntime(id, args);
2211 
2212  top_level_builder()->mark_processed();
2213 }
2214 
2215 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitModuleDeclarations(Declaration::List* decls) {
2216  RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
2217  for (Declaration* decl : *decls) {
2218  Variable* var = decl->var();
2219  if (!var->is_used()) continue;
2220  if (var->location() == VariableLocation::MODULE) {
2221  if (decl->IsFunctionDeclaration()) {
2222  DCHECK(var->IsExport());
2223  FunctionDeclaration* f = static_cast<FunctionDeclaration*>(decl);
2224  AddToEagerLiteralsIfEager(f->fun());
2225  top_level_builder()->record_module_function_declaration();
2226  } else if (var->IsExport() && var->binding_needs_init()) {
2227  DCHECK(decl->IsVariableDeclaration());
2228  top_level_builder()->record_module_variable_declaration();
2229  }
2230  } else {
2231  RegisterAllocationScope inner_register_scope(this);
2232  Visit(decl);
2233  }
2234  }
2235  BuildDeclareCall(Runtime::kDeclareModuleExports);
2236 }
2237 
2238 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitGlobalDeclarations(Declaration::List* decls) {
2239  RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
2240  for (Declaration* decl : *decls) {
2241  Variable* var = decl->var();
2242  DCHECK(var->is_used());
2243  if (var->location() == VariableLocation::UNALLOCATED) {
2244  // var or function.
2245  if (decl->IsFunctionDeclaration()) {
2246  top_level_builder()->record_global_function_declaration();
2247  FunctionDeclaration* f = static_cast<FunctionDeclaration*>(decl);
2248  AddToEagerLiteralsIfEager(f->fun());
2249  } else {
2250  top_level_builder()->record_global_variable_declaration();
2251  }
2252  } else {
2253  // let or const. Handled in NewScriptContext.
2254  DCHECK(decl->IsVariableDeclaration());
2255  DCHECK(IsLexicalVariableMode(var->mode()));
2256  }
2257  }
2258 
2259  BuildDeclareCall(Runtime::kDeclareGlobals);
2260 }
2261 
2262 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitDeclarations(Declaration::List* declarations) {
2263  for (Declaration* decl : *declarations) {
2264  RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
2265  Visit(decl);
2266  }
2267 }

2269 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitStatements(
2270  const ZonePtrList<Statement>* statements, int start) {
2271  for (int i = start; i < statements->length(); i++) {
2272  // Allocate an outer register allocations scope for the statement.
2273  RegisterAllocationScope allocation_scope(this);
2274  Statement* stmt = statements->at(i);
2275  Visit(stmt);
2276  if (builder()->RemainderOfBlockIsDead()) break;
2277  }
2278 }

2282  VisitForEffect(stmt->expression());
2283 }

2287 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitIfStatement(IfStatement* stmt) {
2288  ConditionalControlFlowBuilder conditional_builder(
2289  builder(), block_coverage_builder_, stmt);
2290  builder()->SetStatementPosition(stmt);
2291 
2292  if (stmt->condition()->ToBooleanIsTrue()) {
2293  // Generate then block unconditionally as always true.
2294  conditional_builder.Then();
2295  Visit(stmt->then_statement());
2296  } else if (stmt->condition()->ToBooleanIsFalse()) {
2297  // Generate else block unconditionally if it exists.
2298  if (stmt->HasElseStatement()) {
2299  conditional_builder.Else();
2300  Visit(stmt->else_statement());
2301  }
2302  } else {
2303  // TODO(oth): If then statement is BreakStatement or
2304  // ContinueStatement we can reduce number of generated
2305  // jump/jump_ifs here. See BasicLoops test.
2306  VisitForTest(stmt->condition(), conditional_builder.then_labels(),
2307  conditional_builder.else_labels(), TestFallthrough::kThen);
2308 
2309  HoleCheckElisionMergeScope merge_elider(this);
2310  {
2311  HoleCheckElisionMergeScope::Branch branch(merge_elider);
2312  conditional_builder.Then();
2313  Visit(stmt->then_statement());
2314  }
2315 
2316  {
2317  HoleCheckElisionMergeScope::Branch branch(merge_elider);
2318  if (stmt->HasElseStatement()) {
2319  conditional_builder.JumpToEnd();
2320  conditional_builder.Else();
2321  Visit(stmt->else_statement());
2322  }
2323  }
2324 
2325  merge_elider.Merge();
2326  }
2327 }

2330  SloppyBlockFunctionStatement* stmt) {
2331  Visit(stmt->statement());
2332 }

2346 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitReturnStatement(ReturnStatement* stmt) {
2347  AllocateBlockCoverageSlotIfEnabled(stmt, SourceRangeKind::kContinuation);
2348  builder()->SetStatementPosition(stmt);
2349  VisitForAccumulatorValue(stmt->expression());
2350  int return_position = stmt->end_position();
2351  if (return_position == ReturnStatement::kFunctionLiteralReturnPosition) {
2352  return_position = info()->literal()->return_position();
2353  }
2354  if (stmt->is_async_return()) {
2355  execution_control()->AsyncReturnAccumulator(return_position);
2356  } else {
2357  execution_control()->ReturnAccumulator(return_position);
2358  }
2359 }
