2370 bool IsSmiLiteralSwitchCaseValue(Expression* expr) {
2371  if (expr->IsSmiLiteral() ||
2372  (expr->IsLiteral() && expr->AsLiteral()->IsNumber() &&
2373  expr->AsLiteral()->AsNumber() == 0.0)) {
2374  return true;
2375 #ifdef DEBUG
2376  } else if (expr->IsLiteral() && expr->AsLiteral()->IsNumber()) {
2377  DCHECK(!IsSmiDouble(expr->AsLiteral()->AsNumber()));
2378 #endif
2379  }
2380  return false;
2381 }
2382 
2383 // Precondition: we called IsSmiLiteral to check this.
2384 inline int ReduceToSmiSwitchCaseValue(Expression* expr) {
2385  if (V8_LIKELY(expr->IsSmiLiteral())) {
2386  return expr->AsLiteral()->AsSmiLiteral().value();
2387  } else {
2388  // Only the zero case is possible otherwise.
2389  DCHECK(expr->IsLiteral() && expr->AsLiteral()->IsNumber() &&
2390  expr->AsLiteral()->AsNumber() == -0.0);
2391  return 0;
2392  }
2393 }
2394 
2395 // Is the range of Smi's small enough relative to number of cases?
2396 inline bool IsSpreadAcceptable(int spread, int ncases) {
2397  return spread < v8_flags.switch_table_spread_threshold * ncases;
2398 }
2399 
2400 struct SwitchInfo {
2401  static const int kDefaultNotFound = -1;
2402 
2403  std::map<int, CaseClause*> covered_cases;
2404  int default_case;
2405 
2406  SwitchInfo() { default_case = kDefaultNotFound; }
2407 
2408  bool DefaultExists() { return default_case != kDefaultNotFound; }
2409  bool CaseExists(int j) {
2410  return covered_cases.find(j) != covered_cases.end();
2411  }
2412  bool CaseExists(Expression* expr) {
2413  return IsSmiLiteralSwitchCaseValue(expr)
2414  ? CaseExists(ReduceToSmiSwitchCaseValue(expr))
2415  : false;
2416  }
2417  CaseClause* GetClause(int j) { return covered_cases[j]; }
2418 
2419  bool IsDuplicate(CaseClause* clause) {
2420  return IsSmiLiteralSwitchCaseValue(clause->label()) &&
2421  CaseExists(clause->label()) &&
2422  clause != GetClause(ReduceToSmiSwitchCaseValue(clause->label()));
2423  }
2424  int MinCase() {
2425  return covered_cases.empty() ? INT_MAX : covered_cases.begin()->first;
2426  }
2427  int MaxCase() {
2428  return covered_cases.empty() ? INT_MIN : covered_cases.rbegin()->first;
2429  }
2430  void Print() {
2431  std::cout << "Covered_cases: " << '\n';
2432  for (auto iter = covered_cases.begin(); iter != covered_cases.end();
2433  ++iter) {
2434  std::cout << iter->first << "->" << iter->second << '\n';
2435  }
2436  std::cout << "Default_case: " << default_case << '\n';
2437  }
2438 };
2439 
2440 // Checks whether we should use a jump table to implement a switch operation.
2441 bool IsSwitchOptimizable(SwitchStatement* stmt, SwitchInfo* info) {
2442  ZonePtrList<CaseClause>* cases = stmt->cases();
2443 
2444  for (int i = 0; i < cases->length(); ++i) {
2445  CaseClause* clause = cases->at(i);
2446  if (clause->is_default()) {
2447  continue;
2448  } else if (!(clause->label()->IsLiteral())) {
2449  // Don't consider Smi cases after a non-literal, because we
2450  // need to evaluate the non-literal.
2451  break;
2452  } else if (IsSmiLiteralSwitchCaseValue(clause->label())) {
2453  int value = ReduceToSmiSwitchCaseValue(clause->label());
2454  info->covered_cases.insert({value, clause});
2455  }
2456  }
2457 
2458  // GCC also jump-table optimizes switch statements with 6 cases or more.
2459  if (static_cast<int>(info->covered_cases.size()) >=
2460  v8_flags.switch_table_min_cases) {
2461  // Due to case spread will be used as the size of jump-table,
2462  // we need to check if it doesn't overflow by casting its
2463  // min and max bounds to int64_t, and calculate if the difference is less
2464  // than or equal to INT_MAX.
2465  int64_t min = static_cast<int64_t>(info->MinCase());
2466  int64_t max = static_cast<int64_t>(info->MaxCase());
2467  int64_t spread = max - min + 1;
2468 
2469  DCHECK_GT(spread, 0);
2470 
2471  // Check if casted spread is acceptable and doesn't overflow.
2472  if (spread <= INT_MAX &&
2473  IsSpreadAcceptable(static_cast<int>(spread), cases->length())) {
2474  return true;
2475  }
2476  }
2477  // Invariant- covered_cases has all cases and only cases that will go in the
2478  // jump table.
2479  info->covered_cases.clear();
2480  return false;
2481 }
2482 
2483 } // namespace
2484 
2485 // This adds a jump table optimization for switch statements with Smi cases.
2486 // If there are 5+ non-duplicate Smi clauses, and they are sufficiently compact,
2487 // we generate a jump table. In the fall-through path, we put the compare-jumps
2488 // for the non-Smi cases.
2489 
2490 // e.g.
2491 //
2492 // switch(x){
2493 // case -0: out = 10;
2494 // case 1: out = 11; break;
2495 // case 0: out = 12; break;
2496 // case 2: out = 13;
2497 // case 3: out = 14; break;
2498 // case 0.5: out = 15; break;
2499 // case 4: out = 16;
2500 // case y: out = 17;
2501 // case 5: out = 18;
2502 // default: out = 19; break;
2503 // }
2504 
2505 // becomes this pseudo-bytecode:
2506 
2507 // lda x
2508 // star r1
2509 // test_type number
2510 // jump_if_false @fallthrough
2511 // ldar r1
2512 // test_greater_than_or_equal_to smi_min
2513 // jump_if_false @fallthrough
2514 // ldar r1
2515 // test_less_than_or_equal_to smi_max
2516 // jump_if_false @fallthrough
2517 // ldar r1
2518 // bitwise_or 0
2519 // star r2
2520 // test_strict_equal r1
2521 // jump_if_false @fallthrough
2522 // ldar r2
2523 // switch_on_smi {1: @case_1, 2: @case_2, 3: @case_3, 4: @case_4}
2524 // @fallthrough:
2525 // jump_if_strict_equal -0.0 @case_minus_0.0
2526 // jump_if_strict_equal 0.5 @case_0.5
2527 // jump_if_strict_equal y @case_y
2528 // jump_if_strict_equal 5 @case_5
2529 // jump @default
2530 // @case_minus_0.0:
2531 // <out = 10>
2532 // @case_1
2533 // <out = 11, break>
2534 // @case_0:
2535 // <out = 12, break>
2536 // @case_2:
2537 // <out = 13>
2538 // @case_3:
2539 // <out = 14, break>
2540 // @case_0.5:
2541 // <out = 15, break>
2542 // @case_4:
2543 // <out = 16>
2544 // @case_y:
2545 // <out = 17>
2546 // @case_5:
2547 // <out = 18>
2548 // @default:
2549 // <out = 19, break>
2550 
2551 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitSwitchStatement(SwitchStatement* stmt) {
2552  // We need this scope because we visit for register values. We have to
2553  // maintain an execution result scope where registers can be allocated.
2554  ZonePtrList<CaseClause>* clauses = stmt->cases();
2555 
2556  SwitchInfo info;
2557  BytecodeJumpTable* jump_table = nullptr;
2558  bool use_jump_table = IsSwitchOptimizable(stmt, &info);
2559 
2560  // N_comp_cases is number of cases we will generate comparison jumps for.
2561  // Note we ignore duplicate cases, since they are very unlikely.
2562 
2563  int n_comp_cases = clauses->length();
2564  if (use_jump_table) {
2565  n_comp_cases -= static_cast<int>(info.covered_cases.size());
2566  jump_table = builder()->AllocateJumpTable(
2567  info.MaxCase() - info.MinCase() + 1, info.MinCase());
2568  }
2569 
2570  // Are we still using any if-else bytecodes to evaluate the switch?
2571  bool use_jumps = n_comp_cases != 0;
2572 
2573  // Does the comparison for non-jump table jumps need an elision scope?
2574  bool jump_comparison_needs_hole_check_elision_scope = false;
2575 
2576  SwitchBuilder switch_builder(builder(), block_coverage_builder_, stmt,
2577  n_comp_cases, jump_table);
2578  ControlScopeForBreakable scope(this, stmt, &switch_builder);
2579  builder()->SetStatementPosition(stmt);
2580 
2581  VisitForAccumulatorValue(stmt->tag());
2582 
2583  if (use_jump_table) {
2584  // Release temps so that they can be reused in clauses.
2585  RegisterAllocationScope allocation_scope(this);
2586  // This also fills empty slots in jump table.
2587  Register r2 = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
2588 
2589  Register r1 = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
2590  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(r1);
2591 
2592  builder()->CompareTypeOf(TestTypeOfFlags::LiteralFlag::kNumber);
2593  switch_builder.JumpToFallThroughIfFalse();
2594  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(r1);
2595 
2596  // TODO(leszeks): Note these are duplicated range checks with the
2597  // SwitchOnSmi handler for the most part.
2598 
2599  builder()->LoadLiteral(Smi::kMinValue);
2600  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(r2);
2601  builder()->CompareOperation(
2602  Token::kGreaterThanEq, r1,
2603  feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddCompareICSlot()));
2604 
2605  switch_builder.JumpToFallThroughIfFalse();
2606  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(r1);
2607 
2608  builder()->LoadLiteral(Smi::kMaxValue);
2609  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(r2);
2610  builder()->CompareOperation(
2611  Token::kLessThanEq, r1,
2612  feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddCompareICSlot()));
2613 
2614  switch_builder.JumpToFallThroughIfFalse();
2615  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(r1);
2616 
2617  builder()->BinaryOperationSmiLiteral(
2618  Token::kBitOr, Smi::FromInt(0),
2619  feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddBinaryOpICSlot()));
2620 
2621  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(r2);
2622  builder()->CompareOperation(
2623  Token::kEqStrict, r1,
2624  feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddCompareICSlot()));
2625 
2626  switch_builder.JumpToFallThroughIfFalse();
2627  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(r2);
2628 
2629  switch_builder.EmitJumpTableIfExists(info.MinCase(), info.MaxCase(),
2630  info.covered_cases);
2631 
2632  if (use_jumps) {
2633  // When using a jump table, the first jump comparison is conditionally
2634  // executed if the discriminant wasn't matched by anything in the jump
2635  // table, and so needs its own elision scope.
2636  jump_comparison_needs_hole_check_elision_scope = true;
2637  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(r1);
2638  }
2639  }
2640 
2641  int case_compare_ctr = 0;
2642 #ifdef DEBUG
2643  std::unordered_map<int, int> case_ctr_checker;
2644 #endif
2645 
2646  if (use_jumps) {
2647  Register tag_holder = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
2648  FeedbackSlot slot = clauses->length() > 0
2649  ? feedback_spec()->AddCompareICSlot()
2650  : FeedbackSlot::Invalid();
2651  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(tag_holder);
2652 
2653  {
2654  // The comparisons linearly dominate, so no need to open a new elision
2655  // scope for each one.
2656  std::optional<HoleCheckElisionScope> elider;
2657  for (int i = 0; i < clauses->length(); ++i) {
2658  CaseClause* clause = clauses->at(i);
2659  if (clause->is_default()) {
2660  info.default_case = i;
2661  } else if (!info.CaseExists(clause->label())) {
2662  if (jump_comparison_needs_hole_check_elision_scope && !elider) {
2663  elider.emplace(this);
2664  }
2665 
2666  // Perform label comparison as if via '===' with tag.
2667  VisitForAccumulatorValue(clause->label());
2668  builder()->CompareOperation(Token::kEqStrict, tag_holder,
2669  feedback_index(slot));
2670 #ifdef DEBUG
2671  case_ctr_checker[i] = case_compare_ctr;
2672 #endif
2673  switch_builder.JumpToCaseIfTrue(ToBooleanMode::kAlreadyBoolean,
2674  case_compare_ctr++);
2675  // The second and subsequent non-default comparisons are always
2676  // conditionally executed, and need an elision scope.
2677  jump_comparison_needs_hole_check_elision_scope = true;
2678  }
2679  }
2680  }
2681  register_allocator()->ReleaseRegister(tag_holder);
2682  }
2683 
2684  // For fall-throughs after comparisons (or out-of-range/non-Smi's for jump
2685  // tables).
2686  if (info.DefaultExists()) {
2687  switch_builder.JumpToDefault();
2688  } else {
2689  switch_builder.Break();
2690  }
2691 
2692  // It is only correct to merge hole check states if there is a default clause,
2693  // as otherwise it's unknown if the switch is exhaustive.
2694  HoleCheckElisionMergeScope merge_elider(this);
2695 
2696  case_compare_ctr = 0;
2697  for (int i = 0; i < clauses->length(); ++i) {
2698  CaseClause* clause = clauses->at(i);
2699  if (i != info.default_case) {
2700  if (!info.IsDuplicate(clause)) {
2701  bool use_table = use_jump_table && info.CaseExists(clause->label());
2702  if (!use_table) {
2703 // Guarantee that we should generate compare/jump if no table.
2704 #ifdef DEBUG
2705  DCHECK(case_ctr_checker[i] == case_compare_ctr);
2706 #endif
2707  switch_builder.BindCaseTargetForCompareJump(case_compare_ctr++,
2708  clause);
2709  } else {
2710  // Use jump table if this is not a duplicate label.
2711  switch_builder.BindCaseTargetForJumpTable(
2712  ReduceToSmiSwitchCaseValue(clause->label()), clause);
2713  }
2714  }
2715  } else {
2716  switch_builder.BindDefault(clause);
2717  }
2718  // Regardless, generate code (in case of fall throughs).
2719  HoleCheckElisionMergeScope::Branch branch_elider(merge_elider);
2720  VisitStatements(clause->statements());
2721  }
2722 
2723  merge_elider.MergeIf(info.DefaultExists());
2724 }
2725 
2726 template <typename TryBodyFunc, typename CatchBodyFunc>
2727 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildTryCatch(
2728  TryBodyFunc try_body_func, CatchBodyFunc catch_body_func,
2729  HandlerTable::CatchPrediction catch_prediction,
2730  TryCatchStatement* stmt_for_coverage) {
2731  if (builder()->RemainderOfBlockIsDead()) return;
2732 
2733  TryCatchBuilder try_control_builder(
2734  builder(),
2735  stmt_for_coverage == nullptr ? nullptr : block_coverage_builder_,
2736  stmt_for_coverage, catch_prediction);
2737 
2738  // Preserve the context in a dedicated register, so that it can be restored
2739  // when the handler is entered by the stack-unwinding machinery.
2740  // TODO(ignition): Be smarter about register allocation.
2741  Register context = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
2742  builder()->MoveRegister(Register::current_context(), context);
2743 
2744  // Evaluate the try-block inside a control scope. This simulates a handler
2745  // that is intercepting 'throw' control commands.
2746  try_control_builder.BeginTry(context);
2747 
2748  HoleCheckElisionMergeScope merge_elider(this);
2749 
2750  {
2751  ControlScopeForTryCatch scope(this, &try_control_builder);
2752  // The try-block itself, even though unconditionally executed, can throw
2753  // basically at any point, and so must be treated as conditional from the
2754  // perspective of the hole check elision analysis.
2755  //
2756  // try { x } catch (e) { }
2757  // use(x); <-- Still requires a TDZ check
2758  //
2759  // However, if both the try-block and the catch-block emit a hole check,
2760  // subsequent TDZ checks can be elided.
2761  //
2762  // try { x; } catch (e) { x; }
2763  // use(x); <-- TDZ check can be elided
2764  HoleCheckElisionMergeScope::Branch branch_elider(merge_elider);
2765  try_body_func();
2766  }
2767  try_control_builder.EndTry();
2768 
2769  {
2770  HoleCheckElisionMergeScope::Branch branch_elider(merge_elider);
2771  catch_body_func(context);
2772  }
2773 
2774  merge_elider.Merge();
2775 
2776  try_control_builder.EndCatch();
2777 }
2778 
2779 template <typename TryBodyFunc, typename FinallyBodyFunc>
2780 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildTryFinally(
2781  TryBodyFunc try_body_func, FinallyBodyFunc finally_body_func,
2782  HandlerTable::CatchPrediction catch_prediction,
2783  TryFinallyStatement* stmt_for_coverage) {
2784  if (builder()->RemainderOfBlockIsDead()) return;
2785 
2786  // We can't know whether the finally block will override ("catch") an
2787  // exception thrown in the try block, so we just adopt the outer prediction.
2788  TryFinallyBuilder try_control_builder(
2789  builder(),
2790  stmt_for_coverage == nullptr ? nullptr : block_coverage_builder_,
2791  stmt_for_coverage, catch_prediction);
2792 
2793  // We keep a record of all paths that enter the finally-block to be able to
2794  // dispatch to the correct continuation point after the statements in the
2795  // finally-block have been evaluated.
2796  //
2797  // The try-finally construct can enter the finally-block in three ways:
2798  // 1. By exiting the try-block normally, falling through at the end.
2799  // 2. By exiting the try-block with a function-local control flow transfer
2800  // (i.e. through break/continue/return statements).
2801  // 3. By exiting the try-block with a thrown exception.
2802  //
2803  // The result register semantics depend on how the block was entered:
2804  // - ReturnStatement: It represents the return value being returned.
2805  // - ThrowStatement: It represents the exception being thrown.
2806  // - BreakStatement/ContinueStatement: Undefined and not used.
2807  // - Falling through into finally-block: Undefined and not used.
2808  Register token = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
2809  Register result = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
2810  Register message = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
2811  builder()->LoadTheHole().StoreAccumulatorInRegister(message);
2812  ControlScope::DeferredCommands commands(this, token, result, message);
2813 
2814  // Preserve the context in a dedicated register, so that it can be restored
2815  // when the handler is entered by the stack-unwinding machinery.
2816  // TODO(ignition): Be smarter about register allocation.
2817  Register context = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
2818  builder()->MoveRegister(Register::current_context(), context);
2819 
2820  // Evaluate the try-block inside a control scope. This simulates a handler
2821  // that is intercepting all control commands.
2822  try_control_builder.BeginTry(context);
2823  {
2824  ControlScopeForTryFinally scope(this, &try_control_builder, &commands);
2825  // The try-block itself, even though unconditionally executed, can throw
2826  // basically at any point, and so must be treated as conditional from the
2827  // perspective of the hole check elision analysis.
2828  HoleCheckElisionScope elider(this);
2829  try_body_func();
2830  }
2831  try_control_builder.EndTry();
2832 
2833  // Record fall-through and exception cases.
2834  if (!builder()->RemainderOfBlockIsDead()) {
2835  commands.RecordFallThroughPath();
2836  }
2837  try_control_builder.LeaveTry();
2838  try_control_builder.BeginHandler();
2839  commands.RecordHandlerReThrowPath();
2840 
2841  try_control_builder.BeginFinally();
2842 
2843  // Evaluate the finally-block.
2844  finally_body_func(token, result, message);
2845  try_control_builder.EndFinally();
2846 
2847  // Dynamic dispatch after the finally-block.
2848  commands.ApplyDeferredCommands();
2849 }
2850 
2851 template <typename WrappedFunc>
2852 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildDisposeScope(WrappedFunc wrapped_func,
2853  bool has_await_using) {
2854  RegisterAllocationScope allocation_scope(this);
2855  DisposablesStackScope disposables_stack_scope(this);
2856  if (has_await_using) {
2857  set_catch_prediction(info()->scope()->is_repl_mode_scope()
2858  ? HandlerTable::UNCAUGHT_ASYNC_AWAIT
2859  : HandlerTable::ASYNC_AWAIT);
2860  }
2861 
2862  BuildTryFinally(
2863  // Try block
2864  [&]() { wrapped_func(); },
2865  // Finally block
2866  [&](Register body_continuation_token, Register body_continuation_result,
2867  Register message) {
2868  if (has_await_using) {
2869  Register result_register = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
2870  Register disposable_stack_register =
2871  register_allocator()->NewRegister();
2872  builder()->MoveRegister(current_disposables_stack(),
2873  disposable_stack_register);
2874  LoopBuilder loop_builder(builder(), nullptr, nullptr,
2875  feedback_spec());
2876  LoopScope loop_scope(this, &loop_builder);
2877 
2878  {
2879  RegisterAllocationScope allocation_scope(this);
2880  RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(5);
2881  builder()
2882  ->MoveRegister(disposable_stack_register, args[0])
2883  .MoveRegister(body_continuation_token, args[1])
2884  .MoveRegister(body_continuation_result, args[2])
2885  .MoveRegister(message, args[3])
2886  .LoadLiteral(Smi::FromEnum(
2887  DisposableStackResourcesType::kAtLeastOneAsync))
2888  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[4]);
2889  builder()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kDisposeDisposableStack, args);
2890  }
2891 
2892  builder()
2893  ->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(result_register)
2894  .LoadTrue()
2895  .CompareReference(result_register);
2896 
2897  loop_builder.BreakIfTrue(ToBooleanMode::kConvertToBoolean);
2898 
2899  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(result_register);
2900  BuildTryCatch(
2901  [&]() { BuildAwait(); },
2902  [&](Register context) {
2903  RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(3);
2904  builder()
2905  ->MoveRegister(current_disposables_stack(), args[0])
2906  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[1]) // exception
2907  .LoadTheHole()
2908  .SetPendingMessage()
2909  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[2])
2910  .CallRuntime(
2911  Runtime::kHandleExceptionsInDisposeDisposableStack,
2912  args);
2913 
2914  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(
2915  disposable_stack_register);
2916  },
2917  catch_prediction());
2918 
2919  loop_builder.BindContinueTarget();
2920  } else {
2921  RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(5);
2922  builder()
2923  ->MoveRegister(current_disposables_stack(), args[0])
2924  .MoveRegister(body_continuation_token, args[1])
2925  .MoveRegister(body_continuation_result, args[2])
2926  .MoveRegister(message, args[3])
2927  .LoadLiteral(
2928  Smi::FromEnum(DisposableStackResourcesType::kAllSync))
2929  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[4]);
2930  builder()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kDisposeDisposableStack, args);
2931  }
2932  },
2933  catch_prediction());
2934 }

2937  LoopBuilder* loop_builder) {
2938  loop_builder->LoopBody();
2939  ControlScopeForIteration execution_control(this, stmt, loop_builder);
2940  Visit(stmt->body());
2941  loop_builder->BindContinueTarget();
2942 }

2944 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitIterationBodyInHoleCheckElisionScope(
2945  IterationStatement* stmt, LoopBuilder* loop_builder) {

2949 
2950 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitDoWhileStatement(DoWhileStatement* stmt) {
2951  LoopBuilder loop_builder(builder(), block_coverage_builder_, stmt,
2952  feedback_spec());
2953  if (stmt->cond()->ToBooleanIsFalse()) {
2954  // Since we know that the condition is false, we don't create a loop.
2955  // Therefore, we don't create a LoopScope (and thus we don't create a header
2956  // and a JumpToHeader). However, we still need to iterate once through the
2957  // body.
2958  VisitIterationBodyInHoleCheckElisionScope(stmt, &loop_builder);
2959  } else if (stmt->cond()->ToBooleanIsTrue()) {
2960  LoopScope loop_scope(this, &loop_builder);
2961  VisitIterationBodyInHoleCheckElisionScope(stmt, &loop_builder);
2962  } else {
2963  LoopScope loop_scope(this, &loop_builder);
2964  VisitIterationBodyInHoleCheckElisionScope(stmt, &loop_builder);
2965  builder()->SetExpressionAsStatementPosition(stmt->cond());
2966  BytecodeLabels loop_backbranch(zone());
2967  if (!loop_builder.break_labels()->empty()) {
2968  // The test may be conditionally executed if there was a break statement
2969  // inside the loop body, and therefore requires its own elision scope.
2970  HoleCheckElisionScope elider(this);
2971  VisitForTest(stmt->cond(), &loop_backbranch, loop_builder.break_labels(),
2972  TestFallthrough::kThen);
2973  } else {
2974  VisitForTest(stmt->cond(), &loop_backbranch, loop_builder.break_labels(),
2975  TestFallthrough::kThen);
2976  }
2977  loop_backbranch.Bind(builder());
2978  }
2979 }
2980 
2981 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitWhileStatement(WhileStatement* stmt) {
2982  LoopBuilder loop_builder(builder(), block_coverage_builder_, stmt,
2983  feedback_spec());
2984 
2985  if (stmt->cond()->ToBooleanIsFalse()) {
2986  // If the condition is false there is no need to generate the loop.
2987  return;
2988  }
2989 
2990  LoopScope loop_scope(this, &loop_builder);
2991  if (!stmt->cond()->ToBooleanIsTrue()) {
2992  builder()->SetExpressionAsStatementPosition(stmt->cond());
2993  BytecodeLabels loop_body(zone());
2994  VisitForTest(stmt->cond(), &loop_body, loop_builder.break_labels(),
2995  TestFallthrough::kThen);
2996  loop_body.Bind(builder());
2997  }
2998  VisitIterationBodyInHoleCheckElisionScope(stmt, &loop_builder);
2999 }
3000 
3001 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitForStatement(ForStatement* stmt) {
3002  if (stmt->init() != nullptr) {
3003  Visit(stmt->init());
3004  }
3005 
3006  LoopBuilder loop_builder(builder(), block_coverage_builder_, stmt,
3007  feedback_spec());
3008  if (stmt->cond() && stmt->cond()->ToBooleanIsFalse()) {
3009  // If the condition is known to be false there is no need to generate
3010  // body, next or condition blocks. Init block should be generated.
3011  return;
3012  }
3013 
3014  LoopScope loop_scope(this, &loop_builder);
3015  if (stmt->cond() && !stmt->cond()->ToBooleanIsTrue()) {
3016  builder()->SetExpressionAsStatementPosition(stmt->cond());
3017  BytecodeLabels loop_body(zone());
3018  VisitForTest(stmt->cond(), &loop_body, loop_builder.break_labels(),
3019  TestFallthrough::kThen);
3020  loop_body.Bind(builder());
3021  }
3022 
3023  // C-style for loops' textual order differs from dominator order.
3024  //
3025  // for (INIT; TEST; NEXT) BODY
3026  // REST
3027  //
3028  // has the dominator order of
3029  //
3030  // INIT dominates TEST dominates BODY dominates NEXT
3031  // and
3032  // INIT dominates TEST dominates REST
3033  //
3034  // INIT and TEST are always evaluated and so do not have their own
3035  // HoleCheckElisionScope. BODY, like all iteration bodies, can contain control
3036  // flow like breaks or continues, has its own HoleCheckElisionScope. NEXT is
3037  // therefore conditionally evaluated and also so has its own
3038  // HoleCheckElisionScope.
3039  HoleCheckElisionScope elider(this);
3040  VisitIterationBody(stmt, &loop_builder);
3041  if (stmt->next() != nullptr) {
3042  builder()->SetStatementPosition(stmt->next());
3043  Visit(stmt->next());
3044  }
3045 }
3046 
3047 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitForInStatement(ForInStatement* stmt) {
3048  if (stmt->subject()->IsNullLiteral() ||
3049  stmt->subject()->IsUndefinedLiteral()) {
3050  // ForIn generates lots of code, skip if it wouldn't produce any effects.
3051  return;
3052  }
3053 
3054  BytecodeLabel subject_undefined_label;
3055  FeedbackSlot slot = feedback_spec()->AddForInSlot();
3056 
3057  // Prepare the state for executing ForIn.
3058  builder()->SetExpressionAsStatementPosition(stmt->subject());
3059  {
3060  CurrentScope current_scope(this, stmt->subject_scope());
3061  VisitForAccumulatorValue(stmt->subject());
3062  }
3063  builder()->JumpIfUndefinedOrNull(&subject_undefined_label);
3064  Register receiver = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
3065  builder()->ToObject(receiver);
3066 
3067  // Used as kRegTriple and kRegPair in ForInPrepare and ForInNext.
3068  RegisterList triple = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(3);
3069  Register cache_length = triple[2];
3070  builder()->ForInEnumerate(receiver);
3071  builder()->ForInPrepare(triple, feedback_index(slot));
3072 
3073  // Set up loop counter
3074  Register index = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
3075  builder()->LoadLiteral(Smi::zero());
3076  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(index);
3077 
3078  // The loop
3079  {
3080  LoopBuilder loop_builder(builder(), block_coverage_builder_, stmt,
3081  feedback_spec());
3082  LoopScope loop_scope(this, &loop_builder);
3083  HoleCheckElisionScope elider(this);
3084  builder()->SetExpressionAsStatementPosition(stmt->each(),
3085  /*is_breakable= */ false);
3086  loop_builder.BreakIfForInDone(index, cache_length);
3087  builder()->ForInNext(receiver, index, triple.Truncate(2),
3088  feedback_index(slot));
3089  loop_builder.ContinueIfUndefined();
3090 
3091  // Assign accumulator value to the 'each' target.
3092  {
3093  EffectResultScope scope(this);
3094  // Make sure to preserve the accumulator across the PrepareAssignmentLhs
3095  // call.
3096  builder()->SetExpressionAsStatementPosition(stmt->each());
3097  AssignmentLhsData lhs_data = PrepareAssignmentLhs(
3098  stmt->each(), AccumulatorPreservingMode::kPreserve);
3099  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(stmt->each());
3100  BuildAssignment(lhs_data, Token::kAssign, LookupHoistingMode::kNormal);
3101  }
3102 
3103  {
3104  Register cache_type = triple[0];
3105  ForInScope scope(this, stmt, index, cache_type);
3106  VisitIterationBody(stmt, &loop_builder);
3107  builder()->ForInStep(index);
3108  }
3109  }
3110  builder()->Bind(&subject_undefined_label);
3111 }
3112 
3113 // Desugar a for-of statement into an application of the iteration protocol.
3114 //
3115 // for (EACH of SUBJECT) BODY
3116 //
3117 // becomes
3118 //
3119 // iterator = %GetIterator(SUBJECT)
3120 // try {
3121 //
3122 // loop {
3123 // // Make sure we are considered 'done' if .next(), .done or .value fail.
3124 // done = true
3125 // value = iterator.next()
3126 // if (value.done) break;
3127 // value = value.value
3128 // done = false
3129 //
3130 // EACH = value
3131 // BODY
3132 // }
3133 // done = true
3134 //
3135 // } catch(e) {
3136 // iteration_continuation = RETHROW
3137 // } finally {
3138 // %FinalizeIteration(iterator, done, iteration_continuation)
3139 // }
3140 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitForOfStatement(ForOfStatement* stmt) {
3141  EffectResultScope effect_scope(this);
3142 
3143  builder()->SetExpressionAsStatementPosition(stmt->subject());
3144  {
3145  CurrentScope current_scope(this, stmt->subject_scope());
3146  VisitForAccumulatorValue(stmt->subject());
3147  }
3148 
3149  // Store the iterator in a dedicated register so that it can be closed on
3150  // exit, and the 'done' value in a dedicated register so that it can be
3151  // changed and accessed independently of the iteration result.
3152  IteratorRecord iterator = BuildGetIteratorRecord(stmt->type());
3153  Register done = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
3154  builder()->LoadFalse();
3155  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(done);
3156 
3157  BuildTryFinally(
3158  // Try block.
3159  [&]() {
3160  LoopBuilder loop_builder(builder(), block_coverage_builder_, stmt,
3161  feedback_spec());
3162  LoopScope loop_scope(this, &loop_builder);
3163 
3164  // This doesn't need a HoleCheckElisionScope because BuildTryFinally
3165  // already makes one for try blocks.
3166 
3167  builder()->LoadTrue().StoreAccumulatorInRegister(done);
3168 
3169  {
3170  RegisterAllocationScope allocation_scope(this);
3171  Register next_result = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
3172 
3173  // Call the iterator's .next() method. Break from the loop if the
3174  // `done` property is truthy, otherwise load the value from the
3175  // iterator result and append the argument.
3176  builder()->SetExpressionAsStatementPosition(stmt->each(),
3177  /* is_breakable */ false);
3178  BuildIteratorNext(iterator, next_result);
3179  builder()->LoadNamedProperty(
3180  next_result, ast_string_constants()->done_string(),
3181  feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddLoadICSlot()));
3182  loop_builder.BreakIfTrue(ToBooleanMode::kConvertToBoolean);
3183 
3184  builder()
3185  // value = value.value
3186  ->LoadNamedProperty(
3187  next_result, ast_string_constants()->value_string(),
3188  feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddLoadICSlot()));
3189  // done = false, before the assignment to each happens, so that done
3190  // is false if the assignment throws.
3191  builder()
3192  ->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(next_result)
3193  .LoadFalse()
3194  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(done);
3195 
3196  // Assign to the 'each' target.
3197  builder()->SetExpressionAsStatementPosition(stmt->each());
3198  AssignmentLhsData lhs_data = PrepareAssignmentLhs(stmt->each());
3199  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(next_result);
3200  BuildAssignment(lhs_data, Token::kAssign,
3201  LookupHoistingMode::kNormal);
3202  }
3203 
3204  VisitIterationBody(stmt, &loop_builder);
3205  },
3206  // Finally block.
3207  [&](Register iteration_continuation_token,
3208  Register iteration_continuation_result, Register message) {
3209  // Finish the iteration in the finally block.
3210  BuildFinalizeIteration(iterator, done, iteration_continuation_token);
3211  },
3212  catch_prediction());
3213 }
3214 
3215 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitTryCatchStatement(TryCatchStatement* stmt) {
3216  // Update catch prediction tracking. The updated catch_prediction value lasts
3217  // until the end of the try_block in the AST node, and does not apply to the
3218  // catch_block.
3219  HandlerTable::CatchPrediction outer_catch_prediction = catch_prediction();
3220  set_catch_prediction(stmt->GetCatchPrediction(outer_catch_prediction));
3221 
3222  BuildTryCatch(
3223  // Try body.
3224  [&]() {
3225  Visit(stmt->try_block());
3226  set_catch_prediction(outer_catch_prediction);
3227  },
3228  // Catch body.
3229  [&](Register context) {
3230  if (stmt->scope()) {
3231  // Create a catch scope that binds the exception.
3232  BuildNewLocalCatchContext(stmt->scope());
3233  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(context);
3234  }
3235 
3236  // If requested, clear message object as we enter the catch block.
3237  if (stmt->ShouldClearException(outer_catch_prediction)) {
3238  builder()->LoadTheHole().SetPendingMessage();
3239  }
3240 
3241  // Load the catch context into the accumulator.
3242  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(context);
3243 
3244  // Evaluate the catch-block.
3245  if (stmt->scope()) {
3246  VisitInScope(stmt->catch_block(), stmt->scope());
3247  } else {
3248  VisitBlock(stmt->catch_block());
3249  }
3250  },
3251  catch_prediction(), stmt);
3252 }
3253 
3254 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitTryFinallyStatement(TryFinallyStatement* stmt) {
3255  BuildTryFinally(
3256  // Try block.
3257  [&]() { Visit(stmt->try_block()); },
3258  // Finally block.
3259  [&](Register body_continuation_token, Register body_continuation_result,
3260  Register message) { Visit(stmt->finally_block()); },
3261  catch_prediction(), stmt);
3262 }
3263 
3264 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitDebuggerStatement(DebuggerStatement* stmt) {
3265  builder()->SetStatementPosition(stmt);
3266  builder()->Debugger();
3267 }
3268 
3269 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitFunctionLiteral(FunctionLiteral* expr) {
3270  CHECK_LT(info_->literal()->function_literal_id(),
3271  expr->function_literal_id());
3272  DCHECK_EQ(expr->scope()->outer_scope(), current_scope());
3273  uint8_t flags = CreateClosureFlags::Encode(
3274  expr->pretenure(), closure_scope()->is_function_scope(),
3275  info()->flags().might_always_turbofan());
3276  size_t entry = builder()->AllocateDeferredConstantPoolEntry();
3277  builder()->CreateClosure(entry, GetCachedCreateClosureSlot(expr), flags);
3278  function_literals_.push_back(std::make_pair(expr, entry));
3279  AddToEagerLiteralsIfEager(expr);
3280 }
3281 
3282 void BytecodeGenerator::AddToEagerLiteralsIfEager(FunctionLiteral* literal) {
3283  // Only parallel compile when there's a script (not the case for source
3284  // position collection).
3285  if (!script_.is_null() && literal->should_parallel_compile()) {
3286  // If we should normally be eagerly compiling this function, we must be here
3287  // because of post_parallel_compile_tasks_for_eager_toplevel.
3288  DCHECK_IMPLIES(
3289  literal->ShouldEagerCompile(),
3290  info()->flags().post_parallel_compile_tasks_for_eager_toplevel());
3291  // There exists a lazy compile dispatcher.
3292  DCHECK(info()->dispatcher());
3293  // There exists a cloneable character stream.
3294  DCHECK(info()->character_stream()->can_be_cloned_for_parallel_access());
3295 
3296  UnparkedScopeIfOnBackground scope(local_isolate_);
3297  // If there doesn't already exist a SharedFunctionInfo for this function,
3298  // then create one and enqueue it. Otherwise, we're reparsing (e.g. for the
3299  // debugger, source position collection, call printing, recompile after
3300  // flushing, etc.) and don't want to over-compile.
3301  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info =
3302  Compiler::GetSharedFunctionInfo(literal, script_, local_isolate_);
3303  if (!shared_info->is_compiled()) {
3304  info()->dispatcher()->Enqueue(
3305  local_isolate_, indirect_handle(shared_info, local_isolate_),
3306  info()->character_stream()->Clone());
3307  }
3308  } else if (eager_inner_literals_ && literal->ShouldEagerCompile()) {
3309  DCHECK(!IsInEagerLiterals(literal, *eager_inner_literals_));
3310  DCHECK(!literal->should_parallel_compile());
3311  eager_inner_literals_->push_back(literal);
3312  }
3313 }
3314 
3315 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildClassLiteral(ClassLiteral* expr, Register name) {
3316  size_t class_boilerplate_entry =
3317  builder()->AllocateDeferredConstantPoolEntry();
3318  class_literals_.push_back(std::make_pair(expr, class_boilerplate_entry));
3319 
3320  VisitDeclarations(expr->scope()->declarations());
3321  Register class_constructor = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
3322 
3323  // Create the class brand symbol and store it on the context during class
3324  // evaluation. This will be stored in the instance later in the constructor.
3325  // We do this early so that invalid access to private methods or accessors
3326  // in computed property keys throw.
3327  if (expr->scope()->brand() != nullptr) {
3328  Register brand = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
3329  const AstRawString* class_name =
3330  expr->scope()->class_variable() != nullptr
3331  ? expr->scope()->class_variable()->raw_name()
3332  : ast_string_constants()->anonymous_string();
3333  builder()
3334  ->LoadLiteral(class_name)
3335  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(brand)
3336  .CallRuntime(Runtime::kCreatePrivateBrandSymbol, brand);
3337  register_allocator()->ReleaseRegister(brand);
3338 
3339  BuildVariableAssignment(expr->scope()->brand(), Token::kInit,
3340  HoleCheckMode::kElided);
3341  }
3342 
3343  AccessorTable<ClassLiteral::Property> private_accessors(zone());
3344  for (int i = 0; i < expr->private_members()->length(); i++) {
3345  ClassLiteral::Property* property = expr->private_members()->at(i);
3346  DCHECK(property->is_private());
3347  switch (property->kind()) {
3348  case ClassLiteral::Property::FIELD: {
3349  // Initialize the private field variables early.
3350  // Create the private name symbols for fields during class
3351  // evaluation and store them on the context. These will be
3352  // used as keys later during instance or static initialization.
3353  RegisterAllocationScope private_name_register_scope(this);
3354  Register private_name = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
3355  VisitForRegisterValue(property->key(), private_name);
3356  builder()
3357  ->LoadLiteral(property->key()->AsLiteral()->AsRawPropertyName())
3358  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(private_name)
3359  .CallRuntime(Runtime::kCreatePrivateNameSymbol, private_name);
3360  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(property->private_name_var());
3361  BuildVariableAssignment(property->private_name_var(), Token::kInit,
3362  HoleCheckMode::kElided);
3363  break;
3364  }
3365  case ClassLiteral::Property::METHOD: {
3366  RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
3367  VisitForAccumulatorValue(property->value());
3368  BuildVariableAssignment(property->private_name_var(), Token::kInit,
3369  HoleCheckMode::kElided);
3370  break;
3371  }
3372  // Collect private accessors into a table to merge the creation of
3373  // those closures later.
3374  case ClassLiteral::Property::GETTER: {
3375  Literal* key = property->key()->AsLiteral();
3376  DCHECK_NULL(private_accessors.LookupOrInsert(key)->getter);
3377  private_accessors.LookupOrInsert(key)->getter = property;
3378  break;
3379  }
3380  case ClassLiteral::Property::SETTER: {
3381  Literal* key = property->key()->AsLiteral();
3382  DCHECK_NULL(private_accessors.LookupOrInsert(key)->setter);
3383  private_accessors.LookupOrInsert(key)->setter = property;
3384  break;
3385  }
3386  case ClassLiteral::Property::AUTO_ACCESSOR: {
3387  Literal* key = property->key()->AsLiteral();
3388  RegisterAllocationScope private_name_register_scope(this);
3389  Register accessor_storage_private_name =
3390  register_allocator()->NewRegister();
3391  Variable* accessor_storage_private_name_var =
3392  property->auto_accessor_info()
3393  ->accessor_storage_name_proxy()
3394  ->var();
3395  // We reuse the already internalized
3396  // ".accessor-storage-<accessor_number>" strings that were defined in
3397  // the parser instead of the "<name>accessor storage" string from the
3398  // spec. The downsides are that is that these are the property names
3399  // that will show up in devtools and in error messages.
3400  // Additionally, a property can share a name with the corresponding
3401  // property of their parent class, i.e. for classes defined as
3402  // "class C {accessor x}" and "class D extends C {accessor y}",
3403  // if "d = new D()", then d.x and d.y will share the name
3404  // ".accessor-storage-0", (but a different private symbol).
3405  // TODO(42202709): Get to a resolution on how to handle this naming
3406  // issue before shipping the feature.
3407  builder()
3408  ->LoadLiteral(accessor_storage_private_name_var->raw_name())
3409  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(accessor_storage_private_name)
3410  .CallRuntime(Runtime::kCreatePrivateNameSymbol,
3411  accessor_storage_private_name);
3412  BuildVariableAssignment(accessor_storage_private_name_var, Token::kInit,
3413  HoleCheckMode::kElided);
3414  auto* accessor_pair = private_accessors.LookupOrInsert(key);
3415  DCHECK_NULL(accessor_pair->getter);
3416  accessor_pair->getter = property;
3417  DCHECK_NULL(accessor_pair->setter);
3418  accessor_pair->setter = property;
3419  break;
3420  }
3421  default:
3422  UNREACHABLE();
3423  }
3424  }
3425 
3426  {
3427  RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
3428  RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewGrowableRegisterList();
3429 
3430  Register class_boilerplate = register_allocator()->GrowRegisterList(&args);
3431  Register class_constructor_in_args =
3432  register_allocator()->GrowRegisterList(&args);
3433  Register super_class = register_allocator()->GrowRegisterList(&args);
3434  DCHECK_EQ(ClassBoilerplate::kFirstDynamicArgumentIndex,
3435  args.register_count());
3436 
3437  VisitForAccumulatorValueOrTheHole(expr->extends());
3438  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(super_class);
3439 
3440  VisitFunctionLiteral(expr->constructor());
3441  builder()
3442  ->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(class_constructor)
3443  .MoveRegister(class_constructor, class_constructor_in_args)
3444  .LoadConstantPoolEntry(class_boilerplate_entry)
3445  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(class_boilerplate);
3446 
3447  // Create computed names and method values nodes to store into the literal.
3448  for (int i = 0; i < expr->public_members()->length(); i++) {
3449  ClassLiteral::Property* property = expr->public_members()->at(i);
3450  if (property->is_computed_name()) {
3451  Register key = register_allocator()->GrowRegisterList(&args);
3452 
3453  builder()->SetExpressionAsStatementPosition(property->key());
3454  BuildLoadPropertyKey(property, key);
3455  if (property->is_static()) {
3456  // The static prototype property is read only. We handle the non
3457  // computed property name case in the parser. Since this is the only
3458  // case where we need to check for an own read only property we
3459  // special case this so we do not need to do this for every property.
3460 
3461  FeedbackSlot slot = GetDummyCompareICSlot();
3462  BytecodeLabel done;
3463  builder()
3464  ->LoadLiteral(ast_string_constants()->prototype_string())
3465  .CompareOperation(Token::kEqStrict, key, feedback_index(slot))
3466  .JumpIfFalse(ToBooleanMode::kAlreadyBoolean, &done)
3467  .CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowStaticPrototypeError)
3468  .Bind(&done);
3469  }
3470 
3471  if (property->kind() == ClassLiteral::Property::FIELD) {
3472  DCHECK(!property->is_private());
3473  // Initialize field's name variable with the computed name.
3474  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(property->computed_name_var());
3475  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(key);
3476  BuildVariableAssignment(property->computed_name_var(), Token::kInit,
3477  HoleCheckMode::kElided);
3478  }
3479  }
3480 
3481  DCHECK(!property->is_private());
3482 
3483  if (property->kind() == ClassLiteral::Property::FIELD) {
3484  // We don't compute field's value here, but instead do it in the
3485  // initializer function.
3486  continue;
3487  }
3488 
3489  if (property->kind() == ClassLiteral::Property::AUTO_ACCESSOR) {
3490  {
3491  RegisterAllocationScope private_name_register_scope(this);
3492  Register name_register = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
3493  Variable* accessor_storage_private_name_var =
3494  property->auto_accessor_info()
3495  ->accessor_storage_name_proxy()
3496  ->var();
3497  builder()
3498  ->LoadLiteral(accessor_storage_private_name_var->raw_name())
3499  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(name_register)
3500  .CallRuntime(Runtime::kCreatePrivateNameSymbol, name_register);
3501  BuildVariableAssignment(accessor_storage_private_name_var,
3502  Token::kInit, HoleCheckMode::kElided);
3503  }
3504 
3505  Register getter = register_allocator()->GrowRegisterList(&args);
3506  Register setter = register_allocator()->GrowRegisterList(&args);
3507  AutoAccessorInfo* auto_accessor_info = property->auto_accessor_info();
3508  VisitForRegisterValue(auto_accessor_info->generated_getter(), getter);
3509  VisitForRegisterValue(auto_accessor_info->generated_setter(), setter);
3510  continue;
3511  }
3512 
3513  Register value = register_allocator()->GrowRegisterList(&args);
3514  VisitForRegisterValue(property->value(), value);
3515  }
3516 
3517  builder()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kDefineClass, args);
3518  }
3519 
3520  // Assign to the home object variable. Accumulator already contains the
3521  // prototype.
3522  Variable* home_object_variable = expr->home_object();
3523  if (home_object_variable != nullptr) {
3524  DCHECK(home_object_variable->is_used());
3525  DCHECK(home_object_variable->IsContextSlot());
3526  BuildVariableAssignment(home_object_variable, Token::kInit,
3527  HoleCheckMode::kElided);
3528  }
3529  Variable* static_home_object_variable = expr->static_home_object();
3530  if (static_home_object_variable != nullptr) {
3531  DCHECK(static_home_object_variable->is_used());
3532  DCHECK(static_home_object_variable->IsContextSlot());
3533  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(class_constructor);
3534  BuildVariableAssignment(static_home_object_variable, Token::kInit,
3535  HoleCheckMode::kElided);
3536  }
3537 
3538  // Assign to class variable.
3539  Variable* class_variable = expr->scope()->class_variable();
3540  if (class_variable != nullptr && class_variable->is_used()) {
3541  DCHECK(class_variable->IsStackLocal() || class_variable->IsContextSlot());
3542  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(class_constructor);
3543  BuildVariableAssignment(class_variable, Token::kInit,
3544  HoleCheckMode::kElided);
3545  }
3546 
3547  // Define private accessors, using only a single call to the runtime for
3548  // each pair of corresponding getters and setters, in the order the first
3549  // component is declared.
3550  for (auto accessors : private_accessors.ordered_accessors()) {
3551  RegisterAllocationScope inner_register_scope(this);
3552  RegisterList accessors_reg = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
3553  ClassLiteral::Property* getter = accessors.second->getter;
3554  ClassLiteral::Property* setter = accessors.second->setter;
3555  Variable* accessor_pair_var;
3556  if (getter && getter->kind() == ClassLiteral::Property::AUTO_ACCESSOR) {
3557  DCHECK_EQ(setter, getter);
3558  AutoAccessorInfo* auto_accessor_info = getter->auto_accessor_info();
3559  VisitForRegisterValue(auto_accessor_info->generated_getter(),
3560  accessors_reg[0]);
3561  VisitForRegisterValue(auto_accessor_info->generated_setter(),
3562  accessors_reg[1]);
3563  accessor_pair_var =
3564  auto_accessor_info->property_private_name_proxy()->var();
3565  } else {
3566  VisitLiteralAccessor(getter, accessors_reg[0]);
3567  VisitLiteralAccessor(setter, accessors_reg[1]);
3568  accessor_pair_var = getter != nullptr ? getter->private_name_var()
3569  : setter->private_name_var();
3570  }
3571  builder()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kCreatePrivateAccessors, accessors_reg);
3572  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(accessor_pair_var);
3573  BuildVariableAssignment(accessor_pair_var, Token::kInit,
3574  HoleCheckMode::kElided);
3575  }
3576 
3577  if (expr->instance_members_initializer_function() != nullptr) {
3578  VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->instance_members_initializer_function());
3579 
3580  FeedbackSlot slot = feedback_spec()->AddStoreICSlot(language_mode());
3581  builder()
3582  ->StoreClassFieldsInitializer(class_constructor, feedback_index(slot))
3583  .LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(class_constructor);
3584  }
3585 
3586  if (expr->static_initializer() != nullptr) {
3587  // TODO(gsathya): This can be optimized away to be a part of the
3588  // class boilerplate in the future. The name argument can be
3589  // passed to the DefineClass runtime function and have it set
3590  // there.
3591  // TODO(v8:13451): Alternatively, port SetFunctionName to an ic so that we
3592  // can replace the runtime call to a dedicate bytecode here.
3593  if (name.is_valid()) {
3594  RegisterAllocationScope inner_register_scope(this);
3595  RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
3596  builder()
3597  ->MoveRegister(class_constructor, args[0])
3598  .MoveRegister(name, args[1])
3599  .CallRuntime(Runtime::kSetFunctionName, args);
3600  }
3601 
3602  RegisterAllocationScope inner_register_scope(this);
3603  RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(1);
3604  Register initializer = VisitForRegisterValue(expr->static_initializer());
3605 
3606  builder()
3607  ->MoveRegister(class_constructor, args[0])
3608  .CallProperty(initializer, args,
3609  feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddCallICSlot()));
3610  }
3611  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(class_constructor);
3612 }
3613 
3614 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitClassLiteral(ClassLiteral* expr) {
3615  VisitClassLiteral(expr, Register::invalid_value());
3616 }
3617 
3618 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitClassLiteral(ClassLiteral* expr, Register name) {
3619  CurrentScope current_scope(this, expr->scope());
3620  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(expr->scope());
3621  if (expr->scope()->NeedsContext()) {
3622  // Make sure to associate the source position for the class
3623  // after the block context is created. Otherwise we have a mismatch
3624  // between the scope and the context, where we already are in a
3625  // block context for the class, but not yet in the class scope. Only do
3626  // this if the current source position is inside the class scope though.
3627  // For example:
3628  // * `var x = class {};` will break on `class` which is inside
3629  // the class scope, so we expect the BlockContext to be pushed.
3630  //
3631  // * `new class x {};` will break on `new` which is outside the
3632  // class scope, so we expect the BlockContext to not be pushed yet.
3633  std::optional<BytecodeSourceInfo> source_info =
3634  builder()->MaybePopSourcePosition(expr->scope()->start_position());
3635  BuildNewLocalBlockContext(expr->scope());
3636  ContextScope scope(this, expr->scope());
3637  if (source_info) builder()->PushSourcePosition(*source_info);
3638  BuildClassLiteral(expr, name);
3639  } else {
3640  BuildClassLiteral(expr, name);
3641  }
3642 }
3643 
3644 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildClassProperty(ClassLiteral::Property* property) {
3645  RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
3646  Register key;
3647 
3648  // Private methods are not initialized in BuildClassProperty.
3649  DCHECK_IMPLIES(property->is_private(),
3650  property->kind() == ClassLiteral::Property::FIELD ||
3651  property->is_auto_accessor());
3652  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(property->key());
3653 
3654  bool is_literal_store =
3655  property->key()->IsPropertyName() && !property->is_computed_name() &&
3656  !property->is_private() && !property->is_auto_accessor();
3657 
3658  if (!is_literal_store) {
3659  key = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
3660  if (property->is_auto_accessor()) {
3661  Variable* var =
3662  property->auto_accessor_info()->accessor_storage_name_proxy()->var();
3663  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(var);
3664  BuildVariableLoad(var, HoleCheckMode::kElided);
3665  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(key);
3666  } else if (property->is_computed_name()) {
3667  DCHECK_EQ(property->kind(), ClassLiteral::Property::FIELD);
3668  DCHECK(!property->is_private());
3669  Variable* var = property->computed_name_var();
3670  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(var);
3671  // The computed name is already evaluated and stored in a variable at
3672  // class definition time.
3673  BuildVariableLoad(var, HoleCheckMode::kElided);
3674  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(key);
3675  } else if (property->is_private()) {
3676  Variable* private_name_var = property->private_name_var();
3677  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(private_name_var);
3678  BuildVariableLoad(private_name_var, HoleCheckMode::kElided);
3679  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(key);
3680  } else {
3681  VisitForRegisterValue(property->key(), key);
3682  }
3683  }
3684 
3685  builder()->SetExpressionAsStatementPosition(property->value());
3686 
3687  if (is_literal_store) {
3688  VisitForAccumulatorValue(property->value());
3689  FeedbackSlot slot = feedback_spec()->AddDefineNamedOwnICSlot();
3690  builder()->DefineNamedOwnProperty(
3691  builder()->Receiver(),
3692  property->key()->AsLiteral()->AsRawPropertyName(),
3693  feedback_index(slot));
3694  } else {
3695  DefineKeyedOwnPropertyFlags flags = DefineKeyedOwnPropertyFlag::kNoFlags;
3696  if (property->NeedsSetFunctionName()) {
3697  // Static class fields require the name property to be set on
3698  // the class, meaning we can't wait until the
3699  // DefineKeyedOwnProperty call later to set the name.
3700  if (property->value()->IsClassLiteral() &&
3701  property->value()->AsClassLiteral()->static_initializer() !=
3702  nullptr) {
3703  VisitClassLiteral(property->value()->AsClassLiteral(), key);
3704  } else {
3705  VisitForAccumulatorValue(property->value());
3706  flags |= DefineKeyedOwnPropertyFlag::kSetFunctionName;
3707  }
3708  } else {
3709  VisitForAccumulatorValue(property->value());
3710  }
3711  FeedbackSlot slot = feedback_spec()->AddDefineKeyedOwnICSlot();
3712  builder()->DefineKeyedOwnProperty(builder()->Receiver(), key, flags,
3713  feedback_index(slot));
3714  }
3715 }
3716 
3717 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitInitializeClassMembersStatement(
3718  InitializeClassMembersStatement* stmt) {
3719  for (int i = 0; i < stmt->fields()->length(); i++) {
3720  BuildClassProperty(stmt->fields()->at(i));
3721  }
3722 }
3723 
3724 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitInitializeClassStaticElementsStatement(
3725  InitializeClassStaticElementsStatement* stmt) {
3726  for (int i = 0; i < stmt->elements()->length(); i++) {
3727  ClassLiteral::StaticElement* element = stmt->elements()->at(i);
3728  switch (element->kind()) {
3729  case ClassLiteral::StaticElement::PROPERTY:
3730  BuildClassProperty(element->property());
3731  break;
3732  case ClassLiteral::StaticElement::STATIC_BLOCK:
3733  VisitBlock(element->static_block());
3734  break;
3735  }
3736  }
3737 }

3762 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildInvalidPropertyAccess(MessageTemplate tmpl,
3763  Property* property) {

3767  builder()
3768  ->LoadLiteral(Smi::FromEnum(tmpl))
3769  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[0])

3776 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildPrivateBrandInitialization(Register receiver,
3777  Variable* brand) {
3778  BuildVariableLoad(brand, HoleCheckMode::kElided);
3779  int depth = execution_context()->ContextChainDepth(brand->scope());
3780  ContextScope* class_context = execution_context()->Previous(depth);
3781  if (class_context) {
3782  Register brand_reg = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
3783  FeedbackSlot slot = feedback_spec()->AddDefineKeyedOwnICSlot();
3784  builder()
3785  ->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(brand_reg)
3786  .LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(class_context->reg())
3787  .DefineKeyedOwnProperty(receiver, brand_reg,
3788  DefineKeyedOwnPropertyFlag::kNoFlags,
3789  feedback_index(slot));
3790  } else {
3791  // We are in the slow case where super() is called from a nested
3792  // arrow function or an eval(), so the class scope context isn't
3793  // tracked in a context register in the stack, and we have to
3794  // walk the context chain from the runtime to find it.
3795  DCHECK_NE(info()->literal()->scope()->outer_scope(), brand->scope());
3796  RegisterList brand_args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(4);
3797  builder()
3798  ->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(brand_args[1])
3799  .MoveRegister(receiver, brand_args[0])
3800  .MoveRegister(execution_context()->reg(), brand_args[2])
3801  .LoadLiteral(Smi::FromInt(depth))
3802  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(brand_args[3])
3803  .CallRuntime(Runtime::kAddPrivateBrand, brand_args);
3804  }
3805 }
3806 
3807 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildInstanceMemberInitialization(Register constructor,
3808  Register instance) {
3809  RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(1);
3810  Register initializer = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
3811 
3812  FeedbackSlot slot = feedback_spec()->AddLoadICSlot();
3813  BytecodeLabel done;
3814 
3815  builder()
3816  ->LoadClassFieldsInitializer(constructor, feedback_index(slot))
3817  // TODO(gsathya): This jump can be elided for the base
3818  // constructor and derived constructor. This is only required
3819  // when called from an arrow function.
3820  .JumpIfUndefined(&done)
3821  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(initializer)
3822  .MoveRegister(instance, args[0])
3823  .CallProperty(initializer, args,
3824  feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddCallICSlot()))
3825  .Bind(&done);
3826 }

3831  // Native functions don't use argument adaption and so have the special
3832  // kDontAdaptArgumentsSentinel as their parameter count.
3833  int index = feedback_spec()->AddCreateClosureParameterCount(
3834  kDontAdaptArgumentsSentinel);

3839 
3840 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitConditionalChain(ConditionalChain* expr) {
3841  ConditionalChainControlFlowBuilder conditional_builder(
3842  builder(), block_coverage_builder_, expr,
3843  expr->conditional_chain_length());
3844 
3845  HoleCheckElisionMergeScope merge_elider(this);
3846  {
3847  bool should_visit_else_expression = true;
3848  HoleCheckElisionScope elider(this);
3849  for (size_t i = 0; i < expr->conditional_chain_length(); ++i) {
3850  if (expr->condition_at(i)->ToBooleanIsTrue()) {
3851  // Generate then block unconditionally as always true.
3852  should_visit_else_expression = false;
3853  HoleCheckElisionMergeScope::Branch branch(merge_elider);
3854  conditional_builder.ThenAt(i);
3855  VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->then_expression_at(i));
3856  break;
3857  } else if (expr->condition_at(i)->ToBooleanIsFalse()) {
3858  // Generate else block unconditionally by skipping the then block.
3859  HoleCheckElisionMergeScope::Branch branch(merge_elider);
3860  conditional_builder.ElseAt(i);
3861  } else {
3862  VisitForTest(
3863  expr->condition_at(i), conditional_builder.then_labels_at(i),
3864  conditional_builder.else_labels_at(i), TestFallthrough::kThen);
3865  {
3866  HoleCheckElisionMergeScope::Branch branch(merge_elider);
3867  conditional_builder.ThenAt(i);
3868  VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->then_expression_at(i));
3869  }
3870  conditional_builder.JumpToEnd();
3871  {
3872  HoleCheckElisionMergeScope::Branch branch(merge_elider);
3873  conditional_builder.ElseAt(i);
3874  }
3875  }
3876  }
3877 
3878  if (should_visit_else_expression) {
3879  VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->else_expression());
3880  }
3881  }
3882  merge_elider.Merge();
3883 }
3884 
3885 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitConditional(Conditional* expr) {
3886  ConditionalControlFlowBuilder conditional_builder(
3887  builder(), block_coverage_builder_, expr);
3888 
3889  if (expr->condition()->ToBooleanIsTrue()) {
3890  // Generate then block unconditionally as always true.
3891  conditional_builder.Then();
3892  VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->then_expression());
3893  } else if (expr->condition()->ToBooleanIsFalse()) {
3894  // Generate else block unconditionally if it exists.
3895  conditional_builder.Else();
3896  VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->else_expression());
3897  } else {
3898  VisitForTest(expr->condition(), conditional_builder.then_labels(),
3899  conditional_builder.else_labels(), TestFallthrough::kThen);
3900 
3901  HoleCheckElisionMergeScope merge_elider(this);
3902  conditional_builder.Then();
3903  {
3904  HoleCheckElisionMergeScope::Branch branch_elider(merge_elider);
3905  VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->then_expression());
3906  }
3907  conditional_builder.JumpToEnd();
3908 
3909  conditional_builder.Else();
3910  {
3911  HoleCheckElisionMergeScope::Branch branch_elider(merge_elider);
3912  VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->else_expression());
3913  }
3914 
3915  merge_elider.Merge();
3916  }
3917 }
3918 
3919 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitLiteral(Literal* expr) {
3920  if (execution_result()->IsEffect()) return;
3921  switch (expr->type()) {
3922  case Literal::kSmi:
3923  builder()->LoadLiteral(expr->AsSmiLiteral());
3924  break;
3925  case Literal::kHeapNumber:
3926  builder()->LoadLiteral(expr->AsNumber());
3927  break;
3928  case Literal::kUndefined:
3929  builder()->LoadUndefined();
3930  break;
3931  case Literal::kBoolean:
3932  builder()->LoadBoolean(expr->ToBooleanIsTrue());
3933  execution_result()->SetResultIsBoolean();
3934  break;
3935  case Literal::kNull:
3936  builder()->LoadNull();
3937  break;
3938  case Literal::kTheHole:
3939  builder()->LoadTheHole();
3940  break;
3941  case Literal::kString:
3942  builder()->LoadLiteral(expr->AsRawString());
3943  execution_result()->SetResultIsInternalizedString();
3944  break;
3945  case Literal::kConsString:
3946  builder()->LoadLiteral(expr->AsConsString());
3947  break;
3948  case Literal::kBigInt:
3949  builder()->LoadLiteral(expr->AsBigInt());
3950  break;
3951  }
3952 }
3953 
3954 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitRegExpLiteral(RegExpLiteral* expr) {
3955  // Materialize a regular expression literal.
3956  builder()->CreateRegExpLiteral(
3957  expr->raw_pattern(), feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddLiteralSlot()),
3958  expr->flags());
3959 }
