3961 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildCreateObjectLiteral(Register literal,
3962  uint8_t flags, size_t entry) {
3963  // TODO(cbruni): Directly generate runtime call for literals we cannot
3964  // optimize once the CreateShallowObjectLiteral stub is in sync with the TF
3965  // optimizations.
3966  int literal_index = feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddLiteralSlot());
3967  builder()
3968  ->CreateObjectLiteral(entry, literal_index, flags)
3969  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(literal);
3970 }
3971 
3972 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitObjectLiteral(ObjectLiteral* expr) {
3973  expr->builder()->InitDepthAndFlags();
3974 
3975  // Fast path for the empty object literal which doesn't need an
3976  // AllocationSite.
3977  if (expr->builder()->IsEmptyObjectLiteral()) {
3978  DCHECK(expr->builder()->IsFastCloningSupported());
3979  builder()->CreateEmptyObjectLiteral();
3980  return;
3981  }
3982 
3983  Variable* home_object = expr->home_object();
3984  if (home_object != nullptr) {
3985  DCHECK(home_object->is_used());
3986  DCHECK(home_object->IsContextSlot());
3987  }
3988  MultipleEntryBlockContextScope object_literal_context_scope(
3989  this, home_object ? home_object->scope() : nullptr);
3990 
3991  // Deep-copy the literal boilerplate.
3992  uint8_t flags = CreateObjectLiteralFlags::Encode(
3993  expr->builder()->ComputeFlags(),
3994  expr->builder()->IsFastCloningSupported());
3995 
3996  Register literal = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
3997 
3998  // Create literal object.
3999  int property_index = 0;
4000  bool clone_object_spread =
4001  expr->properties()->first()->kind() == ObjectLiteral::Property::SPREAD;
4002  if (clone_object_spread) {
4003  // Avoid the slow path for spreads in the following common cases:
4004  // 1) `let obj = { ...source }`
4005  // 2) `let obj = { ...source, override: 1 }`
4006  // 3) `let obj = { ...source, ...overrides }`
4007  RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
4008  Expression* property = expr->properties()->first()->value();
4009  Register from_value = VisitForRegisterValue(property);
4010  int clone_index = feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddCloneObjectSlot());
4011  builder()->CloneObject(from_value, flags, clone_index);
4012  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(literal);
4013  property_index++;
4014  } else {
4015  size_t entry;
4016  // If constant properties is an empty fixed array, use a cached empty fixed
4017  // array to ensure it's only added to the constant pool once.
4018  if (expr->builder()->properties_count() == 0) {
4019  entry = builder()->EmptyObjectBoilerplateDescriptionConstantPoolEntry();
4020  } else {
4021  entry = builder()->AllocateDeferredConstantPoolEntry();
4022  object_literals_.push_back(std::make_pair(expr->builder(), entry));
4023  }
4024  BuildCreateObjectLiteral(literal, flags, entry);
4025  }
4026 
4027  // Store computed values into the literal.
4028  AccessorTable<ObjectLiteral::Property> accessor_table(zone());
4029  for (; property_index < expr->properties()->length(); property_index++) {
4030  ObjectLiteral::Property* property = expr->properties()->at(property_index);
4031  if (property->is_computed_name()) break;
4032  if (!clone_object_spread && property->IsCompileTimeValue()) continue;
4033 
4034  RegisterAllocationScope inner_register_scope(this);
4035  Literal* key = property->key()->AsLiteral();
4036  switch (property->kind()) {
4037  case ObjectLiteral::Property::SPREAD:
4038  UNREACHABLE();
4039  case ObjectLiteral::Property::CONSTANT:
4040  case ObjectLiteral::Property::MATERIALIZED_LITERAL:
4041  DCHECK(clone_object_spread || !property->value()->IsCompileTimeValue());
4042  [[fallthrough]];
4043  case ObjectLiteral::Property::COMPUTED: {
4044  // It is safe to use [[Put]] here because the boilerplate already
4045  // contains computed properties with an uninitialized value.
4046  Register key_reg;
4047  if (key->IsStringLiteral()) {
4048  DCHECK(key->IsPropertyName());
4049  } else {
4050  key_reg = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
4051  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(property->key());
4052  VisitForRegisterValue(property->key(), key_reg);
4053  }
4054 
4055  object_literal_context_scope.SetEnteredIf(
4056  property->value()->IsConciseMethodDefinition());
4057  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(property->value());
4058 
4059  if (property->emit_store()) {
4060  VisitForAccumulatorValue(property->value());
4061  if (key->IsStringLiteral()) {
4062  FeedbackSlot slot = feedback_spec()->AddDefineNamedOwnICSlot();
4063  builder()->DefineNamedOwnProperty(literal, key->AsRawPropertyName(),
4064  feedback_index(slot));
4065  } else {
4066  FeedbackSlot slot = feedback_spec()->AddDefineKeyedOwnICSlot();
4067  builder()->DefineKeyedOwnProperty(
4068  literal, key_reg, DefineKeyedOwnPropertyFlag::kNoFlags,
4069  feedback_index(slot));
4070  }
4071  } else {
4072  VisitForEffect(property->value());
4073  }
4074  break;
4075  }
4076  case ObjectLiteral::Property::PROTOTYPE: {
4077  // __proto__:null is handled by CreateObjectLiteral.
4078  if (property->IsNullPrototype()) break;
4079  DCHECK(property->emit_store());
4080  DCHECK(!property->NeedsSetFunctionName());
4081  RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
4082  builder()->MoveRegister(literal, args[0]);
4083  object_literal_context_scope.SetEnteredIf(false);
4084  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(property->value());
4085  VisitForRegisterValue(property->value(), args[1]);
4086  builder()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kInternalSetPrototype, args);
4087  break;
4088  }
4089  case ObjectLiteral::Property::GETTER:
4090  if (property->emit_store()) {
4091  accessor_table.LookupOrInsert(key)->getter = property;
4092  }
4093  break;
4094  case ObjectLiteral::Property::SETTER:
4095  if (property->emit_store()) {
4096  accessor_table.LookupOrInsert(key)->setter = property;
4097  }
4098  break;
4099  }
4100  }
4101 
4102  // Define accessors, using only a single call to the runtime for each pair
4103  // of corresponding getters and setters.
4104  object_literal_context_scope.SetEnteredIf(true);
4105  for (auto accessors : accessor_table.ordered_accessors()) {
4106  RegisterAllocationScope inner_register_scope(this);
4107  RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(5);
4108  builder()->MoveRegister(literal, args[0]);
4109  VisitForRegisterValue(accessors.first, args[1]);
4110  VisitLiteralAccessor(accessors.second->getter, args[2]);
4111  VisitLiteralAccessor(accessors.second->setter, args[3]);
4112  builder()
4113  ->LoadLiteral(Smi::FromInt(NONE))
4114  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[4])
4115  .CallRuntime(Runtime::kDefineAccessorPropertyUnchecked, args);
4116  }
4117 
4118  // Object literals have two parts. The "static" part on the left contains no
4119  // computed property names, and so we can compute its map ahead of time; see
4120  // Runtime_CreateObjectLiteralBoilerplate. The second "dynamic" part starts
4121  // with the first computed property name and continues with all properties to
4122  // its right. All the code from above initializes the static component of the
4123  // object literal, and arranges for the map of the result to reflect the
4124  // static order in which the keys appear. For the dynamic properties, we
4125  // compile them into a series of "SetOwnProperty" runtime calls. This will
4126  // preserve insertion order.
4127  for (; property_index < expr->properties()->length(); property_index++) {
4128  ObjectLiteral::Property* property = expr->properties()->at(property_index);
4129  RegisterAllocationScope inner_register_scope(this);
4130 
4131  bool should_be_in_object_literal_scope =
4132  (property->value()->IsConciseMethodDefinition() ||
4133  property->value()->IsAccessorFunctionDefinition());
4134 
4135  if (property->IsPrototype()) {
4136  // __proto__:null is handled by CreateObjectLiteral.
4137  if (property->IsNullPrototype()) continue;
4138  DCHECK(property->emit_store());
4139  DCHECK(!property->NeedsSetFunctionName());
4140  RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
4141  builder()->MoveRegister(literal, args[0]);
4142 
4143  DCHECK(!should_be_in_object_literal_scope);
4144  object_literal_context_scope.SetEnteredIf(false);
4145  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(property->value());
4146  VisitForRegisterValue(property->value(), args[1]);
4147  builder()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kInternalSetPrototype, args);
4148  continue;
4149  }
4150 
4151  switch (property->kind()) {
4152  case ObjectLiteral::Property::CONSTANT:
4153  case ObjectLiteral::Property::COMPUTED:
4154  case ObjectLiteral::Property::MATERIALIZED_LITERAL: {
4155  // Computed property keys don't belong to the object literal scope (even
4156  // if they're syntactically inside it).
4157  if (property->is_computed_name()) {
4158  object_literal_context_scope.SetEnteredIf(false);
4159  }
4160  Register key = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
4161  BuildLoadPropertyKey(property, key);
4162 
4163  object_literal_context_scope.SetEnteredIf(
4164  should_be_in_object_literal_scope);
4165  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(property->value());
4166 
4167  DefineKeyedOwnPropertyInLiteralFlags data_property_flags =
4168  DefineKeyedOwnPropertyInLiteralFlag::kNoFlags;
4169  if (property->NeedsSetFunctionName()) {
4170  // Static class fields require the name property to be set on
4171  // the class, meaning we can't wait until the
4172  // DefineKeyedOwnPropertyInLiteral call later to set the name.
4173  if (property->value()->IsClassLiteral() &&
4174  property->value()->AsClassLiteral()->static_initializer() !=
4175  nullptr) {
4176  VisitClassLiteral(property->value()->AsClassLiteral(), key);
4177  } else {
4178  data_property_flags |=
4179  DefineKeyedOwnPropertyInLiteralFlag::kSetFunctionName;
4180  VisitForAccumulatorValue(property->value());
4181  }
4182  } else {
4183  VisitForAccumulatorValue(property->value());
4184  }
4185 
4186  FeedbackSlot slot =
4187  feedback_spec()->AddDefineKeyedOwnPropertyInLiteralICSlot();
4188  builder()->DefineKeyedOwnPropertyInLiteral(
4189  literal, key, data_property_flags, feedback_index(slot));
4190  break;
4191  }
4192  case ObjectLiteral::Property::GETTER:
4193  case ObjectLiteral::Property::SETTER: {
4194  // Computed property keys don't belong to the object literal scope (even
4195  // if they're syntactically inside it).
4196  if (property->is_computed_name()) {
4197  object_literal_context_scope.SetEnteredIf(false);
4198  }
4199  RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(4);
4200  builder()->MoveRegister(literal, args[0]);
4201  BuildLoadPropertyKey(property, args[1]);
4202 
4203  DCHECK(should_be_in_object_literal_scope);
4204  object_literal_context_scope.SetEnteredIf(true);
4205  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(property->value());
4206  VisitForRegisterValue(property->value(), args[2]);
4207  builder()
4208  ->LoadLiteral(Smi::FromInt(NONE))
4209  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[3]);
4210  Runtime::FunctionId function_id =
4211  property->kind() == ObjectLiteral::Property::GETTER
4212  ? Runtime::kDefineGetterPropertyUnchecked
4213  : Runtime::kDefineSetterPropertyUnchecked;
4214  builder()->CallRuntime(function_id, args);
4215  break;
4216  }
4217  case ObjectLiteral::Property::SPREAD: {
4218  // TODO(olivf, chrome:1204540) This can be slower than the Babel
4219  // translation. Should we compile this to a copying loop in bytecode?
4220  RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
4221  builder()->MoveRegister(literal, args[0]);
4222  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(property->value());
4223  object_literal_context_scope.SetEnteredIf(false);
4224  VisitForRegisterValue(property->value(), args[1]);
4225  builder()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kInlineCopyDataProperties, args);
4226  break;
4227  }
4228  case ObjectLiteral::Property::PROTOTYPE:
4229  UNREACHABLE(); // Handled specially above.
4230  }
4231  }
4232 
4233  if (home_object != nullptr) {
4234  object_literal_context_scope.SetEnteredIf(true);
4235  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(literal);
4236  BuildVariableAssignment(home_object, Token::kInit, HoleCheckMode::kElided);
4237  }
4238  // Make sure to exit the scope before materialising the value into the
4239  // accumulator, to prevent the context scope from clobbering it.
4240  object_literal_context_scope.SetEnteredIf(false);
4241  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(literal);
4242 }
4243 
4244 // Fill an array with values from an iterator, starting at a given index. It is
4245 // guaranteed that the loop will only terminate if the iterator is exhausted, or
4246 // if one of iterator.next(), value.done, or value.value fail.
4247 //
4248 // In pseudocode:
4249 //
4250 // loop {
4251 // value = iterator.next()
4252 // if (value.done) break;
4253 // value = value.value
4254 // array[index++] = value
4255 // }
4256 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildFillArrayWithIterator(
4257  IteratorRecord iterator, Register array, Register index, Register value,
4258  FeedbackSlot next_value_slot, FeedbackSlot next_done_slot,
4259  FeedbackSlot index_slot, FeedbackSlot element_slot) {
4260  DCHECK(array.is_valid());
4261  DCHECK(index.is_valid());
4262  DCHECK(value.is_valid());
4263 
4264  LoopBuilder loop_builder(builder(), nullptr, nullptr, feedback_spec());
4265  LoopScope loop_scope(this, &loop_builder);
4266 
4267  // Call the iterator's .next() method. Break from the loop if the `done`
4268  // property is truthy, otherwise load the value from the iterator result and
4269  // append the argument.
4270  BuildIteratorNext(iterator, value);
4271  builder()->LoadNamedProperty(
4272  value, ast_string_constants()->done_string(),
4273  feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddLoadICSlot()));
4274  loop_builder.BreakIfTrue(ToBooleanMode::kConvertToBoolean);
4275 
4276  loop_builder.LoopBody();
4277  builder()
4278  // value = value.value
4279  ->LoadNamedProperty(value, ast_string_constants()->value_string(),
4280  feedback_index(next_value_slot))
4281  // array[index] = value
4282  .StoreInArrayLiteral(array, index, feedback_index(element_slot))
4283  // index++
4284  .LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(index)
4285  .UnaryOperation(Token::kInc, feedback_index(index_slot))
4286  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(index);
4287  loop_builder.BindContinueTarget();
4288 }
4289 
4290 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildCreateArrayLiteral(
4291  const ZonePtrList<Expression>* elements, ArrayLiteral* expr) {
4292  RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
4293  // Make this the first register allocated so that it has a chance of aliasing
4294  // the next register allocated after returning from this function.
4295  Register array = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
4296  Register index = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
4297  SharedFeedbackSlot element_slot(feedback_spec(),
4298  FeedbackSlotKind::kStoreInArrayLiteral);
4299  ZonePtrList<Expression>::const_iterator current = elements->begin();
4300  ZonePtrList<Expression>::const_iterator end = elements->end();
4301  bool is_empty = elements->is_empty();
4302 
4303  if (!is_empty && (*current)->IsSpread()) {
4304  // If we have a leading spread, use CreateArrayFromIterable to create
4305  // an array from it and then add the remaining components to that array.
4306  VisitForAccumulatorValue(*current);
4307  builder()->SetExpressionPosition((*current)->AsSpread()->expression());
4308  builder()->CreateArrayFromIterable().StoreAccumulatorInRegister(array);
4309 
4310  if (++current != end) {
4311  // If there are remaining elements, prepare the index register that is
4312  // used for adding those elements. The next index is the length of the
4313  // newly created array.
4314  auto length = ast_string_constants()->length_string();
4315  int length_load_slot = feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddLoadICSlot());
4316  builder()
4317  ->LoadNamedProperty(array, length, length_load_slot)
4318  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(index);
4319  }
4320  } else {
4321  // There are some elements before the first (if any) spread, and we can
4322  // use a boilerplate when creating the initial array from those elements.
4323 
4324  // First, allocate a constant pool entry for the boilerplate that will
4325  // be created during finalization, and will contain all the constant
4326  // elements before the first spread. This also handle the empty array case
4327  // and one-shot optimization.
4328 
4329  ArrayLiteralBoilerplateBuilder* array_literal_builder = nullptr;
4330  if (expr != nullptr) {
4331  array_literal_builder = expr->builder();
4332  } else {
4333  DCHECK(!elements->is_empty());
4334 
4335  // get first_spread_index
4336  int first_spread_index = -1;
4337  for (auto iter = elements->begin(); iter != elements->end(); iter++) {
4338  if ((*iter)->IsSpread()) {
4339  first_spread_index = static_cast<int>(iter - elements->begin());
4340  break;
4341  }
4342  }
4343 
4344  array_literal_builder = zone()->New<ArrayLiteralBoilerplateBuilder>(
4345  elements, first_spread_index);
4346  array_literal_builder->InitDepthAndFlags();
4347  }
4348 
4349  DCHECK(array_literal_builder != nullptr);
4350  uint8_t flags = CreateArrayLiteralFlags::Encode(
4351  array_literal_builder->IsFastCloningSupported(),
4352  array_literal_builder->ComputeFlags());
4353  if (is_empty) {
4354  // Empty array literal fast-path.
4355  int literal_index = feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddLiteralSlot());
4356  DCHECK(array_literal_builder->IsFastCloningSupported());
4357  builder()->CreateEmptyArrayLiteral(literal_index);
4358  } else {
4359  // Create array literal from boilerplate.
4360  size_t entry = builder()->AllocateDeferredConstantPoolEntry();
4361  array_literals_.push_back(std::make_pair(array_literal_builder, entry));
4362  int literal_index = feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddLiteralSlot());
4363  builder()->CreateArrayLiteral(entry, literal_index, flags);
4364  }
4365  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(array);
4366 
4367  ZonePtrList<Expression>::const_iterator first_spread_or_end =
4368  array_literal_builder->first_spread_index() >= 0
4369  ? current + array_literal_builder->first_spread_index()
4370  : end;
4371 
4372  // Insert the missing non-constant elements, up until the first spread
4373  // index, into the initial array (the remaining elements will be inserted
4374  // below).
4375  DCHECK_EQ(current, elements->begin());
4376  int array_index = 0;
4377  for (; current != first_spread_or_end; ++current, array_index++) {
4378  Expression* subexpr = *current;
4379  DCHECK(!subexpr->IsSpread());
4380  // Skip the constants.
4381  if (subexpr->IsCompileTimeValue()) continue;
4382 
4383  builder()
4384  ->LoadLiteral(Smi::FromInt(array_index))
4385  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(index);
4386  VisitForAccumulatorValue(subexpr);
4387  builder()->StoreInArrayLiteral(array, index,
4388  feedback_index(element_slot.Get()));
4389  }
4390 
4391  if (current != end) {
4392  // If there are remaining elements, prepare the index register
4393  // to store the next element, which comes from the first spread.
4394  builder()
4395  ->LoadLiteral(Smi::FromInt(array_index))
4396  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(index);
4397  }
4398  }
4399 
4400  // Now build insertions for the remaining elements from current to end.
4401  SharedFeedbackSlot index_slot(feedback_spec(), FeedbackSlotKind::kBinaryOp);
4402  SharedFeedbackSlot length_slot(
4403  feedback_spec(), feedback_spec()->GetStoreICSlot(LanguageMode::kStrict));
4404  for (; current != end; ++current) {
4405  Expression* subexpr = *current;
4406  if (subexpr->IsSpread()) {
4407  RegisterAllocationScope scope(this);
4408  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(subexpr->AsSpread()->expression());
4409  VisitForAccumulatorValue(subexpr->AsSpread()->expression());
4410  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(subexpr->AsSpread()->expression());
4411  IteratorRecord iterator = BuildGetIteratorRecord(IteratorType::kNormal);
4412 
4413  Register value = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
4414  FeedbackSlot next_value_load_slot = feedback_spec()->AddLoadICSlot();
4415  FeedbackSlot next_done_load_slot = feedback_spec()->AddLoadICSlot();
4416  FeedbackSlot real_index_slot = index_slot.Get();
4417  FeedbackSlot real_element_slot = element_slot.Get();
4418  BuildFillArrayWithIterator(iterator, array, index, value,
4419  next_value_load_slot, next_done_load_slot,
4420  real_index_slot, real_element_slot);
4421  } else if (!subexpr->IsTheHoleLiteral()) {
4422  // literal[index++] = subexpr
4423  VisitForAccumulatorValue(subexpr);
4424  builder()
4425  ->StoreInArrayLiteral(array, index,
4426  feedback_index(element_slot.Get()))
4427  .LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(index);
4428  // Only increase the index if we are not the last element.
4429  if (current + 1 != end) {
4430  builder()
4431  ->UnaryOperation(Token::kInc, feedback_index(index_slot.Get()))
4432  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(index);
4433  }
4434  } else {
4435  // literal.length = ++index
4436  // length_slot is only used when there are holes.
4437  auto length = ast_string_constants()->length_string();
4438  builder()
4439  ->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(index)
4440  .UnaryOperation(Token::kInc, feedback_index(index_slot.Get()))
4441  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(index)
4442  .SetNamedProperty(array, length, feedback_index(length_slot.Get()),
4443  LanguageMode::kStrict);
4444  }
4445  }
4446 
4447  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(array);
4448 }
4449 
4450 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitArrayLiteral(ArrayLiteral* expr) {
4451  expr->builder()->InitDepthAndFlags();
4452  BuildCreateArrayLiteral(expr->values(), expr);
4453 }

4457  BuildVariableLoad(proxy->var(), proxy->hole_check_mode());

4482 
4483 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildVariableLoad(Variable* variable,
4484  HoleCheckMode hole_check_mode,
4485  TypeofMode typeof_mode) {
4486  switch (variable->location()) {
4487  case VariableLocation::LOCAL: {
4488  Register source(builder()->Local(variable->index()));
4489  // We need to load the variable into the accumulator, even when in a
4490  // VisitForRegisterScope, in order to avoid register aliasing if
4491  // subsequent expressions assign to the same variable.
4492  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(source);
4493  if (VariableNeedsHoleCheckInCurrentBlock(variable, hole_check_mode)) {
4494  BuildThrowIfHole(variable);
4495  }
4496  break;
4497  }
4498  case VariableLocation::PARAMETER: {
4499  Register source;
4500  if (variable->IsReceiver()) {
4501  source = builder()->Receiver();
4502  } else {
4503  source = builder()->Parameter(variable->index());
4504  }
4505  // We need to load the variable into the accumulator, even when in a
4506  // VisitForRegisterScope, in order to avoid register aliasing if
4507  // subsequent expressions assign to the same variable.
4508  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(source);
4509  if (VariableNeedsHoleCheckInCurrentBlock(variable, hole_check_mode)) {
4510  BuildThrowIfHole(variable);
4511  }
4512  break;
4513  }
4514  case VariableLocation::UNALLOCATED: {
4515  // The global identifier "undefined" is immutable. Everything
4516  // else could be reassigned. For performance, we do a pointer comparison
4517  // rather than checking if the raw_name is really "undefined".
4518  if (variable->raw_name() == ast_string_constants()->undefined_string()) {
4519  builder()->LoadUndefined();
4520  } else {
4521  FeedbackSlot slot = GetCachedLoadGlobalICSlot(typeof_mode, variable);
4522  builder()->LoadGlobal(variable->raw_name(), feedback_index(slot),
4523  typeof_mode);
4524  }
4525  break;
4526  }
4527  case VariableLocation::CONTEXT: {
4528  int depth = execution_context()->ContextChainDepth(variable->scope());
4529  ContextScope* context = execution_context()->Previous(depth);
4530  Register context_reg;
4531  if (context) {
4532  context_reg = context->reg();
4533  depth = 0;
4534  } else {
4535  context_reg = execution_context()->reg();
4536  }
4537 
4538  BytecodeArrayBuilder::ContextSlotMutability immutable =
4539  (variable->maybe_assigned() == kNotAssigned)
4540  ? BytecodeArrayBuilder::kImmutableSlot
4541  : BytecodeArrayBuilder::kMutableSlot;
4542  Register acc = Register::virtual_accumulator();
4543  if (immutable == BytecodeArrayBuilder::kImmutableSlot &&
4544  IsVariableInRegister(variable, acc)) {
4545  return;
4546  }
4547 
4548  builder()->LoadContextSlot(context_reg, variable, depth, immutable);
4549  if (VariableNeedsHoleCheckInCurrentBlock(variable, hole_check_mode)) {
4550  BuildThrowIfHole(variable);
4551  }
4552  if (immutable == BytecodeArrayBuilder::kImmutableSlot) {
4553  SetVariableInRegister(variable, acc);
4554  }
4555  break;
4556  }
4557  case VariableLocation::LOOKUP: {
4558  switch (variable->mode()) {
4559  case VariableMode::kDynamicLocal: {
4560  Variable* local_variable = variable->local_if_not_shadowed();
4561  int depth =
4562  execution_context()->ContextChainDepth(local_variable->scope());
4563  ContextMode context_mode =
4564  (local_variable->scope()->has_context_cells()
4565  ? ContextMode::kHasContextCells
4566  : ContextMode::kNoContextCells);
4567  builder()->LoadLookupContextSlot(variable->raw_name(), typeof_mode,
4568  context_mode,
4569  local_variable->index(), depth);
4570  if (VariableNeedsHoleCheckInCurrentBlock(local_variable,
4571  hole_check_mode)) {
4572  BuildThrowIfHole(local_variable);
4573  }
4574  break;
4575  }
4576  case VariableMode::kDynamicGlobal: {
4577  int depth =
4578  current_scope()->ContextChainLengthUntilOutermostSloppyEval();
4579  // TODO(1008414): Add back caching here when bug is fixed properly.
4580  FeedbackSlot slot = feedback_spec()->AddLoadGlobalICSlot(typeof_mode);
4581 
4582  builder()->LoadLookupGlobalSlot(variable->raw_name(), typeof_mode,
4583  feedback_index(slot), depth);
4584  break;
4585  }
4586  default: {
4587  // Normally, private names should not be looked up dynamically,
4588  // but we make an exception in debug-evaluate, in that case the
4589  // lookup will be done in %SetPrivateMember() and %GetPrivateMember()
4590  // calls, not here.
4591  DCHECK(!variable->raw_name()->IsPrivateName());
4592  builder()->LoadLookupSlot(variable->raw_name(), typeof_mode);
4593  break;
4594  }
4595  }
4596  break;
4597  }
4598  case VariableLocation::MODULE: {
4599  int depth = execution_context()->ContextChainDepth(variable->scope());
4600  builder()->LoadModuleVariable(variable->index(), depth);
4601  if (VariableNeedsHoleCheckInCurrentBlock(variable, hole_check_mode)) {
4602  BuildThrowIfHole(variable);
4603  }
4604  break;
4605  }
4606  case VariableLocation::REPL_GLOBAL: {
4607  DCHECK(variable->IsReplGlobal());
4608  FeedbackSlot slot = GetCachedLoadGlobalICSlot(typeof_mode, variable);
4609  builder()->LoadGlobal(variable->raw_name(), feedback_index(slot),
4610  typeof_mode);
4611  break;
4612  }
4613  }
4614 }
4615 
4616 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildVariableLoadForAccumulatorValue(
4617  Variable* variable, HoleCheckMode hole_check_mode, TypeofMode typeof_mode) {
4618  ValueResultScope accumulator_result(this);
4619  BuildVariableLoad(variable, hole_check_mode, typeof_mode);
4620 }

4622 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildReturn(int source_position) {
4623  if (v8_flags.trace) {
4624  RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
4625  Register result = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
4626  // Runtime returns {result} value, preserving accumulator.
4627  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(result).CallRuntime(
4628  Runtime::kTraceExit, result);
4629  }
4630  builder()->SetStatementPosition(source_position);
4631  builder()->Return();
4632 }

4634 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildAsyncReturn(int source_position) {
4635  RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
4636 
4637  if (IsAsyncGeneratorFunction(info()->literal()->kind())) {
4638  RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(3);
4639  builder()
4640  ->MoveRegister(generator_object(), args[0]) // generator
4641  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[1]) // value
4642  .LoadTrue()
4643  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[2]) // done
4644  .CallRuntime(Runtime::kInlineAsyncGeneratorResolve, args);
4645  } else {
4646  DCHECK(IsAsyncFunction(info()->literal()->kind()) ||
4647  IsModuleWithTopLevelAwait(info()->literal()->kind()));
4648  RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
4649  builder()
4650  ->MoveRegister(generator_object(), args[0]) // generator
4651  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[1]) // value
4652  .CallRuntime(Runtime::kInlineAsyncFunctionResolve, args);
4653  }
4654 
4655  BuildReturn(source_position);
4656 }
4657 
4658 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildReThrow() { builder()->ReThrow(); }
4659 
4660 void BytecodeGenerator::RememberHoleCheckInCurrentBlock(Variable* variable) {
4661  if (!v8_flags.ignition_elide_redundant_tdz_checks) return;
4662 
4663  // The first N-1 variables that need hole checks may be cached in a bitmap to
4664  // elide subsequent hole checks in the same basic block, where N is
4665  // Variable::kHoleCheckBitmapBits.
4666  //
4667  // This numbering is done during bytecode generation instead of scope analysis
4668  // for 2 reasons:
4669  //
4670  // 1. There may be multiple eagerly compiled inner functions during a single
4671  // run of scope analysis, so a global numbering will result in fewer variables
4672  // with cacheable hole checks.
4673  //
4674  // 2. Compiler::CollectSourcePositions reparses functions and checks that the
4675  // recompiled bytecode is identical. Therefore the numbering must be kept
4676  // identical regardless of whether a function is eagerly compiled as part of
4677  // an outer compilation or recompiled during source position collection. The
4678  // simplest way to guarantee identical numbering is to scope it to the
4679  // compilation instead of scope analysis.
4680  variable->RememberHoleCheckInBitmap(hole_check_bitmap_,
4681  vars_in_hole_check_bitmap_);
4682 }
4683 
4684 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildThrowIfHole(Variable* variable) {
4685  if (variable->is_this()) {
4686  DCHECK(variable->mode() == VariableMode::kConst);
4687  builder()->ThrowSuperNotCalledIfHole();
4688  } else {
4689  builder()->ThrowReferenceErrorIfHole(variable->raw_name());
4690  }
4691  RememberHoleCheckInCurrentBlock(variable);
4692 }
4693 
4694 bool BytecodeGenerator::VariableNeedsHoleCheckInCurrentBlock(
4695  Variable* variable, HoleCheckMode hole_check_mode) {
4696  return hole_check_mode == HoleCheckMode::kRequired &&
4697  !variable->HasRememberedHoleCheck(hole_check_bitmap_);
4698 }
4699 
4700 bool BytecodeGenerator::VariableNeedsHoleCheckInCurrentBlockForAssignment(
4701  Variable* variable, Token::Value op, HoleCheckMode hole_check_mode) {
4702  return VariableNeedsHoleCheckInCurrentBlock(variable, hole_check_mode) ||
4703  (variable->is_this() && variable->mode() == VariableMode::kConst &&
4704  op == Token::kInit);
4705 }
4706 
4707 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildHoleCheckForVariableAssignment(Variable* variable,
4708  Token::Value op) {
4709  DCHECK(!IsPrivateMethodOrAccessorVariableMode(variable->mode()));
4710  DCHECK(VariableNeedsHoleCheckInCurrentBlockForAssignment(
4711  variable, op, HoleCheckMode::kRequired));
4712  if (variable->is_this()) {
4713  DCHECK(variable->mode() == VariableMode::kConst && op == Token::kInit);
4714  // Perform an initialization check for 'this'. 'this' variable is the
4715  // only variable able to trigger bind operations outside the TDZ
4716  // via 'super' calls.
4717  //
4718  // Do not remember the hole check because this bytecode throws if 'this' is
4719  // *not* the hole, i.e. the opposite of the TDZ hole check.
4720  builder()->ThrowSuperAlreadyCalledIfNotHole();
4721  } else {
4722  // Perform an initialization check for let/const declared variables.
4723  // E.g. let x = (x = 20); is not allowed.
4724  DCHECK(IsLexicalVariableMode(variable->mode()));
4725  BuildThrowIfHole(variable);
4726  }
4727 }
4728 
4729 void BytecodeGenerator::AddDisposableValue(VariableMode mode) {
4730  if (mode == VariableMode::kUsing) {
4731  RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
4732  builder()
4733  ->MoveRegister(current_disposables_stack(), args[0])
4734  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[1])
4735  .CallRuntime(Runtime::kAddDisposableValue, args);
4736  } else if (mode == VariableMode::kAwaitUsing) {
4737  RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
4738  builder()
4739  ->MoveRegister(current_disposables_stack(), args[0])
4740  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[1])
4741  .CallRuntime(Runtime::kAddAsyncDisposableValue, args);
4742  }
4743 }
4744 
4745 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildVariableAssignment(
4746  Variable* variable, Token::Value op, HoleCheckMode hole_check_mode,
4747  LookupHoistingMode lookup_hoisting_mode) {
4748  VariableMode mode = variable->mode();
4749  RegisterAllocationScope assignment_register_scope(this);
4750  switch (variable->location()) {
4751  case VariableLocation::PARAMETER:
4752  case VariableLocation::LOCAL: {
4753  Register destination;
4754  if (VariableLocation::PARAMETER == variable->location()) {
4755  if (variable->IsReceiver()) {
4756  destination = builder()->Receiver();
4757  } else {
4758  destination = builder()->Parameter(variable->index());
4759  }
4760  } else {
4761  destination = builder()->Local(variable->index());
4762  }
4763 
4764  if (VariableNeedsHoleCheckInCurrentBlockForAssignment(variable, op,
4765  hole_check_mode)) {
4766  // Load destination to check for hole.
4767  Register value_temp = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
4768  builder()
4769  ->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(value_temp)
4770  .LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(destination);
4771  BuildHoleCheckForVariableAssignment(variable, op);
4772  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(value_temp);
4773  }
4774 
4775  if ((mode != VariableMode::kConst && mode != VariableMode::kUsing &&
4776  mode != VariableMode::kAwaitUsing) ||
4777  op == Token::kInit) {
4778  if (op == Token::kInit) {
4779  if (variable->HasHoleCheckUseInSameClosureScope()) {
4780  // After initializing a variable it won't be the hole anymore, so
4781  // elide subsequent checks.
4782  RememberHoleCheckInCurrentBlock(variable);
4783  }
4784  AddDisposableValue(mode);
4785  }
4786  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(destination);
4787  } else if (variable->throw_on_const_assignment(language_mode()) &&
4788  mode == VariableMode::kConst) {
4789  builder()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowConstAssignError);
4790  } else if (variable->throw_on_const_assignment(language_mode()) &&
4791  mode == VariableMode::kUsing) {
4792  builder()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowUsingAssignError);
4793  }
4794  break;
4795  }
4796  case VariableLocation::UNALLOCATED: {
4797  BuildStoreGlobal(variable);
4798  break;
4799  }
4800  case VariableLocation::CONTEXT: {
4801  int depth = execution_context()->ContextChainDepth(variable->scope());
4802  ContextScope* context = execution_context()->Previous(depth);
4803  Register context_reg;
4804 
4805  if (context) {
4806  context_reg = context->reg();
4807  depth = 0;
4808  } else {
4809  context_reg = execution_context()->reg();
4810  }
4811 
4812  if (VariableNeedsHoleCheckInCurrentBlockForAssignment(variable, op,
4813  hole_check_mode)) {
4814  // Load destination to check for hole.
4815  Register value_temp = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
4816  builder()
4817  ->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(value_temp)
4818  .LoadContextSlot(context_reg, variable, depth,
4819  BytecodeArrayBuilder::kMutableSlot);
4820 
4821  BuildHoleCheckForVariableAssignment(variable, op);
4822  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(value_temp);
4823  }
4824 
4825  if ((mode != VariableMode::kConst && mode != VariableMode::kUsing &&
4826  mode != VariableMode::kAwaitUsing) ||
4827  op == Token::kInit) {
4828  if (op == Token::kInit) {
4829  if (variable->HasHoleCheckUseInSameClosureScope()) {
4830  // After initializing a variable it won't be the hole anymore, so
4831  // elide subsequent checks.
4832  RememberHoleCheckInCurrentBlock(variable);
4833  }
4834  AddDisposableValue(mode);
4835  }
4836  builder()->StoreContextSlot(context_reg, variable, depth);
4837  } else if (variable->throw_on_const_assignment(language_mode())) {
4838  builder()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowConstAssignError);
4839  }
4840  break;
4841  }
4842  case VariableLocation::LOOKUP: {
4843  builder()->StoreLookupSlot(variable->raw_name(), language_mode(),
4844  lookup_hoisting_mode);
4845  break;
4846  }
4847  case VariableLocation::MODULE: {
4848  DCHECK(IsDeclaredVariableMode(mode));
4849 
4850  if (mode == VariableMode::kConst && op != Token::kInit) {
4851  builder()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowConstAssignError);
4852  break;
4853  }
4854 
4855  // If we don't throw above, we know that we're dealing with an
4856  // export because imports are const and we do not generate initializing
4857  // assignments for them.
4858  DCHECK(variable->IsExport());
4859 
4860  int depth = execution_context()->ContextChainDepth(variable->scope());
4861  if (VariableNeedsHoleCheckInCurrentBlockForAssignment(variable, op,
4862  hole_check_mode)) {
4863  Register value_temp = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
4864  builder()
4865  ->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(value_temp)
4866  .LoadModuleVariable(variable->index(), depth);
4867  BuildHoleCheckForVariableAssignment(variable, op);
4868  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(value_temp);
4869  }
4870  builder()->StoreModuleVariable(variable->index(), depth);
4871  break;
4872  }
4873  case VariableLocation::REPL_GLOBAL: {
4874  // A let or const declaration like 'let x = 7' is effectively translated
4875  // to:
4876  // <top of the script>:
4877  // ScriptContext.x = TheHole;
4878  // ...
4879  // <where the actual 'let' is>:
4880  // ScriptContextTable.x = 7; // no hole check
4881  //
4882  // The ScriptContext slot for 'x' that we store to here is not
4883  // necessarily the ScriptContext of this script, but rather the
4884  // first ScriptContext that has a slot for name 'x'.
4885  DCHECK(variable->IsReplGlobal());
4886  if (op == Token::kInit) {
4887  RegisterList store_args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
4888  builder()
4889  ->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(store_args[1])
4890  .LoadLiteral(variable->raw_name())
4891  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(store_args[0]);
4892  builder()->CallRuntime(
4893  Runtime::kStoreGlobalNoHoleCheckForReplLetOrConst, store_args);
4894  } else {
4895  if (mode == VariableMode::kConst) {
4896  builder()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowConstAssignError);
4897  } else {
4898  BuildStoreGlobal(variable);
4899  }
4900  }
4901  break;
4902  }
4903  }
4904 }
4905

4907  Register object,
4908  const AstRawString* name) {
4909  FeedbackSlot slot = GetCachedLoadICSlot(object_expr, name);
4910  builder()->LoadNamedProperty(object, name, feedback_index(slot));
4911 }

4920  }

4928  }

4931 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildStoreGlobal(Variable* variable) {

4936  }

4939  builder()->StoreGlobal(variable->raw_name(), feedback_index(slot));

4946 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildLoadKeyedProperty(Register object,
4947  FeedbackSlot slot) {
4948  if (v8_flags.enable_enumerated_keyed_access_bytecode &&
4949  current_for_in_scope() != nullptr) {
4950  Variable* key = GetPotentialVariableInAccumulator();
4951  if (key != nullptr) {
4952  ForInScope* scope = current_for_in_scope()->GetForInScope(key);
4953  if (scope != nullptr) {
4954  Register enum_index = scope->enum_index();
4955  Register cache_type = scope->cache_type();
4956  builder()->LoadEnumeratedKeyedProperty(object, enum_index, cache_type,
4957  feedback_index(slot));
4958  return;
4959  }
4960  }
4961  }
4962  builder()->LoadKeyedProperty(object, feedback_index(slot));
4963 }
