5015 
5016 BytecodeGenerator::AssignmentLhsData BytecodeGenerator::PrepareAssignmentLhs(
5017  Expression* lhs, AccumulatorPreservingMode accumulator_preserving_mode) {
5018  // Left-hand side can only be a property, a global or a variable slot.
5019  Property* property = lhs->AsProperty();
5020  AssignType assign_type = Property::GetAssignType(property);
5021 
5022  // Evaluate LHS expression.
5023  switch (assign_type) {
5024  case NON_PROPERTY:
5025  return AssignmentLhsData::NonProperty(lhs);
5026  case NAMED_PROPERTY: {
5027  AccumulatorPreservingScope scope(this, accumulator_preserving_mode);
5028  Register object = VisitForRegisterValue(property->obj());
5029  const AstRawString* name =
5030  property->key()->AsLiteral()->AsRawPropertyName();
5031  return AssignmentLhsData::NamedProperty(property->obj(), object, name);
5032  }
5033  case KEYED_PROPERTY: {
5034  AccumulatorPreservingScope scope(this, accumulator_preserving_mode);
5035  Register object = VisitForRegisterValue(property->obj());
5036  Register key = VisitForRegisterValue(property->key());
5037  return AssignmentLhsData::KeyedProperty(object, key);
5038  }
5039  case PRIVATE_METHOD:
5040  case PRIVATE_GETTER_ONLY:
5041  case PRIVATE_SETTER_ONLY:
5042  case PRIVATE_GETTER_AND_SETTER: {
5043  DCHECK(!property->IsSuperAccess());
5044  AccumulatorPreservingScope scope(this, accumulator_preserving_mode);
5045  Register object = VisitForRegisterValue(property->obj());
5046  Register key = VisitForRegisterValue(property->key());
5047  return AssignmentLhsData::PrivateMethodOrAccessor(assign_type, property,
5048  object, key);
5049  }
5050  case PRIVATE_DEBUG_DYNAMIC: {
5051  AccumulatorPreservingScope scope(this, accumulator_preserving_mode);
5052  Register object = VisitForRegisterValue(property->obj());
5053  // Do not visit the key here, instead we will look them up at run time.
5054  return AssignmentLhsData::PrivateDebugEvaluate(assign_type, property,
5055  object);
5056  }
5057  case NAMED_SUPER_PROPERTY: {
5058  AccumulatorPreservingScope scope(this, accumulator_preserving_mode);
5059  RegisterList super_property_args =
5060  register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(4);
5061  BuildThisVariableLoad();
5062  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(super_property_args[0]);
5063  BuildVariableLoad(
5064  property->obj()->AsSuperPropertyReference()->home_object()->var(),
5065  HoleCheckMode::kElided);
5066  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(super_property_args[1]);
5067  builder()
5068  ->LoadLiteral(property->key()->AsLiteral()->AsRawPropertyName())
5069  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(super_property_args[2]);
5070  return AssignmentLhsData::NamedSuperProperty(super_property_args);
5071  }
5072  case KEYED_SUPER_PROPERTY: {
5073  AccumulatorPreservingScope scope(this, accumulator_preserving_mode);
5074  RegisterList super_property_args =
5075  register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(4);
5076  BuildThisVariableLoad();
5077  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(super_property_args[0]);
5078  BuildVariableLoad(
5079  property->obj()->AsSuperPropertyReference()->home_object()->var(),
5080  HoleCheckMode::kElided);
5081  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(super_property_args[1]);
5082  VisitForRegisterValue(property->key(), super_property_args[2]);
5083  return AssignmentLhsData::KeyedSuperProperty(super_property_args);
5084  }
5085  }
5086  UNREACHABLE();
5087 }
5088 
5089 // Build the iteration finalizer called in the finally block of an iteration
5090 // protocol execution. This closes the iterator if needed, and suppresses any
5091 // exception it throws if necessary, including the exception when the return
5092 // method is not callable.
5093 //
5094 // In pseudo-code, this builds:
5095 //
5096 // if (!done) {
5097 // try {
5098 // let method = iterator.return
5099 // if (method !== null && method !== undefined) {
5100 // let return_val = method.call(iterator)
5101 // if (!%IsObject(return_val)) throw TypeError
5102 // }
5103 // } catch (e) {
5104 // if (iteration_continuation != RETHROW)
5105 // rethrow e
5106 // }
5107 // }
5108 //
5109 // For async iterators, iterator.close() becomes await iterator.close().
5110 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildFinalizeIteration(
5111  IteratorRecord iterator, Register done,
5112  Register iteration_continuation_token) {
5113  RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
5114  BytecodeLabels iterator_is_done(zone());
5115 
5116  // if (!done) {
5117  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(done).JumpIfTrue(
5118  ToBooleanMode::kConvertToBoolean, iterator_is_done.New());
5119 
5120  {
5121  RegisterAllocationScope inner_register_scope(this);
5122  BuildTryCatch(
5123  // try {
5124  // let method = iterator.return
5125  // if (method !== null && method !== undefined) {
5126  // let return_val = method.call(iterator)
5127  // if (!%IsObject(return_val)) throw TypeError
5128  // }
5129  // }
5130  [&]() {
5131  Register method = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
5132  builder()
5133  ->LoadNamedProperty(
5134  iterator.object(), ast_string_constants()->return_string(),
5135  feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddLoadICSlot()))
5136  .JumpIfUndefinedOrNull(iterator_is_done.New())
5137  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(method);
5138 
5139  RegisterList args(iterator.object());
5140  builder()->CallProperty(
5141  method, args, feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddCallICSlot()));
5142  if (iterator.type() == IteratorType::kAsync) {
5143  BuildAwait();
5144  }
5145  builder()->JumpIfJSReceiver(iterator_is_done.New());
5146  {
5147  // Throw this exception inside the try block so that it is
5148  // suppressed by the iteration continuation if necessary.
5149  RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
5150  Register return_result = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
5151  builder()
5152  ->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(return_result)
5153  .CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowIteratorResultNotAnObject,
5154  return_result);
5155  }
5156  },
5157 
5158  // catch (e) {
5159  // if (iteration_continuation != RETHROW)
5160  // rethrow e
5161  // }
5162  [&](Register context) {
5163  // Reuse context register to store the exception.
5164  Register close_exception = context;
5165  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(close_exception);
5166 
5167  BytecodeLabel suppress_close_exception;
5168  builder()
5169  ->LoadLiteral(Smi::FromInt(
5170  static_cast<int>(TryFinallyContinuationToken::kRethrowToken)))
5171  .CompareReference(iteration_continuation_token)
5172  .JumpIfTrue(ToBooleanMode::kAlreadyBoolean,
5173  &suppress_close_exception)
5174  .LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(close_exception)
5175  .ReThrow()
5176  .Bind(&suppress_close_exception);
5177  },
5178  catch_prediction());
5179  }
5180 
5181  iterator_is_done.Bind(builder());
5182 }
5183 
5184 // Get the default value of a destructuring target. Will mutate the
5185 // destructuring target expression if there is a default value.
5186 //
5187 // For
5188 // a = b
5189 // in
5190 // let {a = b} = c
5191 // returns b and mutates the input into a.
5192 Expression* BytecodeGenerator::GetDestructuringDefaultValue(
5193  Expression** target) {
5194  Expression* default_value = nullptr;
5195  if ((*target)->IsAssignment()) {
5196  Assignment* default_init = (*target)->AsAssignment();
5197  DCHECK_EQ(default_init->op(), Token::kAssign);
5198  default_value = default_init->value();
5199  *target = default_init->target();
5200  DCHECK((*target)->IsValidReferenceExpression() || (*target)->IsPattern());
5201  }
5202  return default_value;
5203 }
5204 
5205 // Convert a destructuring assignment to an array literal into a sequence of
5206 // iterator accesses into the value being assigned (in the accumulator).
5207 //
5208 // [a().x, ...b] = accumulator
5209 //
5210 // becomes
5211 //
5212 // iterator = %GetIterator(accumulator)
5213 // try {
5214 //
5215 // // Individual assignments read off the value from iterator.next() This gets
5216 // // repeated per destructuring element.
5217 // if (!done) {
5218 // // Make sure we are considered 'done' if .next(), .done or .value fail.
5219 // done = true
5220 // var next_result = iterator.next()
5221 // var tmp_done = next_result.done
5222 // if (!tmp_done) {
5223 // value = next_result.value
5224 // done = false
5225 // }
5226 // }
5227 // if (done)
5228 // value = undefined
5229 // a().x = value
5230 //
5231 // // A spread receives the remaining items in the iterator.
5232 // var array = []
5233 // var index = 0
5234 // %FillArrayWithIterator(iterator, array, index, done)
5235 // done = true
5236 // b = array
5237 //
5238 // } catch(e) {
5239 // iteration_continuation = RETHROW
5240 // } finally {
5241 // %FinalizeIteration(iterator, done, iteration_continuation)
5242 // }
5243 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildDestructuringArrayAssignment(
5244  ArrayLiteral* pattern, Token::Value op,
5245  LookupHoistingMode lookup_hoisting_mode) {
5246  RegisterAllocationScope scope(this);
5247 
5248  Register value = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
5249  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(value);
5250 
5251  // Store the iterator in a dedicated register so that it can be closed on
5252  // exit, and the 'done' value in a dedicated register so that it can be
5253  // changed and accessed independently of the iteration result.
5254  IteratorRecord iterator = BuildGetIteratorRecord(IteratorType::kNormal);
5255  Register done = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
5256  builder()->LoadFalse();
5257  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(done);
5258 
5259  BuildTryFinally(
5260  // Try block.
5261  [&]() {
5262  Register next_result = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
5263  FeedbackSlot next_value_load_slot = feedback_spec()->AddLoadICSlot();
5264  FeedbackSlot next_done_load_slot = feedback_spec()->AddLoadICSlot();
5265 
5266  Spread* spread = nullptr;
5267  for (Expression* target : *pattern->values()) {
5268  if (target->IsSpread()) {
5269  spread = target->AsSpread();
5270  break;
5271  }
5272 
5273  Expression* default_value = GetDestructuringDefaultValue(&target);
5274  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(target);
5275 
5276  AssignmentLhsData lhs_data = PrepareAssignmentLhs(target);
5277 
5278  // if (!done) {
5279  // // Make sure we are considered done if .next(), .done or .value
5280  // // fail.
5281  // done = true
5282  // var next_result = iterator.next()
5283  // var tmp_done = next_result.done
5284  // if (!tmp_done) {
5285  // value = next_result.value
5286  // done = false
5287  // }
5288  // }
5289  // if (done)
5290  // value = undefined
5291  BytecodeLabels is_done(zone());
5292 
5293  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(done);
5294  builder()->JumpIfTrue(ToBooleanMode::kConvertToBoolean,
5295  is_done.New());
5296 
5297  builder()->LoadTrue().StoreAccumulatorInRegister(done);
5298  BuildIteratorNext(iterator, next_result);
5299  builder()
5300  ->LoadNamedProperty(next_result,
5301  ast_string_constants()->done_string(),
5302  feedback_index(next_done_load_slot))
5303  .JumpIfTrue(ToBooleanMode::kConvertToBoolean, is_done.New());
5304 
5305  // Only do the assignment if this is not a hole (i.e. 'elided').
5306  if (!target->IsTheHoleLiteral()) {
5307  builder()
5308  ->LoadNamedProperty(next_result,
5309  ast_string_constants()->value_string(),
5310  feedback_index(next_value_load_slot))
5311  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(next_result)
5312  .LoadFalse()
5313  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(done)
5314  .LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(next_result);
5315 
5316  // [<pattern> = <init>] = <value>
5317  // becomes (roughly)
5318  // temp = <value>.next();
5319  // <pattern> = temp === undefined ? <init> : temp;
5320  BytecodeLabel do_assignment;
5321  if (default_value) {
5322  builder()->JumpIfNotUndefined(&do_assignment);
5323  // Since done == true => temp == undefined, jump directly to using
5324  // the default value for that case.
5325  is_done.Bind(builder());
5326  VisitInHoleCheckElisionScopeForAccumulatorValue(default_value);
5327  } else {
5328  builder()->Jump(&do_assignment);
5329  is_done.Bind(builder());
5330  builder()->LoadUndefined();
5331  }
5332  builder()->Bind(&do_assignment);
5333 
5334  BuildAssignment(lhs_data, op, lookup_hoisting_mode);
5335  } else {
5336  builder()->LoadFalse().StoreAccumulatorInRegister(done);
5337  DCHECK_EQ(lhs_data.assign_type(), NON_PROPERTY);
5338  is_done.Bind(builder());
5339  }
5340  }
5341 
5342  if (spread) {
5343  RegisterAllocationScope scope(this);
5344  BytecodeLabel is_done;
5345 
5346  // A spread is turned into a loop over the remainer of the iterator.
5347  Expression* target = spread->expression();
5348  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(spread);
5349 
5350  AssignmentLhsData lhs_data = PrepareAssignmentLhs(target);
5351 
5352  // var array = [];
5353  Register array = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
5354  builder()->CreateEmptyArrayLiteral(
5355  feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddLiteralSlot()));
5356  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(array);
5357 
5358  // If done, jump to assigning empty array
5359  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(done);
5360  builder()->JumpIfTrue(ToBooleanMode::kConvertToBoolean, &is_done);
5361 
5362  // var index = 0;
5363  Register index = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
5364  builder()->LoadLiteral(Smi::zero());
5365  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(index);
5366 
5367  // Set done to true, since it's guaranteed to be true by the time the
5368  // array fill completes.
5369  builder()->LoadTrue().StoreAccumulatorInRegister(done);
5370 
5371  // Fill the array with the iterator.
5372  FeedbackSlot element_slot =
5373  feedback_spec()->AddStoreInArrayLiteralICSlot();
5374  FeedbackSlot index_slot = feedback_spec()->AddBinaryOpICSlot();
5375  BuildFillArrayWithIterator(iterator, array, index, next_result,
5376  next_value_load_slot, next_done_load_slot,
5377  index_slot, element_slot);
5378 
5379  builder()->Bind(&is_done);
5380  // Assign the array to the LHS.
5381  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(array);
5382  BuildAssignment(lhs_data, op, lookup_hoisting_mode);
5383  }
5384  },
5385  // Finally block.
5386  [&](Register iteration_continuation_token,
5387  Register iteration_continuation_result, Register message) {
5388  // Finish the iteration in the finally block.
5389  BuildFinalizeIteration(iterator, done, iteration_continuation_token);
5390  },
5391  HandlerTable::UNCAUGHT);
5392 
5393  if (!execution_result()->IsEffect()) {
5394  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(value);
5395  }
5396 }
5397 
5398 // Convert a destructuring assignment to an object literal into a sequence of
5399 // property accesses into the value being assigned (in the accumulator).
5400 //
5401 // { y, [x++]: a(), ...b.c } = value
5402 //
5403 // becomes
5404 //
5405 // var rest_runtime_callargs = new Array(3);
5406 // rest_runtime_callargs[0] = value;
5407 //
5408 // rest_runtime_callargs[1] = "y";
5409 // y = value.y;
5410 //
5411 // var temp1 = %ToName(x++);
5412 // rest_runtime_callargs[2] = temp1;
5413 // a() = value[temp1];
5414 //
5415 // b.c =
5416 // %CopyDataPropertiesWithExcludedPropertiesOnStack.call(rest_runtime_callargs);
5417 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildDestructuringObjectAssignment(
5418  ObjectLiteral* pattern, Token::Value op,
5419  LookupHoistingMode lookup_hoisting_mode) {
5420  RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
5421 
5422  // Store the assignment value in a register.
5423  Register value;
5424  RegisterList rest_runtime_callargs;
5425  if (pattern->builder()->has_rest_property()) {
5426  rest_runtime_callargs =
5427  register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(pattern->properties()->length());
5428  value = rest_runtime_callargs[0];
5429  } else {
5430  value = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
5431  }
5432  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(value);
5433 
5434  // if (value === null || value === undefined)
5435  // throw new TypeError(kNonCoercible);
5436  //
5437  // Since the first property access on null/undefined will also trigger a
5438  // TypeError, we can elide this check. The exception is when there are no
5439  // properties and no rest property (this is an empty literal), or when the
5440  // first property is a computed name and accessing it can have side effects.
5441  //
5442  // TODO(leszeks): Also eliminate this check if the value is known to be
5443  // non-null (e.g. an object literal).
5444  if (pattern->properties()->is_empty() ||
5445  (pattern->properties()->at(0)->is_computed_name() &&
5446  pattern->properties()->at(0)->kind() != ObjectLiteralProperty::SPREAD)) {
5447  BytecodeLabel is_null_or_undefined, not_null_or_undefined;
5448  builder()
5449  ->JumpIfUndefinedOrNull(&is_null_or_undefined)
5450  .Jump(&not_null_or_undefined);
5451 
5452  {
5453  builder()->Bind(&is_null_or_undefined);
5454  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(pattern);
5455  builder()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowPatternAssignmentNonCoercible,
5456  value);
5457  }
5458  builder()->Bind(&not_null_or_undefined);
5459  }
5460 
5461  int i = 0;
5462  for (ObjectLiteralProperty* pattern_property : *pattern->properties()) {
5463  RegisterAllocationScope inner_register_scope(this);
5464 
5465  // The key of the pattern becomes the key into the RHS value, and the value
5466  // of the pattern becomes the target of the assignment.
5467  //
5468  // e.g. { a: b } = o becomes b = o.a
5469  Expression* pattern_key = pattern_property->key();
5470  Expression* target = pattern_property->value();
5471  Expression* default_value = GetDestructuringDefaultValue(&target);
5472  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(target);
5473 
5474  // Calculate this property's key into the assignment RHS value, additionally
5475  // storing the key for rest_runtime_callargs if needed.
5476  //
5477  // The RHS is accessed using the key either by LoadNamedProperty (if
5478  // value_name is valid) or by LoadKeyedProperty (otherwise).
5479  const AstRawString* value_name = nullptr;
5480  Register value_key;
5481 
5482  if (pattern_property->kind() != ObjectLiteralProperty::Kind::SPREAD) {
5483  if (pattern_key->IsPropertyName()) {
5484  value_name = pattern_key->AsLiteral()->AsRawPropertyName();
5485  }
5486  if (pattern->builder()->has_rest_property() || !value_name) {
5487  if (pattern->builder()->has_rest_property()) {
5488  value_key = rest_runtime_callargs[i + 1];
5489  } else {
5490  value_key = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
5491  }
5492  if (pattern_property->is_computed_name()) {
5493  // { [a()]: b().x } = c
5494  // becomes
5495  // var tmp = a()
5496  // b().x = c[tmp]
5497  DCHECK(!pattern_key->IsPropertyName() ||
5498  !pattern_key->IsNumberLiteral());
5499  VisitForAccumulatorValue(pattern_key);
5500  builder()->ToName().StoreAccumulatorInRegister(value_key);
5501  } else {
5502  // We only need the key for non-computed properties when it is numeric
5503  // or is being saved for the rest_runtime_callargs.
5504  DCHECK(pattern_key->IsNumberLiteral() ||
5505  (pattern->builder()->has_rest_property() &&
5506  pattern_key->IsPropertyName()));
5507  VisitForRegisterValue(pattern_key, value_key);
5508  }
5509  }
5510  }
5511 
5512  AssignmentLhsData lhs_data = PrepareAssignmentLhs(target);
5513 
5514  // Get the value from the RHS.
5515  if (pattern_property->kind() == ObjectLiteralProperty::Kind::SPREAD) {
5516  DCHECK_EQ(i, pattern->properties()->length() - 1);
5517  DCHECK(!value_key.is_valid());
5518  DCHECK_NULL(value_name);
5519  builder()->CallRuntime(
5520  Runtime::kInlineCopyDataPropertiesWithExcludedPropertiesOnStack,
5521  rest_runtime_callargs);
5522  } else if (value_name) {
5523  builder()->LoadNamedProperty(
5524  value, value_name, feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddLoadICSlot()));
5525  } else {
5526  DCHECK(value_key.is_valid());
5527  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(value_key).LoadKeyedProperty(
5528  value, feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddKeyedLoadICSlot()));
5529  }
5530 
5531  // {<pattern> = <init>} = <value>
5532  // becomes
5533  // temp = <value>;
5534  // <pattern> = temp === undefined ? <init> : temp;
5535  if (default_value) {
5536  BytecodeLabel value_not_undefined;
5537  builder()->JumpIfNotUndefined(&value_not_undefined);
5538  VisitInHoleCheckElisionScopeForAccumulatorValue(default_value);
5539  builder()->Bind(&value_not_undefined);
5540  }
5541 
5542  BuildAssignment(lhs_data, op, lookup_hoisting_mode);
5543 
5544  i++;
5545  }
5546 
5547  if (!execution_result()->IsEffect()) {
5548  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(value);
5549  }
5550 }
5551 
5552 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildAssignment(
5553  const AssignmentLhsData& lhs_data, Token::Value op,
5554  LookupHoistingMode lookup_hoisting_mode) {
5555  // Assign the value to the LHS.
5556  switch (lhs_data.assign_type()) {
5557  case NON_PROPERTY: {
5558  if (ObjectLiteral* pattern_as_object =
5559  lhs_data.expr()->AsObjectLiteral()) {
5560  // Split object literals into destructuring.
5561  BuildDestructuringObjectAssignment(pattern_as_object, op,
5562  lookup_hoisting_mode);
5563  } else if (ArrayLiteral* pattern_as_array =
5564  lhs_data.expr()->AsArrayLiteral()) {
5565  // Split object literals into destructuring.
5566  BuildDestructuringArrayAssignment(pattern_as_array, op,
5567  lookup_hoisting_mode);
5568  } else {
5569  DCHECK(lhs_data.expr()->IsVariableProxy());
5570  VariableProxy* proxy = lhs_data.expr()->AsVariableProxy();
5571  BuildVariableAssignment(proxy->var(), op, proxy->hole_check_mode(),
5572  lookup_hoisting_mode);
5573  }
5574  break;
5575  }
5576  case NAMED_PROPERTY: {
5577  BuildSetNamedProperty(lhs_data.object_expr(), lhs_data.object(),
5578  lhs_data.name());
5579  break;
5580  }
5581  case KEYED_PROPERTY: {
5582  FeedbackSlot slot = feedback_spec()->AddKeyedStoreICSlot(language_mode());
5583  Register value;
5584  if (!execution_result()->IsEffect()) {
5585  value = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
5586  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(value);
5587  }
5588  builder()->SetKeyedProperty(lhs_data.object(), lhs_data.key(),
5589  feedback_index(slot), language_mode());
5590  if (!execution_result()->IsEffect()) {
5591  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(value);
5592  }
5593  break;
5594  }
5595  case NAMED_SUPER_PROPERTY: {
5596  builder()
5597  ->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(lhs_data.super_property_args()[3])
5598  .CallRuntime(Runtime::kStoreToSuper, lhs_data.super_property_args());
5599  break;
5600  }
5601  case KEYED_SUPER_PROPERTY: {
5602  builder()
5603  ->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(lhs_data.super_property_args()[3])
5604  .CallRuntime(Runtime::kStoreKeyedToSuper,
5605  lhs_data.super_property_args());
5606  break;
5607  }
5608  case PRIVATE_METHOD: {
5609  Property* property = lhs_data.expr()->AsProperty();
5610  BuildPrivateBrandCheck(property, lhs_data.object());
5611  BuildInvalidPropertyAccess(MessageTemplate::kInvalidPrivateMethodWrite,
5612  lhs_data.expr()->AsProperty());
5613  break;
5614  }
5615  case PRIVATE_GETTER_ONLY: {
5616  Property* property = lhs_data.expr()->AsProperty();
5617  BuildPrivateBrandCheck(property, lhs_data.object());
5618  BuildInvalidPropertyAccess(MessageTemplate::kInvalidPrivateSetterAccess,
5619  lhs_data.expr()->AsProperty());
5620  break;
5621  }
5622  case PRIVATE_SETTER_ONLY:
5623  case PRIVATE_GETTER_AND_SETTER: {
5624  Register value = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
5625  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(value);
5626  Property* property = lhs_data.expr()->AsProperty();
5627  BuildPrivateBrandCheck(property, lhs_data.object());
5628  BuildPrivateSetterAccess(lhs_data.object(), lhs_data.key(), value);
5629  if (!execution_result()->IsEffect()) {
5630  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(value);
5631  }
5632  break;
5633  }
5634  case PRIVATE_DEBUG_DYNAMIC: {
5635  Register value = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
5636  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(value);
5637  Property* property = lhs_data.expr()->AsProperty();
5638  BuildPrivateDebugDynamicSet(property, lhs_data.object(), value);
5639  if (!execution_result()->IsEffect()) {
5640  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(value);
5641  }
5642  break;
5643  }
5644  }
5645 }
5646 
5647 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitAssignment(Assignment* expr) {
5648  AssignmentLhsData lhs_data = PrepareAssignmentLhs(expr->target());
5649 
5650  VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->value());
5651 
5652  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr);
5653  BuildAssignment(lhs_data, expr->op(), expr->lookup_hoisting_mode());
5654 }
5655 
5656 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitCompoundAssignment(CompoundAssignment* expr) {
5657  AssignmentLhsData lhs_data = PrepareAssignmentLhs(expr->target());
5658 
5659  // Evaluate the value and potentially handle compound assignments by loading
5660  // the left-hand side value and performing a binary operation.
5661  switch (lhs_data.assign_type()) {
5662  case NON_PROPERTY: {
5663  VariableProxy* proxy = expr->target()->AsVariableProxy();
5664  BuildVariableLoad(proxy->var(), proxy->hole_check_mode());
5665  break;
5666  }
5667  case NAMED_PROPERTY: {
5668  BuildLoadNamedProperty(lhs_data.object_expr(), lhs_data.object(),
5669  lhs_data.name());
5670  break;
5671  }
5672  case KEYED_PROPERTY: {
5673  FeedbackSlot slot = feedback_spec()->AddKeyedLoadICSlot();
5674  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(lhs_data.key());
5675  BuildLoadKeyedProperty(lhs_data.object(), slot);
5676  break;
5677  }
5678  case NAMED_SUPER_PROPERTY: {
5679  builder()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kLoadFromSuper,
5680  lhs_data.super_property_args().Truncate(3));
5681  break;
5682  }
5683  case KEYED_SUPER_PROPERTY: {
5684  builder()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kLoadKeyedFromSuper,
5685  lhs_data.super_property_args().Truncate(3));
5686  break;
5687  }
5688  // BuildAssignment() will throw an error about the private method being
5689  // read-only.
5690  case PRIVATE_METHOD: {
5691  Property* property = lhs_data.expr()->AsProperty();
5692  BuildPrivateBrandCheck(property, lhs_data.object());
5693  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(lhs_data.key());
5694  break;
5695  }
5696  // For read-only properties, BuildAssignment() will throw an error about
5697  // the missing setter.
5698  case PRIVATE_GETTER_ONLY:
5699  case PRIVATE_GETTER_AND_SETTER: {
5700  Property* property = lhs_data.expr()->AsProperty();
5701  BuildPrivateBrandCheck(property, lhs_data.object());
5702  BuildPrivateGetterAccess(lhs_data.object(), lhs_data.key());
5703  break;
5704  }
5705  case PRIVATE_SETTER_ONLY: {
5706  // The property access is invalid, but if the brand check fails too, we
5707  // need to return the error from the brand check.
5708  Property* property = lhs_data.expr()->AsProperty();
5709  BuildPrivateBrandCheck(property, lhs_data.object());
5710  BuildInvalidPropertyAccess(MessageTemplate::kInvalidPrivateGetterAccess,
5711  lhs_data.expr()->AsProperty());
5712  break;
5713  }
5714  case PRIVATE_DEBUG_DYNAMIC: {
5715  Property* property = lhs_data.expr()->AsProperty();
5716  BuildPrivateDebugDynamicGet(property, lhs_data.object());
5717  break;
5718  }
5719  }
5720 
5721  BinaryOperation* binop = expr->binary_operation();
5722  FeedbackSlot slot = feedback_spec()->AddBinaryOpICSlot();
5723  BytecodeLabel short_circuit;
5724  if (binop->op() == Token::kNullish) {
5725  BytecodeLabel nullish;
5726  builder()
5727  ->JumpIfUndefinedOrNull(&nullish)
5728  .Jump(&short_circuit)
5729  .Bind(&nullish);
5730  VisitInHoleCheckElisionScopeForAccumulatorValue(expr->value());
5731  } else if (binop->op() == Token::kOr) {
5732  builder()->JumpIfTrue(ToBooleanMode::kConvertToBoolean, &short_circuit);
5733  VisitInHoleCheckElisionScopeForAccumulatorValue(expr->value());
5734  } else if (binop->op() == Token::kAnd) {
5735  builder()->JumpIfFalse(ToBooleanMode::kConvertToBoolean, &short_circuit);
5736  VisitInHoleCheckElisionScopeForAccumulatorValue(expr->value());
5737  } else if (expr->value()->IsSmiLiteral()) {
5738  builder()->BinaryOperationSmiLiteral(
5739  binop->op(), expr->value()->AsLiteral()->AsSmiLiteral(),
5740  feedback_index(slot));
5741  } else {
5742  Register old_value = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
5743  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(old_value);
5744  VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->value());
5745  builder()->BinaryOperation(binop->op(), old_value, feedback_index(slot));
5746  }
5747  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr);
5748 
5749  BuildAssignment(lhs_data, expr->op(), expr->lookup_hoisting_mode());
5750  builder()->Bind(&short_circuit);
5751 }
5752 
5753 // Suspends the generator to resume at the next suspend_id, with output stored
5754 // in the accumulator. When the generator is resumed, the sent value is loaded
5755 // in the accumulator.
5756 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildSuspendPoint(int position) {
5757  // Because we eliminate jump targets in dead code, we also eliminate resumes
5758  // when the suspend is not emitted because otherwise the below call to Bind
5759  // would start a new basic block and the code would be considered alive.
5760  if (builder()->RemainderOfBlockIsDead()) {
5761  return;
5762  }
5763  const int suspend_id = suspend_count_++;
5764 
5765  RegisterList registers = register_allocator()->AllLiveRegisters();
5766 
5767  // Save context, registers, and state. This bytecode then returns the value
5768  // in the accumulator.
5769  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(position);
5770  builder()->SuspendGenerator(generator_object(), registers, suspend_id);
5771 
5772  // Upon resume, we continue here.
5773  builder()->Bind(generator_jump_table_, suspend_id);
5774 
5775  // Clobbers all registers and sets the accumulator to the
5776  // [[input_or_debug_pos]] slot of the generator object.
5777  builder()->ResumeGenerator(generator_object(), registers);
5778 }
5779 
5780 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitYield(Yield* expr) {
5781  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr);
5782  VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->expression());
5783 
5784  bool is_async = IsAsyncGeneratorFunction(function_kind());
5785  // If this is not the first yield
5786  if (suspend_count_ > 0) {
5787  if (is_async) {
5788  // AsyncGenerator yields (with the exception of the initial yield)
5789  // delegate work to the AsyncGeneratorYieldWithAwait stub, which Awaits
5790  // the operand and on success, wraps the value in an IteratorResult.
5791  //
5792  // In the spec the Await is a separate operation, but they are combined
5793  // here to reduce bytecode size.
5794  RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
5795  RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
5796  builder()
5797  ->MoveRegister(generator_object(), args[0]) // generator
5798  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[1]) // value
5799  .CallRuntime(Runtime::kInlineAsyncGeneratorYieldWithAwait, args);
5800  } else {
5801  // Generator yields (with the exception of the initial yield) wrap the
5802  // value into IteratorResult.
5803  RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
5804  RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
5805  builder()
5806  ->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[0]) // value
5807  .LoadFalse()
5808  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[1]) // done
5809  .CallRuntime(Runtime::kInlineCreateIterResultObject, args);
5810  }
5811  }
5812 
5813  BuildSuspendPoint(expr->position());
5814  // At this point, the generator has been resumed, with the received value in
5815  // the accumulator.
5816 
5817  // TODO(caitp): remove once yield* desugaring for async generators is handled
5818  // in BytecodeGenerator.
5819  if (expr->on_abrupt_resume() == Yield::kNoControl) {
5820  DCHECK(is_async);
5821  return;
5822  }
5823 
5824  Register input = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
5825  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(input).CallRuntime(
5826  Runtime::kInlineGeneratorGetResumeMode, generator_object());
5827 
5828  // Now dispatch on resume mode.
5829  static_assert(JSGeneratorObject::kNext + 1 == JSGeneratorObject::kReturn);
5830  static_assert(JSGeneratorObject::kReturn + 1 == JSGeneratorObject::kThrow);
5831  BytecodeJumpTable* jump_table =
5832  builder()->AllocateJumpTable(is_async ? 3 : 2, JSGeneratorObject::kNext);
5833 
5834  builder()->SwitchOnSmiNoFeedback(jump_table);
5835 
5836  if (is_async) {
5837  // Resume with rethrow (switch fallthrough).
5838  // This case is only necessary in async generators.
5839  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr);
5840  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(input);
5841  builder()->ReThrow();
5842 
5843  // Add label for kThrow (next case).
5844  builder()->Bind(jump_table, JSGeneratorObject::kThrow);
5845  }
5846 
5847  {
5848  // Resume with throw (switch fallthrough in sync case).
5849  // TODO(leszeks): Add a debug-only check that the accumulator is
5850  // JSGeneratorObject::kThrow.
5851  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr);
5852  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(input);
5853  builder()->Throw();
5854  }
5855 
5856  {
5857  // Resume with return.
5858  builder()->Bind(jump_table, JSGeneratorObject::kReturn);
5859  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(input);
5860  if (is_async) {
5861  execution_control()->AsyncReturnAccumulator(kNoSourcePosition);
5862  } else {
5863  execution_control()->ReturnAccumulator(kNoSourcePosition);
5864  }
5865  }
5866 
5867  {
5868  // Resume with next.
5869  builder()->Bind(jump_table, JSGeneratorObject::kNext);
5870  BuildIncrementBlockCoverageCounterIfEnabled(expr,
5871  SourceRangeKind::kContinuation);
5872  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(input);
5873  }
5874 }
5875 
5876 // Desugaring of (yield* iterable)
5877 //
5878 // do {
5879 // const kNext = 0;
5880 // const kReturn = 1;
5881 // const kThrow = 2;
5882 //
5883 // let output; // uninitialized
5884 //
5885 // let iteratorRecord = GetIterator(iterable);
5886 // let iterator = iteratorRecord.[[Iterator]];
5887 // let next = iteratorRecord.[[NextMethod]];
5888 // let input = undefined;
5889 // let resumeMode = kNext;
5890 //
5891 // while (true) {
5892 // // From the generator to the iterator:
5893 // // Forward input according to resumeMode and obtain output.
5894 // switch (resumeMode) {
5895 // case kNext:
5896 // output = next.[[Call]](iterator, );;
5897 // break;
5898 // case kReturn:
5899 // let iteratorReturn = iterator.return;
5900 // if (IS_NULL_OR_UNDEFINED(iteratorReturn)) {
5901 // if (IS_ASYNC_GENERATOR) input = await input;
5902 // return input;
5903 // }
5904 // output = iteratorReturn.[[Call]](iterator, input);
5905 // break;
5906 // case kThrow:
5907 // let iteratorThrow = iterator.throw;
5908 // if (IS_NULL_OR_UNDEFINED(iteratorThrow)) {
5909 // let iteratorReturn = iterator.return;
5910 // if (!IS_NULL_OR_UNDEFINED(iteratorReturn)) {
5911 // output = iteratorReturn.[[Call]](iterator, );
5912 // if (IS_ASYNC_GENERATOR) output = await output;
5913 // if (!IS_RECEIVER(output)) %ThrowIterResultNotAnObject(output);
5914 // }
5915 // throw MakeTypeError(kThrowMethodMissing);
5916 // }
5917 // output = iteratorThrow.[[Call]](iterator, input);
5918 // break;
5919 // }
5920 //
5921 // if (IS_ASYNC_GENERATOR) output = await output;
5922 // if (!IS_RECEIVER(output)) %ThrowIterResultNotAnObject(output);
5923 // if (output.done) break;
5924 //
5925 // // From the generator to its user:
5926 // // Forward output, receive new input, and determine resume mode.
5927 // if (IS_ASYNC_GENERATOR) {
5928 // // Resolve the promise for the current AsyncGeneratorRequest.
5929 // %_AsyncGeneratorResolve(output.value, /* done = */ false)
5930 // }
5931 // input = Suspend(output);
5932 // resumeMode = %GeneratorGetResumeMode();
5933 // }
5934 //
5935 // if (resumeMode === kReturn) {
5936 // return output.value;
5937 // }
5938 // output.value
5939 // }
5940 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitYieldStar(YieldStar* expr) {
5941  Register output = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
5942  Register resume_mode = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
5943  IteratorType iterator_type = IsAsyncGeneratorFunction(function_kind())
5944  ? IteratorType::kAsync
5945  : IteratorType::kNormal;
5946 
5947  {
5948  RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
5949  RegisterList iterator_and_input = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
5950  VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->expression());
5951  IteratorRecord iterator = BuildGetIteratorRecord(
5952  register_allocator()->NewRegister() /* next method */,
5953  iterator_and_input[0], iterator_type);
5954 
5955  Register input = iterator_and_input[1];
5956  builder()->LoadUndefined().StoreAccumulatorInRegister(input);
5957  builder()
5958  ->LoadLiteral(Smi::FromInt(JSGeneratorObject::kNext))
5959  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(resume_mode);
5960 
5961  {
5962  // This loop builder does not construct counters as the loop is not
5963  // visible to the user, and we therefore neither pass the block coverage
5964  // builder nor the expression.
5965  //
5966  // In addition to the normal suspend for yield*, a yield* in an async
5967  // generator has 2 additional suspends:
5968  // - One for awaiting the iterator result of closing the generator when
5969  // resumed with a "throw" completion, and a throw method is not
5970  // present on the delegated iterator
5971  // - One for awaiting the iterator result yielded by the delegated
5972  // iterator
5973 
5974  LoopBuilder loop_builder(builder(), nullptr, nullptr, feedback_spec());
5975  LoopScope loop_scope(this, &loop_builder);
5976 
5977  {
5978  BytecodeLabels after_switch(zone());
5979  BytecodeJumpTable* switch_jump_table =
5980  builder()->AllocateJumpTable(2, 1);
5981 
5982  builder()
5983  ->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(resume_mode)
5984  .SwitchOnSmiNoFeedback(switch_jump_table);
5985 
5986  // Fallthrough to default case.
5987  // TODO(ignition): Add debug code to check that {resume_mode} really is
5988  // {JSGeneratorObject::kNext} in this case.
5989  static_assert(JSGeneratorObject::kNext == 0);
5990  {
5991  FeedbackSlot slot = feedback_spec()->AddCallICSlot();
5992  builder()->CallProperty(iterator.next(), iterator_and_input,
5993  feedback_index(slot));
5994  builder()->Jump(after_switch.New());
5995  }
5996 
5997  static_assert(JSGeneratorObject::kReturn == 1);
5998  builder()->Bind(switch_jump_table, JSGeneratorObject::kReturn);
5999  {
6000  const AstRawString* return_string =
6001  ast_string_constants()->return_string();
6002  BytecodeLabels no_return_method(zone());
6003 
6004  BuildCallIteratorMethod(iterator.object(), return_string,
6005  iterator_and_input, after_switch.New(),
6006  &no_return_method);
6007  no_return_method.Bind(builder());
6008  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(input);
6009  if (iterator_type == IteratorType::kAsync) {
6010  // Await input.
6011  BuildAwait(expr->position());
6012  execution_control()->AsyncReturnAccumulator(kNoSourcePosition);
6013  } else {
6014  execution_control()->ReturnAccumulator(kNoSourcePosition);
6015  }
6016  }
6017 
6018  static_assert(JSGeneratorObject::kThrow == 2);
6019  builder()->Bind(switch_jump_table, JSGeneratorObject::kThrow);
6020  {
6021  const AstRawString* throw_string =
6022  ast_string_constants()->throw_string();
6023  BytecodeLabels no_throw_method(zone());
6024  BuildCallIteratorMethod(iterator.object(), throw_string,
6025  iterator_and_input, after_switch.New(),
6026  &no_throw_method);
6027 
6028  // If there is no "throw" method, perform IteratorClose, and finally
6029  // throw a TypeError.
6030  no_throw_method.Bind(builder());
6031  BuildIteratorClose(iterator, expr);
6032  builder()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowThrowMethodMissing);
6033  }
6034 
6035  after_switch.Bind(builder());
6036  }
6037 
6038  if (iterator_type == IteratorType::kAsync) {
6039  // Await the result of the method invocation.
6040  BuildAwait(expr->position());
6041  }
6042 
6043  // Check that output is an object.
6044  BytecodeLabel check_if_done;
6045  builder()
6046  ->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(output)
6047  .JumpIfJSReceiver(&check_if_done)
6048  .CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowIteratorResultNotAnObject, output);
6049 
6050  builder()->Bind(&check_if_done);
6051  // Break once output.done is true.
6052  builder()->LoadNamedProperty(
6053  output, ast_string_constants()->done_string(),
6054  feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddLoadICSlot()));
6055 
6056  loop_builder.BreakIfTrue(ToBooleanMode::kConvertToBoolean);
6057 
6058  // Suspend the current generator.
6059  if (iterator_type == IteratorType::kNormal) {
6060  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(output);
6061  } else {
6062  RegisterAllocationScope inner_register_scope(this);
6063  DCHECK_EQ(iterator_type, IteratorType::kAsync);
6064  // If generatorKind is async, perform
6065  // AsyncGeneratorResolve(output.value, /* done = */ false), which will
6066  // resolve the current AsyncGeneratorRequest's promise with
6067  // output.value.
6068  builder()->LoadNamedProperty(
6069  output, ast_string_constants()->value_string(),
6070  feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddLoadICSlot()));
6071 
6072  RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(3);
6073  builder()
6074  ->MoveRegister(generator_object(), args[0]) // generator
6075  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[1]) // value
6076  .LoadFalse()
6077  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[2]) // done
6078  .CallRuntime(Runtime::kInlineAsyncGeneratorResolve, args);
6079  }
6080 
6081  BuildSuspendPoint(expr->position());
6082  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(input);
6083  builder()
6084  ->CallRuntime(Runtime::kInlineGeneratorGetResumeMode,
6085  generator_object())
6086  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(resume_mode);
6087 
6088  loop_builder.BindContinueTarget();
6089  }
6090  }
6091 
6092  // Decide if we trigger a return or if the yield* expression should just
6093  // produce a value.
6094  BytecodeLabel completion_is_output_value;
6095  Register output_value = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
6096  builder()
6097  ->LoadNamedProperty(output, ast_string_constants()->value_string(),
6098  feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddLoadICSlot()))
6099  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(output_value)
6100  .LoadLiteral(Smi::FromInt(JSGeneratorObject::kReturn))
6101  .CompareReference(resume_mode)
6102  .JumpIfFalse(ToBooleanMode::kAlreadyBoolean, &completion_is_output_value)
6103  .LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(output_value);
6104  if (iterator_type == IteratorType::kAsync) {
6105  execution_control()->AsyncReturnAccumulator(kNoSourcePosition);
6106  } else {
6107  execution_control()->ReturnAccumulator(kNoSourcePosition);
6108  }
6109 
6110  builder()->Bind(&completion_is_output_value);
6111  BuildIncrementBlockCoverageCounterIfEnabled(expr,
6112  SourceRangeKind::kContinuation);
6113  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(output_value);
6114 }
6115 
6116 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildAwait(int position) {
6117  // Rather than HandlerTable::UNCAUGHT, async functions use
6118  // HandlerTable::ASYNC_AWAIT to communicate that top-level exceptions are
6119  // transformed into promise rejections. This is necessary to prevent emitting
6120  // multiple debug events for the same uncaught exception. There is no point
6121  // in the body of an async function where catch prediction is
6122  // HandlerTable::UNCAUGHT.
6123  DCHECK(catch_prediction() != HandlerTable::UNCAUGHT ||
6124  info()->scope()->is_repl_mode_scope());
6125 
6126  {
6127  // Await(operand) and suspend.
6128  RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
6129 
6130  Runtime::FunctionId await_intrinsic_id;
6131  if (IsAsyncGeneratorFunction(function_kind())) {
6132  await_intrinsic_id = Runtime::kInlineAsyncGeneratorAwait;
6133  } else {
6134  await_intrinsic_id = Runtime::kInlineAsyncFunctionAwait;
6135  }
6136  RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
6137  builder()
6138  ->MoveRegister(generator_object(), args[0])
6139  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[1])
6140  .CallRuntime(await_intrinsic_id, args);
6141  }
6142 
6143  BuildSuspendPoint(position);
6144 
6145  Register input = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
6146  Register resume_mode = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
6147 
6148  // Now dispatch on resume mode.
6149  BytecodeLabel resume_next;
6150  builder()
6151  ->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(input)
6152  .CallRuntime(Runtime::kInlineGeneratorGetResumeMode, generator_object())
6153  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(resume_mode)
6154  .LoadLiteral(Smi::FromInt(JSGeneratorObject::kNext))
6155  .CompareReference(resume_mode)
6156  .JumpIfTrue(ToBooleanMode::kAlreadyBoolean, &resume_next);
6157 
6158  // Resume with "throw" completion (rethrow the received value).
6159  // TODO(leszeks): Add a debug-only check that the accumulator is
6160  // JSGeneratorObject::kThrow.
6161  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(input).ReThrow();
6162 
6163  // Resume with next.
6164  builder()->Bind(&resume_next);
6165  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(input);
6166 }
6167 
6168 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitAwait(Await* expr) {
6169  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr);
6170  VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->expression());
6171  BuildAwait(expr->position());
6172  BuildIncrementBlockCoverageCounterIfEnabled(expr,
6173  SourceRangeKind::kContinuation);
6174 }
6175 
6176 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitThrow(Throw* expr) {
6177  AllocateBlockCoverageSlotIfEnabled(expr, SourceRangeKind::kContinuation);
6178  VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->exception());
6179  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr);
6180  builder()->Throw();
6181 }
6182 
6183 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitPropertyLoad(Register obj, Property* property) {
6184  if (property->is_optional_chain_link()) {
6185  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(optional_chaining_null_labels_);
6186  int right_range =
6187  AllocateBlockCoverageSlotIfEnabled(property, SourceRangeKind::kRight);
6188  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(obj).JumpIfUndefinedOrNull(
6189  optional_chaining_null_labels_->New());
6190  BuildIncrementBlockCoverageCounterIfEnabled(right_range);
6191  }
6192 
6193  AssignType property_kind = Property::GetAssignType(property);
6194 
6195  switch (property_kind) {
6196  case NON_PROPERTY:
6197  UNREACHABLE();
6198  case NAMED_PROPERTY: {
6199  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(property);
6200  const AstRawString* name =
6201  property->key()->AsLiteral()->AsRawPropertyName();
6202  BuildLoadNamedProperty(property->obj(), obj, name);
6203  break;
6204  }
6205  case KEYED_PROPERTY: {
6206  VisitForAccumulatorValueAsPropertyKey(property->key());
6207  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(property);
6208  BuildLoadKeyedProperty(obj, feedback_spec()->AddKeyedLoadICSlot());
6209  break;
6210  }
6211  case NAMED_SUPER_PROPERTY:
6212  VisitNamedSuperPropertyLoad(property, Register::invalid_value());
6213  break;
6214  case KEYED_SUPER_PROPERTY:
6215  VisitKeyedSuperPropertyLoad(property, Register::invalid_value());
6216  break;
6217  case PRIVATE_SETTER_ONLY: {
6218  BuildPrivateBrandCheck(property, obj);
6219  BuildInvalidPropertyAccess(MessageTemplate::kInvalidPrivateGetterAccess,
6220  property);
6221  break;
6222  }
6223  case PRIVATE_GETTER_ONLY:
6224  case PRIVATE_GETTER_AND_SETTER: {
6225  Register key = VisitForRegisterValue(property->key());
6226  BuildPrivateBrandCheck(property, obj);
6227  BuildPrivateGetterAccess(obj, key);
6228  break;
6229  }
6230  case PRIVATE_METHOD: {
6231  BuildPrivateBrandCheck(property, obj);
6232  // In the case of private methods, property->key() is the function to be
6233  // loaded (stored in a context slot), so load this directly.
6234  VisitForAccumulatorValue(property->key());
6235  break;
6236  }
6237  case PRIVATE_DEBUG_DYNAMIC: {
6238  BuildPrivateDebugDynamicGet(property, obj);
6239  break;
6240  }
6241  }
6242 }
6243 
6244 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildPrivateDebugDynamicGet(Property* property,
6245  Register obj) {
6246  RegisterAllocationScope scope(this);
6247  RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
6248 
6249  Variable* private_name = property->key()->AsVariableProxy()->var();
6250  builder()
6251  ->MoveRegister(obj, args[0])
6252  .LoadLiteral(private_name->raw_name())
6253  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[1])
6254  .CallRuntime(Runtime::kGetPrivateMember, args);
6255 }
6256 
6257 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildPrivateDebugDynamicSet(Property* property,
6258  Register obj,
6259  Register value) {
6260  RegisterAllocationScope scope(this);
6261  RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(3);
6262 
6263  Variable* private_name = property->key()->AsVariableProxy()->var();
6264  builder()
6265  ->MoveRegister(obj, args[0])
6266  .LoadLiteral(private_name->raw_name())
6267  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[1])
6268  .MoveRegister(value, args[2])
6269  .CallRuntime(Runtime::kSetPrivateMember, args);
6270 }
