6272 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildPrivateGetterAccess(Register object,
6273  Register accessor_pair) {
6274  RegisterAllocationScope scope(this);
6275  Register accessor = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
6276  RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(1);
6277 
6278  builder()
6279  ->CallRuntime(Runtime::kLoadPrivateGetter, accessor_pair)
6280  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(accessor)
6281  .MoveRegister(object, args[0])
6282  .CallProperty(accessor, args,
6283  feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddCallICSlot()));
6284 }
6285 
6286 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildPrivateSetterAccess(Register object,
6287  Register accessor_pair,
6288  Register value) {
6289  RegisterAllocationScope scope(this);
6290  Register accessor = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
6291  RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
6292 
6293  builder()
6294  ->CallRuntime(Runtime::kLoadPrivateSetter, accessor_pair)
6295  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(accessor)
6296  .MoveRegister(object, args[0])
6297  .MoveRegister(value, args[1])
6298  .CallProperty(accessor, args,
6299  feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddCallICSlot()));
6300 }
6301 
6302 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildPrivateMethodIn(Variable* private_name,
6303  Expression* object_expression) {
6304  DCHECK(IsPrivateMethodOrAccessorVariableMode(private_name->mode()));
6305  ClassScope* scope = private_name->scope()->AsClassScope();
6306  if (private_name->is_static()) {
6307  // For static private methods, "#privatemethod in ..." only returns true for
6308  // the class constructor.
6309  if (scope->class_variable() == nullptr) {
6310  // Can only happen via the debugger. See comment in
6311  // BuildPrivateBrandCheck.
6312  RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
6313  RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
6314  builder()
6315  ->LoadLiteral(Smi::FromEnum(
6316  MessageTemplate::
6317  kInvalidUnusedPrivateStaticMethodAccessedByDebugger))
6318  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[0])
6319  .LoadLiteral(private_name->raw_name())
6320  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[1])
6321  .CallRuntime(Runtime::kNewError, args)
6322  .Throw();
6323  } else {
6324  VisitForAccumulatorValue(object_expression);
6325  Register object = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
6326  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(object);
6327 
6328  BytecodeLabel is_object;
6329  builder()->JumpIfJSReceiver(&is_object);
6330 
6331  RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(3);
6332  builder()
6333  ->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[2])
6334  .LoadLiteral(Smi::FromEnum(MessageTemplate::kInvalidInOperatorUse))
6335  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[0])
6336  .LoadLiteral(private_name->raw_name())
6337  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[1])
6338  .CallRuntime(Runtime::kNewTypeError, args)
6339  .Throw();
6340 
6341  builder()->Bind(&is_object);
6342  BuildVariableLoadForAccumulatorValue(scope->class_variable(),
6343  HoleCheckMode::kElided);
6344  builder()->CompareReference(object);
6345  }
6346  } else {
6347  BuildVariableLoadForAccumulatorValue(scope->brand(),
6348  HoleCheckMode::kElided);
6349  Register brand = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
6350  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(brand);
6351 
6352  VisitForAccumulatorValue(object_expression);
6353  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(object_expression);
6354 
6355  FeedbackSlot slot = feedback_spec()->AddKeyedHasICSlot();
6356  builder()->CompareOperation(Token::kIn, brand, feedback_index(slot));
6357  execution_result()->SetResultIsBoolean();
6358  }
6359 }
6360 
6361 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildPrivateBrandCheck(Property* property,
6362  Register object) {
6363  Variable* private_name = property->key()->AsVariableProxy()->var();
6364  DCHECK(IsPrivateMethodOrAccessorVariableMode(private_name->mode()));
6365  ClassScope* scope = private_name->scope()->AsClassScope();
6366  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(property);
6367  if (private_name->is_static()) {
6368  // For static private methods, the only valid receiver is the class.
6369  // Load the class constructor.
6370  if (scope->class_variable() == nullptr) {
6371  // If the static private method has not been used used in source
6372  // code (either explicitly or through the presence of eval), but is
6373  // accessed by the debugger at runtime, reference to the class variable
6374  // is not available since it was not be context-allocated. Therefore we
6375  // can't build a branch check, and throw an ReferenceError as if the
6376  // method was optimized away.
6377  // TODO(joyee): get a reference to the class constructor through
6378  // something other than scope->class_variable() in this scenario.
6379  RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
6380  RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
6381  builder()
6382  ->LoadLiteral(Smi::FromEnum(
6383  MessageTemplate::
6384  kInvalidUnusedPrivateStaticMethodAccessedByDebugger))
6385  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[0])
6386  .LoadLiteral(private_name->raw_name())
6387  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[1])
6388  .CallRuntime(Runtime::kNewError, args)
6389  .Throw();
6390  } else {
6391  BuildVariableLoadForAccumulatorValue(scope->class_variable(),
6392  HoleCheckMode::kElided);
6393  BytecodeLabel return_check;
6394  builder()->CompareReference(object).JumpIfTrue(
6395  ToBooleanMode::kAlreadyBoolean, &return_check);
6396  const AstRawString* name = scope->class_variable()->raw_name();
6397  RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
6398  RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
6399  builder()
6400  ->LoadLiteral(
6401  Smi::FromEnum(MessageTemplate::kInvalidPrivateBrandStatic))
6402  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[0])
6403  .LoadLiteral(name)
6404  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[1])
6405  .CallRuntime(Runtime::kNewTypeError, args)
6406  .Throw();
6407  builder()->Bind(&return_check);
6408  }
6409  } else {
6410  BuildVariableLoadForAccumulatorValue(scope->brand(),
6411  HoleCheckMode::kElided);
6412  builder()->LoadKeyedProperty(
6413  object, feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddKeyedLoadICSlot()));
6414  }
6415 }
6416 
6417 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitPropertyLoadForRegister(Register obj,
6418  Property* expr,
6419  Register destination) {
6420  ValueResultScope result_scope(this);
6421  VisitPropertyLoad(obj, expr);
6422  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(destination);
6423 }
6424 
6425 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitNamedSuperPropertyLoad(Property* property,
6426  Register opt_receiver_out) {
6427  RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
6428  if (v8_flags.super_ic) {
6429  Register receiver = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
6430  BuildThisVariableLoad();
6431  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(receiver);
6432  BuildVariableLoad(
6433  property->obj()->AsSuperPropertyReference()->home_object()->var(),
6434  HoleCheckMode::kElided);
6435  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(property);
6436  auto name = property->key()->AsLiteral()->AsRawPropertyName();
6437  FeedbackSlot slot = GetCachedLoadSuperICSlot(name);
6438  builder()->LoadNamedPropertyFromSuper(receiver, name, feedback_index(slot));
6439  if (opt_receiver_out.is_valid()) {
6440  builder()->MoveRegister(receiver, opt_receiver_out);
6441  }
6442  } else {
6443  RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(3);
6444  BuildThisVariableLoad();
6445  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[0]);
6446  BuildVariableLoad(
6447  property->obj()->AsSuperPropertyReference()->home_object()->var(),
6448  HoleCheckMode::kElided);
6449  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[1]);
6450  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(property);
6451  builder()
6452  ->LoadLiteral(property->key()->AsLiteral()->AsRawPropertyName())
6453  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[2])
6454  .CallRuntime(Runtime::kLoadFromSuper, args);
6455 
6456  if (opt_receiver_out.is_valid()) {
6457  builder()->MoveRegister(args[0], opt_receiver_out);
6458  }
6459  }
6460 }
6461 
6462 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitKeyedSuperPropertyLoad(Property* property,
6463  Register opt_receiver_out) {
6464  RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
6465  RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(3);
6466  BuildThisVariableLoad();
6467  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[0]);
6468  BuildVariableLoad(
6469  property->obj()->AsSuperPropertyReference()->home_object()->var(),
6470  HoleCheckMode::kElided);
6471  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[1]);
6472  VisitForRegisterValue(property->key(), args[2]);
6473 
6474  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(property);
6475  builder()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kLoadKeyedFromSuper, args);
6476 
6477  if (opt_receiver_out.is_valid()) {
6478  builder()->MoveRegister(args[0], opt_receiver_out);
6479  }
6480 }
6481 
6482 template <typename ExpressionFunc>
6483 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildOptionalChain(ExpressionFunc expression_func) {
6484  BytecodeLabel done;
6485  OptionalChainNullLabelScope label_scope(this);
6486  // Use the same scope for the entire optional chain, as links earlier in the
6487  // chain dominate later links, linearly.
6488  HoleCheckElisionScope elider(this);
6489  expression_func();
6490  builder()->Jump(&done);
6491  label_scope.labels()->Bind(builder());
6492  builder()->LoadUndefined();
6493  builder()->Bind(&done);
6494 }
6495 
6496 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitOptionalChain(OptionalChain* expr) {
6497  BuildOptionalChain([&]() { VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->expression()); });
6498 }
6499 
6500 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitProperty(Property* expr) {
6501  AssignType property_kind = Property::GetAssignType(expr);
6502  if (property_kind != NAMED_SUPER_PROPERTY &&
6503  property_kind != KEYED_SUPER_PROPERTY) {
6504  Register obj = VisitForRegisterValue(expr->obj());
6505  VisitPropertyLoad(obj, expr);
6506  } else {
6507  VisitPropertyLoad(Register::invalid_value(), expr);
6508  }
6509 }
6510 
6511 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitArguments(const ZonePtrList<Expression>* args,
6512  RegisterList* arg_regs) {
6513  // Visit arguments.
6514  builder()->UpdateMaxArguments(static_cast<uint16_t>(args->length()));
6515  for (int i = 0; i < static_cast<int>(args->length()); i++) {
6516  VisitAndPushIntoRegisterList(args->at(i), arg_regs);
6517  }
6518 }
6519 
6520 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitCall(Call* expr) {
6521  Expression* callee_expr = expr->expression();
6522  Call::CallType call_type = expr->GetCallType();
6523 
6524  if (call_type == Call::SUPER_CALL) {
6525  return VisitCallSuper(expr);
6526  }
6527 
6528  // We compile the call differently depending on the presence of spreads and
6529  // their positions.
6530  //
6531  // If there is only one spread and it is the final argument, there is a
6532  // special CallWithSpread bytecode.
6533  //
6534  // If there is a non-final spread, we rewrite calls like
6535  // callee(1, ...x, 2)
6536  // to
6537  // %reflect_apply(callee, receiver, [1, ...x, 2])
6538  const Call::SpreadPosition spread_position = expr->spread_position();
6539 
6540  // Grow the args list as we visit receiver / arguments to avoid allocating all
6541  // the registers up-front. Otherwise these registers are unavailable during
6542  // receiver / argument visiting and we can end up with memory leaks due to
6543  // registers keeping objects alive.
6544  RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewGrowableRegisterList();
6545 
6546  // The callee is the first register in args for ease of calling %reflect_apply
6547  // if we have a non-final spread. For all other cases it is popped from args
6548  // before emitting the call below.
6549  Register callee = register_allocator()->GrowRegisterList(&args);
6550 
6551  bool implicit_undefined_receiver = false;
6552 
6553  // TODO(petermarshall): We have a lot of call bytecodes that are very similar,
6554  // see if we can reduce the number by adding a separate argument which
6555  // specifies the call type (e.g., property, spread, tailcall, etc.).
6556 
6557  // Prepare the callee and the receiver to the function call. This depends on
6558  // the semantics of the underlying call type.
6559  switch (call_type) {
6560  case Call::NAMED_PROPERTY_CALL:
6561  case Call::KEYED_PROPERTY_CALL:
6562  case Call::PRIVATE_CALL: {
6563  Property* property = callee_expr->AsProperty();
6564  VisitAndPushIntoRegisterList(property->obj(), &args);
6565  VisitPropertyLoadForRegister(args.last_register(), property, callee);
6566  break;
6567  }
6568  case Call::GLOBAL_CALL: {
6569  // Receiver is undefined for global calls.
6570  if (spread_position == Call::kNoSpread) {
6571  implicit_undefined_receiver = true;
6572  } else {
6573  // TODO(leszeks): There's no special bytecode for tail calls or spread
6574  // calls with an undefined receiver, so just push undefined ourselves.
6575  BuildPushUndefinedIntoRegisterList(&args);
6576  }
6577  // Load callee as a global variable.
6578  VariableProxy* proxy = callee_expr->AsVariableProxy();
6579  BuildVariableLoadForAccumulatorValue(proxy->var(),
6580  proxy->hole_check_mode());
6581  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(callee);
6582  break;
6583  }
6584  case Call::WITH_CALL: {
6585  Register receiver = register_allocator()->GrowRegisterList(&args);
6586  DCHECK(callee_expr->AsVariableProxy()->var()->IsLookupSlot());
6587  {
6588  RegisterAllocationScope inner_register_scope(this);
6589  Register name = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
6590 
6591  // Call %LoadLookupSlotForCall to get the callee and receiver.
6592  RegisterList result_pair = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
6593  Variable* variable = callee_expr->AsVariableProxy()->var();
6594  builder()
6595  ->LoadLiteral(variable->raw_name())
6596  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(name)
6597  .CallRuntimeForPair(Runtime::kLoadLookupSlotForCall, name,
6598  result_pair)
6599  .MoveRegister(result_pair[0], callee)
6600  .MoveRegister(result_pair[1], receiver);
6601  }
6602  break;
6603  }
6604  case Call::OTHER_CALL: {
6605  // Receiver is undefined for other calls.
6606  if (spread_position == Call::kNoSpread) {
6607  implicit_undefined_receiver = true;
6608  } else {
6609  // TODO(leszeks): There's no special bytecode for tail calls or spread
6610  // calls with an undefined receiver, so just push undefined ourselves.
6611  BuildPushUndefinedIntoRegisterList(&args);
6612  }
6613  VisitForRegisterValue(callee_expr, callee);
6614  break;
6615  }
6616  case Call::NAMED_SUPER_PROPERTY_CALL: {
6617  Register receiver = register_allocator()->GrowRegisterList(&args);
6618  Property* property = callee_expr->AsProperty();
6619  VisitNamedSuperPropertyLoad(property, receiver);
6620  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(callee);
6621  break;
6622  }
6623  case Call::KEYED_SUPER_PROPERTY_CALL: {
6624  Register receiver = register_allocator()->GrowRegisterList(&args);
6625  Property* property = callee_expr->AsProperty();
6626  VisitKeyedSuperPropertyLoad(property, receiver);
6627  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(callee);
6628  break;
6629  }
6630  case Call::NAMED_OPTIONAL_CHAIN_PROPERTY_CALL:
6631  case Call::KEYED_OPTIONAL_CHAIN_PROPERTY_CALL:
6632  case Call::PRIVATE_OPTIONAL_CHAIN_CALL: {
6633  OptionalChain* chain = callee_expr->AsOptionalChain();
6634  Property* property = chain->expression()->AsProperty();
6635  BuildOptionalChain([&]() {
6636  VisitAndPushIntoRegisterList(property->obj(), &args);
6637  VisitPropertyLoad(args.last_register(), property);
6638  });
6639  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(callee);
6640  break;
6641  }
6642  case Call::SUPER_CALL:
6643  UNREACHABLE();
6644  }
6645 
6646  if (expr->is_optional_chain_link()) {
6647  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(optional_chaining_null_labels_);
6648  int right_range =
6649  AllocateBlockCoverageSlotIfEnabled(expr, SourceRangeKind::kRight);
6650  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(callee).JumpIfUndefinedOrNull(
6651  optional_chaining_null_labels_->New());
6652  BuildIncrementBlockCoverageCounterIfEnabled(right_range);
6653  }
6654 
6655  int receiver_arg_count = -1;
6656  if (spread_position == Call::kHasNonFinalSpread) {
6657  // If we're building %reflect_apply, build the array literal and put it in
6658  // the 3rd argument.
6659  DCHECK(!implicit_undefined_receiver);
6660  DCHECK_EQ(args.register_count(), 2);
6661  BuildCreateArrayLiteral(expr->arguments(), nullptr);
6662  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(
6663  register_allocator()->GrowRegisterList(&args));
6664  } else {
6665  // If we're not building %reflect_apply and don't need to build an array
6666  // literal, pop the callee and evaluate all arguments to the function call
6667  // and store in sequential args registers.
6668  args = args.PopLeft();
6669  VisitArguments(expr->arguments(), &args);
6670  receiver_arg_count = implicit_undefined_receiver ? 0 : 1;
6671  CHECK_EQ(receiver_arg_count + expr->arguments()->length(),
6672  args.register_count());
6673  }
6674 
6675  // Resolve callee for a potential direct eval call. This block will mutate the
6676  // callee value.
6677  if (expr->is_possibly_eval() && expr->arguments()->length() > 0) {
6678  RegisterAllocationScope inner_register_scope(this);
6679  RegisterList runtime_call_args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(6);
6680  // Set up arguments for ResolvePossiblyDirectEval by copying callee, source
6681  // strings and function closure, and loading language and
6682  // position.
6683 
6684  // Move the first arg.
6685  if (spread_position == Call::kHasNonFinalSpread) {
6686  int feedback_slot_index =
6687  feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddKeyedLoadICSlot());
6688  Register args_array = args[2];
6689  builder()
6690  ->LoadLiteral(Smi::FromInt(0))
6691  .LoadKeyedProperty(args_array, feedback_slot_index)
6692  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(runtime_call_args[1]);
6693  } else {
6694  // FIXME(v8:5690): Support final spreads for eval.
6695  DCHECK_GE(receiver_arg_count, 0);
6696  builder()->MoveRegister(args[receiver_arg_count], runtime_call_args[1]);
6697  }
6698  Scope* scope_with_context = current_scope();
6699  if (!scope_with_context->NeedsContext()) {
6700  scope_with_context = scope_with_context->GetOuterScopeWithContext();
6701  }
6702  if (scope_with_context) {
6703  eval_calls_.emplace_back(expr, scope_with_context);
6704  }
6705  builder()
6706  ->MoveRegister(callee, runtime_call_args[0])
6707  .MoveRegister(Register::function_closure(), runtime_call_args[2])
6708  .LoadLiteral(Smi::FromEnum(language_mode()))
6709  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(runtime_call_args[3])
6710  .LoadLiteral(Smi::FromInt(expr->eval_scope_info_index()))
6711  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(runtime_call_args[4])
6712  .LoadLiteral(Smi::FromInt(expr->position()))
6713  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(runtime_call_args[5]);
6714 
6715  // Call ResolvePossiblyDirectEval and modify the callee.
6716  builder()
6717  ->CallRuntime(Runtime::kResolvePossiblyDirectEval, runtime_call_args)
6718  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(callee);
6719  }
6720 
6721  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr);
6722 
6723  if (spread_position == Call::kHasFinalSpread) {
6724  DCHECK(!implicit_undefined_receiver);
6725  builder()->CallWithSpread(callee, args,
6726  feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddCallICSlot()));
6727  } else if (spread_position == Call::kHasNonFinalSpread) {
6728  builder()->CallJSRuntime(Context::REFLECT_APPLY_INDEX, args);
6729  } else if (call_type == Call::NAMED_PROPERTY_CALL ||
6730  call_type == Call::KEYED_PROPERTY_CALL) {
6731  DCHECK(!implicit_undefined_receiver);
6732  builder()->CallProperty(callee, args,
6733  feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddCallICSlot()));
6734  } else if (implicit_undefined_receiver) {
6735  builder()->CallUndefinedReceiver(
6736  callee, args, feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddCallICSlot()));
6737  } else {
6738  builder()->CallAnyReceiver(
6739  callee, args, feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddCallICSlot()));
6740  }
6741 }
6742 
6743 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitCallSuper(Call* expr) {
6744  RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
6745  SuperCallReference* super = expr->expression()->AsSuperCallReference();
6746  const ZonePtrList<Expression>* args = expr->arguments();
6747 
6748  // We compile the super call differently depending on the presence of spreads
6749  // and their positions.
6750  //
6751  // If there is only one spread and it is the final argument, there is a
6752  // special ConstructWithSpread bytecode.
6753  //
6754  // It there is a non-final spread, we rewrite something like
6755  // super(1, ...x, 2)
6756  // to
6757  // %reflect_construct(constructor, [1, ...x, 2], new_target)
6758  //
6759  // That is, we implement (non-last-arg) spreads in super calls via our
6760  // mechanism for spreads in array literals.
6761  const Call::SpreadPosition spread_position = expr->spread_position();
6762 
6763  // Prepare the constructor to the super call.
6764  Register this_function = VisitForRegisterValue(super->this_function_var());
6765  // This register will initially hold the constructor, then afterward it will
6766  // hold the instance -- the lifetimes of the two don't need to overlap, and
6767  // this way FindNonDefaultConstructorOrConstruct can choose to write either
6768  // the instance or the constructor into the same register.
6769  Register constructor_then_instance = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
6770 
6771  BytecodeLabel super_ctor_call_done;
6772 
6773  if (spread_position == Call::kHasNonFinalSpread) {
6774  RegisterAllocationScope inner_register_scope(this);
6775  RegisterList construct_args(constructor_then_instance);
6776  const Register& constructor = constructor_then_instance;
6777 
6778  // Generate the array containing all arguments.
6779  BuildCreateArrayLiteral(args, nullptr);
6780  Register args_array =
6781  register_allocator()->GrowRegisterList(&construct_args);
6782  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args_array);
6783 
6784  Register new_target =
6785  register_allocator()->GrowRegisterList(&construct_args);
6786  VisitForRegisterValue(super->new_target_var(), new_target);
6787 
6788  BuildGetAndCheckSuperConstructor(this_function, new_target, constructor,
6789  &super_ctor_call_done);
6790 
6791  // Now pass that array to %reflect_construct.
6792  builder()->CallJSRuntime(Context::REFLECT_CONSTRUCT_INDEX, construct_args);
6793  } else {
6794  RegisterAllocationScope inner_register_scope(this);
6795  RegisterList args_regs = register_allocator()->NewGrowableRegisterList();
6796  VisitArguments(args, &args_regs);
6797 
6798  // The new target is loaded into the new_target register from the
6799  // {new.target} variable.
6800  Register new_target = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
6801  VisitForRegisterValue(super->new_target_var(), new_target);
6802 
6803  const Register& constructor = constructor_then_instance;
6804  BuildGetAndCheckSuperConstructor(this_function, new_target, constructor,
6805  &super_ctor_call_done);
6806 
6807  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(new_target);
6808  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr);
6809 
6810  int feedback_slot_index = feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddCallICSlot());
6811 
6812  if (spread_position == Call::kHasFinalSpread) {
6813  builder()->ConstructWithSpread(constructor, args_regs,
6814  feedback_slot_index);
6815  } else {
6816  DCHECK_EQ(spread_position, Call::kNoSpread);
6817  // Call construct.
6818  // TODO(turbofan): For now we do gather feedback on super constructor
6819  // calls, utilizing the existing machinery to inline the actual call
6820  // target and the JSCreate for the implicit receiver allocation. This
6821  // is not an ideal solution for super constructor calls, but it gets
6822  // the job done for now. In the long run we might want to revisit this
6823  // and come up with a better way.
6824  builder()->Construct(constructor, args_regs, feedback_slot_index);
6825  }
6826  }
6827 
6828  // From here onwards, constructor_then_instance will hold the instance.
6829  const Register& instance = constructor_then_instance;
6830  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(instance);
6831  builder()->Bind(&super_ctor_call_done);
6832 
6833  BuildInstanceInitializationAfterSuperCall(this_function, instance);
6834  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(instance);
6835 }
6836 
6837 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildInstanceInitializationAfterSuperCall(
6838  Register this_function, Register instance) {
6839  // Explicit calls to the super constructor using super() perform an
6840  // implicit binding assignment to the 'this' variable.
6841  //
6842  // Default constructors don't need have to do the assignment because
6843  // 'this' isn't accessed in default constructors.
6844  if (!IsDefaultConstructor(info()->literal()->kind())) {
6845  Variable* var = closure_scope()->GetReceiverScope()->receiver();
6846  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(instance);
6847  BuildVariableAssignment(var, Token::kInit, HoleCheckMode::kRequired);
6848  }
6849 
6850  // The constructor scope always needs ScopeInfo, so we are certain that
6851  // the first constructor scope found in the outer scope chain is the
6852  // scope that we are looking for for this super() call.
6853  // Note that this doesn't necessarily mean that the constructor needs
6854  // a context, if it doesn't this would get handled specially in
6855  // BuildPrivateBrandInitialization().
6856  DeclarationScope* constructor_scope = info()->scope()->GetConstructorScope();
6857 
6858  // We can rely on the class_scope_has_private_brand bit to tell if the
6859  // constructor needs private brand initialization, and if that's
6860  // the case we are certain that its outer class scope requires a context to
6861  // keep the brand variable, so we can just get the brand variable
6862  // from the outer scope.
6863  if (constructor_scope->class_scope_has_private_brand()) {
6864  DCHECK(constructor_scope->outer_scope()->is_class_scope());
6865  ClassScope* class_scope = constructor_scope->outer_scope()->AsClassScope();
6866  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(class_scope->brand());
6867  Variable* brand = class_scope->brand();
6868  BuildPrivateBrandInitialization(instance, brand);
6869  }
6870 
6871  // The derived constructor has the correct bit set always, so we
6872  // don't emit code to load and call the initializer if not
6873  // required.
6874  //
6875  // For the arrow function or eval case, we always emit code to load
6876  // and call the initializer.
6877  //
6878  // TODO(gsathya): In the future, we could tag nested arrow functions
6879  // or eval with the correct bit so that we do the load conditionally
6880  // if required.
6881  if (info()->literal()->requires_instance_members_initializer() ||
6882  !IsDerivedConstructor(info()->literal()->kind())) {
6883  BuildInstanceMemberInitialization(this_function, instance);
6884  }
6885 }
6886 
6887 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildGetAndCheckSuperConstructor(
6888  Register this_function, Register new_target, Register constructor,
6889  BytecodeLabel* super_ctor_call_done) {
6890  bool omit_super_ctor = v8_flags.omit_default_ctors &&
6891  IsDerivedConstructor(info()->literal()->kind());
6892 
6893  if (omit_super_ctor) {
6894  BuildSuperCallOptimization(this_function, new_target, constructor,
6895  super_ctor_call_done);
6896  } else {
6897  builder()
6898  ->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(this_function)
6899  .GetSuperConstructor(constructor);
6900  }
6901 
6902  // Check if the constructor is in fact a constructor.
6903  builder()->ThrowIfNotSuperConstructor(constructor);
6904 }
6905 
6906 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildSuperCallOptimization(
6907  Register this_function, Register new_target,
6908  Register constructor_then_instance, BytecodeLabel* super_ctor_call_done) {
6909  DCHECK(v8_flags.omit_default_ctors);
6910  RegisterList output = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
6911  builder()->FindNonDefaultConstructorOrConstruct(this_function, new_target,
6912  output);
6913  builder()->MoveRegister(output[1], constructor_then_instance);
6914  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(output[0]).JumpIfTrue(
6915  ToBooleanMode::kAlreadyBoolean, super_ctor_call_done);
6916 }
6917 
6918 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitCallNew(CallNew* expr) {
6919  RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewGrowableRegisterList();
6920 
6921  // Load the constructor. It's in the first register in args for ease of
6922  // calling %reflect_construct if we have a non-final spread. For all other
6923  // cases it is popped before emitting the construct below.
6924  VisitAndPushIntoRegisterList(expr->expression(), &args);
6925 
6926  // We compile the new differently depending on the presence of spreads and
6927  // their positions.
6928  //
6929  // If there is only one spread and it is the final argument, there is a
6930  // special ConstructWithSpread bytecode.
6931  //
6932  // If there is a non-final spread, we rewrite calls like
6933  // new ctor(1, ...x, 2)
6934  // to
6935  // %reflect_construct(ctor, [1, ...x, 2])
6936  const CallNew::SpreadPosition spread_position = expr->spread_position();
6937 
6938  if (spread_position == CallNew::kHasNonFinalSpread) {
6939  BuildCreateArrayLiteral(expr->arguments(), nullptr);
6940  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr);
6941  builder()
6942  ->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(
6943  register_allocator()->GrowRegisterList(&args))
6944  .CallJSRuntime(Context::REFLECT_CONSTRUCT_INDEX, args);
6945  return;
6946  }
6947 
6948  Register constructor = args.first_register();
6949  args = args.PopLeft();
6950  VisitArguments(expr->arguments(), &args);
6951 
6952  // The accumulator holds new target which is the same as the
6953  // constructor for CallNew.
6954  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr);
6955  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(constructor);
6956 
6957  int feedback_slot_index = feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddCallICSlot());
6958  if (spread_position == CallNew::kHasFinalSpread) {
6959  builder()->ConstructWithSpread(constructor, args, feedback_slot_index);
6960  } else {
6961  DCHECK_EQ(spread_position, CallNew::kNoSpread);
6962  builder()->Construct(constructor, args, feedback_slot_index);
6963  }
6964 }
6965 
6966 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitSuperCallForwardArgs(SuperCallForwardArgs* expr) {
6967  RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
6968 
6969  SuperCallReference* super = expr->expression();
6970  Register this_function = VisitForRegisterValue(super->this_function_var());
6971  Register new_target = VisitForRegisterValue(super->new_target_var());
6972 
6973  // This register initially holds the constructor, then the instance.
6974  Register constructor_then_instance = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
6975 
6976  BytecodeLabel super_ctor_call_done;
6977 
6978  {
6979  const Register& constructor = constructor_then_instance;
6980  BuildGetAndCheckSuperConstructor(this_function, new_target, constructor,
6981  &super_ctor_call_done);
6982 
6983  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(new_target);
6984  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr);
6985  int feedback_slot_index = feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddCallICSlot());
6986 
6987  builder()->ConstructForwardAllArgs(constructor, feedback_slot_index);
6988  }
6989 
6990  // From here onwards, constructor_then_instance holds the instance.
6991  const Register& instance = constructor_then_instance;
6992  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(instance);
6993  builder()->Bind(&super_ctor_call_done);
6994 
6995  BuildInstanceInitializationAfterSuperCall(this_function, instance);
6996  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(instance);
6997 }
6998 
6999 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitCallRuntime(CallRuntime* expr) {
7000  // Evaluate all arguments to the runtime call.
7001  RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewGrowableRegisterList();
7002  VisitArguments(expr->arguments(), &args);
7003  Runtime::FunctionId function_id = expr->function()->function_id;
7004  builder()->CallRuntime(function_id, args);
7005 }
7006 
7007 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitVoid(UnaryOperation* expr) {
7008  VisitForEffect(expr->expression());
7009  builder()->LoadUndefined();
7010 }
7011 
7012 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitForTypeOfValue(Expression* expr) {
7013  if (expr->IsVariableProxy()) {
7014  // Typeof does not throw a reference error on global variables, hence we
7015  // perform a non-contextual load in case the operand is a variable proxy.
7016  VariableProxy* proxy = expr->AsVariableProxy();
7017  BuildVariableLoadForAccumulatorValue(proxy->var(), proxy->hole_check_mode(),
7018  TypeofMode::kInside);
7019  } else {
7020  VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr);
7021  }
7022 }
7023 
7024 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitTypeOf(UnaryOperation* expr) {
7025  VisitForTypeOfValue(expr->expression());
7026  builder()->TypeOf(feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddTypeOfSlot()));
7027  execution_result()->SetResultIsInternalizedString();
7028 }
7029 
7030 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitNot(UnaryOperation* expr) {
7031  if (execution_result()->IsEffect()) {
7032  VisitForEffect(expr->expression());
7033  } else if (execution_result()->IsTest()) {
7034  // No actual logical negation happening, we just swap the control flow, by
7035  // swapping the target labels and the fallthrough branch, and visit in the
7036  // same test result context.
7037  TestResultScope* test_result = execution_result()->AsTest();
7038  test_result->InvertControlFlow();
7039  VisitInSameTestExecutionScope(expr->expression());
7040  } else {
7041  UnaryOperation* unary_op = expr->expression()->AsUnaryOperation();
7042  if (unary_op && unary_op->op() == Token::kNot) {
7043  // Shortcut repeated nots, to capture the `!!foo` pattern for converting
7044  // expressions to booleans.
7045  TypeHint type_hint = VisitForAccumulatorValue(unary_op->expression());
7046  builder()->ToBoolean(ToBooleanModeFromTypeHint(type_hint));
7047  } else {
7048  TypeHint type_hint = VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->expression());
7049  builder()->LogicalNot(ToBooleanModeFromTypeHint(type_hint));
7050  }
7051  // Always returns a boolean value.
7052  execution_result()->SetResultIsBoolean();
7053  }
7054 }
7055 
7056 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitUnaryOperation(UnaryOperation* expr) {
7057  switch (expr->op()) {
7058  case Token::kNot:
7059  VisitNot(expr);
7060  break;
7061  case Token::kTypeOf:
7062  VisitTypeOf(expr);
7063  break;
7064  case Token::kVoid:
7065  VisitVoid(expr);
7066  break;
7067  case Token::kDelete:
7068  VisitDelete(expr);
7069  break;
7070  case Token::kAdd:
7071  case Token::kSub:
7072  case Token::kBitNot:
7073  VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->expression());
7074  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr);
7075  builder()->UnaryOperation(
7076  expr->op(), feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddBinaryOpICSlot()));
7077  break;
7078  default:
7079  UNREACHABLE();
7080  }
7081 }
7082 
7083 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitDelete(UnaryOperation* unary) {
7084  Expression* expr = unary->expression();
7085  if (expr->IsProperty()) {
7086  // Delete of an object property is allowed both in sloppy
7087  // and strict modes.
7088  Property* property = expr->AsProperty();
7089  DCHECK(!property->IsPrivateReference());
7090  if (property->IsSuperAccess()) {
7091  // Delete of super access is not allowed.
7092  VisitForEffect(property->key());
7093  builder()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowUnsupportedSuperError);
7094  } else {
7095  Register object = VisitForRegisterValue(property->obj());
7096  VisitForAccumulatorValue(property->key());
7097  builder()->Delete(object, language_mode());
7098  }
7099  } else if (expr->IsOptionalChain()) {
7100  Expression* expr_inner = expr->AsOptionalChain()->expression();
7101  if (expr_inner->IsProperty()) {
7102  Property* property = expr_inner->AsProperty();
7103  DCHECK(!property->IsPrivateReference());
7104  BytecodeLabel done;
7105  OptionalChainNullLabelScope label_scope(this);
7106  VisitForAccumulatorValue(property->obj());
7107  if (property->is_optional_chain_link()) {
7108  int right_range = AllocateBlockCoverageSlotIfEnabled(
7109  property, SourceRangeKind::kRight);
7110  builder()->JumpIfUndefinedOrNull(label_scope.labels()->New());
7111  BuildIncrementBlockCoverageCounterIfEnabled(right_range);
7112  }
7113  Register object = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
7114  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(object);
7115  if (property->is_optional_chain_link()) {
7116  VisitInHoleCheckElisionScopeForAccumulatorValue(property->key());
7117  } else {
7118  VisitForAccumulatorValue(property->key());
7119  }
7120  builder()->Delete(object, language_mode());
7121  builder()->Jump(&done);
7122  label_scope.labels()->Bind(builder());
7123  builder()->LoadTrue();
7124  builder()->Bind(&done);
7125  } else {
7126  VisitForEffect(expr);
7127  builder()->LoadTrue();
7128  }
7129  } else if (expr->IsVariableProxy() &&
7130  !expr->AsVariableProxy()->is_new_target()) {
7131  // Delete of an unqualified identifier is allowed in sloppy mode but is
7132  // not allowed in strict mode.
7133  DCHECK(is_sloppy(language_mode()));
7134  Variable* variable = expr->AsVariableProxy()->var();
7135  switch (variable->location()) {
7136  case VariableLocation::PARAMETER:
7137  case VariableLocation::LOCAL:
7138  case VariableLocation::CONTEXT:
7139  case VariableLocation::REPL_GLOBAL: {
7140  // Deleting local var/let/const, context variables, and arguments
7141  // does not have any effect.
7142  builder()->LoadFalse();
7143  break;
7144  }
7145  case VariableLocation::UNALLOCATED:
7146  // TODO(adamk): Falling through to the runtime results in correct
7147  // behavior, but does unnecessary context-walking (since scope
7148  // analysis has already proven that the variable doesn't exist in
7149  // any non-global scope). Consider adding a DeleteGlobal bytecode
7150  // that knows how to deal with ScriptContexts as well as global
7151  // object properties.
7152  case VariableLocation::LOOKUP: {
7153  Register name_reg = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
7154  builder()
7155  ->LoadLiteral(variable->raw_name())
7156  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(name_reg)
7157  .CallRuntime(Runtime::kDeleteLookupSlot, name_reg);
7158  break;
7159  }
7160  case VariableLocation::MODULE:
7161  // Modules are always in strict mode and unqualified identifiers are not
7162  // allowed in strict mode.
7163  UNREACHABLE();
7164  }
7165  } else {
7166  // Delete of an unresolvable reference, new.target, and this returns true.
7167  VisitForEffect(expr);
7168  builder()->LoadTrue();
7169  }
7170 }
7171 
7172 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitCountOperation(CountOperation* expr) {
7173  DCHECK(expr->expression()->IsValidReferenceExpression());
7174 
7175  // Left-hand side can only be a property, a global or a variable slot.
7176  Property* property = expr->expression()->AsProperty();
7177  AssignType assign_type = Property::GetAssignType(property);
7178 
7179  bool is_postfix = expr->is_postfix() && !execution_result()->IsEffect();
7180 
7181  // Evaluate LHS expression and get old value.
7182  Register object, key, old_value;
7183  RegisterList super_property_args;
7184  const AstRawString* name;
7185  switch (assign_type) {
7186  case NON_PROPERTY: {
7187  VariableProxy* proxy = expr->expression()->AsVariableProxy();
7188  BuildVariableLoadForAccumulatorValue(proxy->var(),
7189  proxy->hole_check_mode());
7190  break;
7191  }
7192  case NAMED_PROPERTY: {
7193  object = VisitForRegisterValue(property->obj());
7194  name = property->key()->AsLiteral()->AsRawPropertyName();
7195  builder()->LoadNamedProperty(
7196  object, name,
7197  feedback_index(GetCachedLoadICSlot(property->obj(), name)));
7198  break;
7199  }
7200  case KEYED_PROPERTY: {
7201  object = VisitForRegisterValue(property->obj());
7202  // Use visit for accumulator here since we need the key in the accumulator
7203  // for the LoadKeyedProperty.
7204  key = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
7205  VisitForAccumulatorValue(property->key());
7206  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(key).LoadKeyedProperty(
7207  object, feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddKeyedLoadICSlot()));
7208  break;
7209  }
7210  case NAMED_SUPER_PROPERTY: {
7211  super_property_args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(4);
7212  RegisterList load_super_args = super_property_args.Truncate(3);
7213  BuildThisVariableLoad();
7214  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(load_super_args[0]);
7215  BuildVariableLoad(
7216  property->obj()->AsSuperPropertyReference()->home_object()->var(),
7217  HoleCheckMode::kElided);
7218  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(load_super_args[1]);
7219  builder()
7220  ->LoadLiteral(property->key()->AsLiteral()->AsRawPropertyName())
7221  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(load_super_args[2])
7222  .CallRuntime(Runtime::kLoadFromSuper, load_super_args);
7223  break;
7224  }
7225  case KEYED_SUPER_PROPERTY: {
7226  super_property_args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(4);
7227  RegisterList load_super_args = super_property_args.Truncate(3);
7228  BuildThisVariableLoad();
7229  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(load_super_args[0]);
7230  BuildVariableLoad(
7231  property->obj()->AsSuperPropertyReference()->home_object()->var(),
7232  HoleCheckMode::kElided);
7233  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(load_super_args[1]);
7234  VisitForRegisterValue(property->key(), load_super_args[2]);
7235  builder()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kLoadKeyedFromSuper, load_super_args);
7236  break;
7237  }
7238  case PRIVATE_METHOD: {
7239  object = VisitForRegisterValue(property->obj());
7240  BuildPrivateBrandCheck(property, object);
7241  BuildInvalidPropertyAccess(MessageTemplate::kInvalidPrivateMethodWrite,
7242  property);
7243  return;
7244  }
7245  case PRIVATE_GETTER_ONLY: {
7246  object = VisitForRegisterValue(property->obj());
7247  BuildPrivateBrandCheck(property, object);
7248  BuildInvalidPropertyAccess(MessageTemplate::kInvalidPrivateSetterAccess,
7249  property);
7250  return;
7251  }
7252  case PRIVATE_SETTER_ONLY: {
7253  object = VisitForRegisterValue(property->obj());
7254  BuildPrivateBrandCheck(property, object);
7255  BuildInvalidPropertyAccess(MessageTemplate::kInvalidPrivateGetterAccess,
7256  property);
7257  return;
7258  }
7259  case PRIVATE_GETTER_AND_SETTER: {
7260  object = VisitForRegisterValue(property->obj());
7261  key = VisitForRegisterValue(property->key());
7262  BuildPrivateBrandCheck(property, object);
7263  BuildPrivateGetterAccess(object, key);
7264  break;
7265  }
7266  case PRIVATE_DEBUG_DYNAMIC: {
7267  object = VisitForRegisterValue(property->obj());
7268  BuildPrivateDebugDynamicGet(property, object);
7269  break;
7270  }
7271  }
7272 
7273  // Save result for postfix expressions.
7274  FeedbackSlot count_slot = feedback_spec()->AddBinaryOpICSlot();
7275  if (is_postfix) {
7276  old_value = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
7277  // Convert old value into a number before saving it.
7278  // TODO(ignition): Think about adding proper PostInc/PostDec bytecodes
7279  // instead of this ToNumeric + Inc/Dec dance.
7280  builder()
7281  ->ToNumeric(feedback_index(count_slot))
7282  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(old_value);
7283  }
7284 
7285  // Perform +1/-1 operation.
7286  builder()->UnaryOperation(expr->op(), feedback_index(count_slot));
7287 
7288  // Store the value.
7289  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr);
7290  switch (assign_type) {
7291  case NON_PROPERTY: {
7292  VariableProxy* proxy = expr->expression()->AsVariableProxy();
7293  BuildVariableAssignment(proxy->var(), expr->op(),
7294  proxy->hole_check_mode());
7295  break;
7296  }
7297  case NAMED_PROPERTY: {
7298  FeedbackSlot slot = GetCachedStoreICSlot(property->obj(), name);
7299  Register value;
7300  if (!execution_result()->IsEffect()) {
7301  value = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
7302  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(value);
7303  }
7304  builder()->SetNamedProperty(object, name, feedback_index(slot),
7305  language_mode());
7306  if (!execution_result()->IsEffect()) {
7307  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(value);
7308  }
7309  break;
7310  }
7311  case KEYED_PROPERTY: {
7312  FeedbackSlot slot = feedback_spec()->AddKeyedStoreICSlot(language_mode());
7313  Register value;
7314  if (!execution_result()->IsEffect()) {
7315  value = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
7316  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(value);
7317  }
7318  builder()->SetKeyedProperty(object, key, feedback_index(slot),
7319  language_mode());
7320  if (!execution_result()->IsEffect()) {
7321  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(value);
7322  }
7323  break;
7324  }
7325  case NAMED_SUPER_PROPERTY: {
7326  builder()
7327  ->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(super_property_args[3])
7328  .CallRuntime(Runtime::kStoreToSuper, super_property_args);
7329  break;
7330  }
7331  case KEYED_SUPER_PROPERTY: {
7332  builder()
7333  ->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(super_property_args[3])
7334  .CallRuntime(Runtime::kStoreKeyedToSuper, super_property_args);
7335  break;
7336  }
7337  case PRIVATE_SETTER_ONLY:
7338  case PRIVATE_GETTER_ONLY:
7339  case PRIVATE_METHOD: {
7340  UNREACHABLE();
7341  }
7342  case PRIVATE_GETTER_AND_SETTER: {
7343  Register value = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
7344  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(value);
7345  BuildPrivateSetterAccess(object, key, value);
7346  if (!execution_result()->IsEffect()) {
7347  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(value);
7348  }
7349  break;
7350  }
7351  case PRIVATE_DEBUG_DYNAMIC: {
7352  Register value = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
7353  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(value);
7354  BuildPrivateDebugDynamicSet(property, object, value);
7355  break;
7356  }
7357  }
7358 
7359  // Restore old value for postfix expressions.
7360  if (is_postfix) {
7361  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(old_value);
7362  }
7363 }
7364 
7365 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitBinaryOperation(BinaryOperation* binop) {
7366  switch (binop->op()) {
7367  case Token::kComma:
7368  VisitCommaExpression(binop);
7369  break;
7370  case Token::kOr:
7371  VisitLogicalOrExpression(binop);
7372  break;
7373  case Token::kAnd:
7374  VisitLogicalAndExpression(binop);
7375  break;
7376  case Token::kNullish:
7377  VisitNullishExpression(binop);
7378  break;
7379  default:
7380  VisitArithmeticExpression(binop);
7381  break;
7382  }
7383 }
7384 
7385 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitNaryOperation(NaryOperation* expr) {
7386  switch (expr->op()) {
7387  case Token::kComma:
7388  VisitNaryCommaExpression(expr);
7389  break;
7390  case Token::kOr:
7391  VisitNaryLogicalOrExpression(expr);
7392  break;
7393  case Token::kAnd:
7394  VisitNaryLogicalAndExpression(expr);
7395  break;
7396  case Token::kNullish:
7397  VisitNaryNullishExpression(expr);
7398  break;
7399  default:
7400  VisitNaryArithmeticExpression(expr);
7401  break;
7402  }
7403 }
7404 
7405 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildLiteralCompareNil(
7406  Token::Value op, BytecodeArrayBuilder::NilValue nil) {
7407  if (execution_result()->IsTest()) {
7408  TestResultScope* test_result = execution_result()->AsTest();
7409  switch (test_result->fallthrough()) {
7410  case TestFallthrough::kThen:
7411  builder()->JumpIfNotNil(test_result->NewElseLabel(), op, nil);
7412  break;
7413  case TestFallthrough::kElse:
7414  builder()->JumpIfNil(test_result->NewThenLabel(), op, nil);
7415  break;
7416  case TestFallthrough::kNone:
7417  builder()
7418  ->JumpIfNil(test_result->NewThenLabel(), op, nil)
7419  .Jump(test_result->NewElseLabel());
7420  }
7421  test_result->SetResultConsumedByTest();
7422  } else {
7423  builder()->CompareNil(op, nil);
7424  }
7425 }
7426 
7427 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildLiteralStrictCompareBoolean(Literal* literal) {
7428  DCHECK(literal->IsBooleanLiteral());
7429  Register result = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
7430  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(result);
7431  builder()->LoadBoolean(literal->AsBooleanLiteral());
7432  builder()->CompareReference(result);
7433 }

7435 bool BytecodeGenerator::IsLocalVariableWithInternalizedStringHint(
7436  Expression* expr) {
7437  VariableProxy* proxy = expr->AsVariableProxy();
7438  return proxy != nullptr && proxy->is_resolved() &&
7439  proxy->var()->IsStackLocal() &&
7440  GetTypeHintForLocalVariable(proxy->var()) ==
7441  TypeHint::kInternalizedString;
7442 }
7443 
7444 static bool IsTypeof(Expression* expr) {
7445  UnaryOperation* maybe_unary = expr->AsUnaryOperation();
7446  return maybe_unary != nullptr && maybe_unary->op() == Token::kTypeOf;
7447 }
7448 
7449 static bool IsCharU(const AstRawString* str) {
7450  return str->length() == 1 && str->FirstCharacter() == 'u';
7451 }
7452 
7453 static bool IsLiteralCompareTypeof(CompareOperation* expr,
7454  Expression** sub_expr,
7455  TestTypeOfFlags::LiteralFlag* flag,
7456  const AstStringConstants* ast_constants) {
7457  if (IsTypeof(expr->left()) && expr->right()->IsStringLiteral()) {
7458  Literal* right_lit = expr->right()->AsLiteral();
7459 
7460  if (Token::IsEqualityOp(expr->op())) {
7461  // typeof(x) === 'string'
7462  *flag = TestTypeOfFlags::GetFlagForLiteral(ast_constants, right_lit);
7463  } else if (expr->op() == Token::kGreaterThan &&
7464  IsCharU(right_lit->AsRawString())) {
7465  // typeof(x) > 'u'
7466  // Minifier may convert `typeof(x) === 'undefined'` to this form,
7467  // since `undefined` is the only valid value that is greater than 'u'.
7468  // Check the test OnlyUndefinedGreaterThanU in bytecodes-unittest.cc
7469  *flag = TestTypeOfFlags::LiteralFlag::kUndefined;
7470  } else {
7471  return false;
7472  }
7473 
7474  *sub_expr = expr->left()->AsUnaryOperation()->expression();
7475  return true;
7476  }
7477 
7478  if (IsTypeof(expr->right()) && expr->left()->IsStringLiteral()) {
7479  Literal* left_lit = expr->left()->AsLiteral();
7480 
7481  if (Token::IsEqualityOp(expr->op())) {
7482  // 'string' === typeof(x)
7483  *flag = TestTypeOfFlags::GetFlagForLiteral(ast_constants, left_lit);
7484  } else if (expr->op() == Token::kLessThan &&
7485  IsCharU(left_lit->AsRawString())) {
7486  // 'u' < typeof(x)
7487  *flag = TestTypeOfFlags::LiteralFlag::kUndefined;
7488  } else {
7489  return false;
7490  }
7491 
7492  *sub_expr = expr->right()->AsUnaryOperation()->expression();
7493  return true;
7494  }
7495 
7496  return false;
7497 }
7498 
7499 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitCompareOperation(CompareOperation* expr) {
7500  Expression* sub_expr;
7501  Literal* literal;
7502  TestTypeOfFlags::LiteralFlag flag;
7503  if (IsLiteralCompareTypeof(expr, &sub_expr, &flag, ast_string_constants())) {
7504  // Emit a fast literal comparison for expressions of the form:
7505  // typeof(x) === 'string'.
7506  VisitForTypeOfValue(sub_expr);
7507  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr);
7508  if (flag == TestTypeOfFlags::LiteralFlag::kOther) {
7509  builder()->LoadFalse();
7510  } else {
7511  builder()->CompareTypeOf(flag);
7512  }
7513  } else if (expr->IsLiteralStrictCompareBoolean(&sub_expr, &literal)) {
7514  DCHECK(expr->op() == Token::kEqStrict);
7515  VisitForAccumulatorValue(sub_expr);
7516  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr);
7517  BuildLiteralStrictCompareBoolean(literal);
7518  } else if (expr->IsLiteralCompareUndefined(&sub_expr)) {
7519  VisitForAccumulatorValue(sub_expr);
7520  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr);
7521  BuildLiteralCompareNil(expr->op(), BytecodeArrayBuilder::kUndefinedValue);
7522  } else if (expr->IsLiteralCompareNull(&sub_expr)) {
7523  VisitForAccumulatorValue(sub_expr);
7524  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr);
7525  BuildLiteralCompareNil(expr->op(), BytecodeArrayBuilder::kNullValue);
7526  } else if (expr->IsLiteralCompareEqualVariable(&sub_expr, &literal) &&
7527  IsLocalVariableWithInternalizedStringHint(sub_expr)) {
7528  builder()->LoadLiteral(literal->AsRawString());
7529  builder()->CompareReference(
7530  GetRegisterForLocalVariable(sub_expr->AsVariableProxy()->var()));
7531  } else {
7532  if (expr->op() == Token::kIn && expr->left()->IsPrivateName()) {
7533  Variable* var = expr->left()->AsVariableProxy()->var();
7534  if (IsPrivateMethodOrAccessorVariableMode(var->mode())) {
7535  BuildPrivateMethodIn(var, expr->right());
7536  return;
7537  }
7538  // For private fields, the code below does the right thing.
7539  }
7540 
7541  Register lhs = VisitForRegisterValue(expr->left());
7542  VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->right());
7543  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr);
7544  FeedbackSlot slot;
7545  if (expr->op() == Token::kIn) {
7546  slot = feedback_spec()->AddKeyedHasICSlot();
7547  } else if (expr->op() == Token::kInstanceOf) {
7548  slot = feedback_spec()->AddInstanceOfSlot();
7549  } else {
7550  slot = feedback_spec()->AddCompareICSlot();
7551  }
7552  builder()->CompareOperation(expr->op(), lhs, feedback_index(slot));
7553  }
7554  // Always returns a boolean value.
7555  execution_result()->SetResultIsBoolean();
7556 }
7557 
7558 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitArithmeticExpression(BinaryOperation* expr) {
7559  FeedbackSlot slot;
7560 
7561  // We special-case string concatenation when the result is used as a property
7562  // key. In this case, we know it will eventually be internalized and it's
7563  // better to do so early.
7564  //
7565  // For now, we handle only the specialized situation in which one side is a
7566  // string constant.
7567  // TODO(jgruber): Generalize. ConsString literals, property-key but no
7568  // string-literal, string-literal but no property-key.
7569  const bool maybe_emit_specialized_string_add =
7570  expr->op() == Token::kAdd && execution_result()->IsValueAsPropertyKey() &&
7571  v8_flags.cache_property_key_string_adds;
7572  bool emit_add_string_constant_internalize = false;
7573  using ASVariant = AddStringConstantAndInternalizeVariant;
7574  auto as_variant = ASVariant::kLhsIsStringConstant;
7575  if (maybe_emit_specialized_string_add) {
7576  // Is lhs a string constant?
7577  emit_add_string_constant_internalize =
7578  expr->left()->IsLiteral() && expr->left()->AsLiteral()->IsRawString();
7579  if (!emit_add_string_constant_internalize) {
7580  // Is rhs a string constant?
7581  emit_add_string_constant_internalize =
7582  expr->right()->IsLiteral() &&
7583  expr->right()->AsLiteral()->IsRawString();
7584  if (emit_add_string_constant_internalize) {
7585  as_variant = ASVariant::kRhsIsStringConstant;
7586  }
7587  }
7588  }
7589 
7590  if (emit_add_string_constant_internalize) {
7591  slot = feedback_spec()->AddStringAddAndInternalizeICSlot();
7592  } else {
7593  slot = feedback_spec()->AddBinaryOpICSlot();
7594  }
7595 
7596  Expression* subexpr;
7597  Tagged<Smi> literal;
7598  if (expr->IsSmiLiteralOperation(&subexpr, &literal)) {
7599  TypeHint type_hint = VisitForAccumulatorValue(subexpr);
7600  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr);
7601  builder()->BinaryOperationSmiLiteral(expr->op(), literal,
7602  feedback_index(slot));
7603  if (expr->op() == Token::kAdd && IsStringTypeHint(type_hint)) {
7604  execution_result()->SetResultIsString();
7605  }
7606  } else {
7607  TypeHint lhs_type = VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->left());
7608  Register lhs = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
7609  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(lhs);
7610  TypeHint rhs_type = VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->right());
7611  if (expr->op() == Token::kAdd &&
7612  (IsStringTypeHint(lhs_type) || IsStringTypeHint(rhs_type))) {
7613  execution_result()->SetResultIsString();
7614  }
7615 
7616  if (emit_add_string_constant_internalize) {
7617  // Subtle: Stack overflows can cause the AST to be visited only
7618  // partially. Visitation is eventually aborted and the resulting
7619  // bytecode discarded.
7620  DCHECK_IMPLIES(
7621  !HasStackOverflow(),
7622  IsStringTypeHint(as_variant == ASVariant::kLhsIsStringConstant
7623  ? lhs_type
7624  : rhs_type));
7625  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr);
7626  builder()->Add_StringConstant_Internalize(
7627  expr->op(), lhs, feedback_index(slot), as_variant);
7628  } else {
7629  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr);
7630  builder()->BinaryOperation(expr->op(), lhs, feedback_index(slot));
7631  }
7632  }
7633 }
7634 
7635 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitNaryArithmeticExpression(NaryOperation* expr) {
7636  // TODO(leszeks): Add support for lhs smi in commutative ops.
7637  TypeHint type_hint = VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->first());
7638 
7639  for (size_t i = 0; i < expr->subsequent_length(); ++i) {
7640  RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
7641  if (expr->subsequent(i)->IsSmiLiteral()) {
7642  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr->subsequent_op_position(i));
7643  builder()->BinaryOperationSmiLiteral(
7644  expr->op(), expr->subsequent(i)->AsLiteral()->AsSmiLiteral(),
7645  feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddBinaryOpICSlot()));
7646  } else {
7647  Register lhs = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
7648  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(lhs);
7649  TypeHint rhs_hint = VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->subsequent(i));
7650  if (IsStringTypeHint(rhs_hint)) type_hint = TypeHint::kString;
7651  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr->subsequent_op_position(i));
7652  builder()->BinaryOperation(
7653  expr->op(), lhs,
7654  feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddBinaryOpICSlot()));
7655  }
7656  }
7657 
7658  if (IsStringTypeHint(type_hint) && expr->op() == Token::kAdd) {
7659  // If any operand of an ADD is a String, a String is produced.
7660  execution_result()->SetResultIsString();
7661  }
7662 }
7663 
7664 // Note: the actual spreading is performed by the surrounding expression's
7665 // visitor.
7666 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitSpread(Spread* expr) { Visit(expr->expression()); }
7667 
7668 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitEmptyParentheses(EmptyParentheses* expr) {
7669  UNREACHABLE();
7670 }
7671 
7672 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitImportCallExpression(ImportCallExpression* expr) {
7673  const int register_count = expr->import_options() ? 4 : 3;
7674  // args is a list of [ function_closure, specifier, phase, import_options ].
7675  RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(register_count);
7676 
7677  builder()->MoveRegister(Register::function_closure(), args[0]);
7678  VisitForRegisterValue(expr->specifier(), args[1]);
7679  builder()
7680  ->LoadLiteral(Smi::FromInt(static_cast<int>(expr->phase())))
7681  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(args[2]);
7682 
7683  if (expr->import_options()) {
7684  VisitForRegisterValue(expr->import_options(), args[3]);
7685  }
7686 
7687  builder()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kDynamicImportCall, args);
7688 }
7689 
7690 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildGetIterator(IteratorType hint) {
7691  if (hint == IteratorType::kAsync) {
7692  RegisterAllocationScope scope(this);
7693 
7694  Register obj = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
7695  Register method = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
7696 
7697  // Set method to GetMethod(obj, @@asyncIterator)
7698  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(obj).LoadAsyncIteratorProperty(
7699  obj, feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddLoadICSlot()));
7700 
7701  BytecodeLabel async_iterator_undefined, done;
7702  builder()->JumpIfUndefinedOrNull(&async_iterator_undefined);
7703 
7704  // Let iterator be Call(method, obj)
7705  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(method).CallProperty(
7706  method, RegisterList(obj),
7707  feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddCallICSlot()));
7708 
7709  // If Type(iterator) is not Object, throw a TypeError exception.
7710  builder()->JumpIfJSReceiver(&done);
7711  builder()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowSymbolAsyncIteratorInvalid);
7712 
7713  builder()->Bind(&async_iterator_undefined);
7714  // If method is undefined,
7715  // Let syncMethod be GetMethod(obj, @@iterator)
7716  builder()
7717  ->LoadIteratorProperty(obj,
7718  feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddLoadICSlot()))
7719  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(method);
7720 
7721  // Let syncIterator be Call(syncMethod, obj)
7722  builder()->CallProperty(method, RegisterList(obj),
7723  feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddCallICSlot()));
7724 
7725  // Return CreateAsyncFromSyncIterator(syncIterator)
7726  // alias `method` register as it's no longer used
7727  Register sync_iter = method;
7728  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(sync_iter).CallRuntime(
7729  Runtime::kInlineCreateAsyncFromSyncIterator, sync_iter);
7730 
7731  builder()->Bind(&done);
7732  } else {
7733  {
7734  RegisterAllocationScope scope(this);
7735 
7736  Register obj = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
7737  int load_feedback_index =
7738  feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddLoadICSlot());
7739  int call_feedback_index =
7740  feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddCallICSlot());
7741 
7742  // Let method be GetMethod(obj, @@iterator) and
7743  // iterator be Call(method, obj). If iterator is
7744  // not JSReceiver, then throw TypeError.
7745  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(obj).GetIterator(
7746  obj, load_feedback_index, call_feedback_index);
7747  }
7748  }
7749 }
7750 
7751 // Returns an IteratorRecord which is valid for the lifetime of the current
7752 // register_allocation_scope.
7753 BytecodeGenerator::IteratorRecord BytecodeGenerator::BuildGetIteratorRecord(
7754  Register next, Register object, IteratorType hint) {
7755  DCHECK(next.is_valid() && object.is_valid());
7756  BuildGetIterator(hint);
7757 
7758  builder()
7759  ->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(object)
7760  .LoadNamedProperty(object, ast_string_constants()->next_string(),
7761  feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddLoadICSlot()))
7762  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(next);
7763  return IteratorRecord(object, next, hint);
7764 }
7765 
7766 BytecodeGenerator::IteratorRecord BytecodeGenerator::BuildGetIteratorRecord(
7767  IteratorType hint) {
7768  Register next = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
7769  Register object = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
7770  return BuildGetIteratorRecord(next, object, hint);
7771 }

7773 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildIteratorNext(const IteratorRecord& iterator,
7774  Register next_result) {
7775  DCHECK(next_result.is_valid());
7776  builder()->CallProperty(iterator.next(), RegisterList(iterator.object()),
7777  feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddCallICSlot()));
7778 
7779  if (iterator.type() == IteratorType::kAsync) {
7780  BuildAwait();
7781  }
7782 
7783  BytecodeLabel is_object;
7784  builder()
7785  ->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(next_result)
7786  .JumpIfJSReceiver(&is_object)
7787  .CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowIteratorResultNotAnObject, next_result)
7788  .Bind(&is_object);
7789 }
7790 
7791 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildCallIteratorMethod(Register iterator,
7792  const AstRawString* method_name,
7793  RegisterList receiver_and_args,
7794  BytecodeLabel* if_called,
7795  BytecodeLabels* if_notcalled) {
7796  RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
7797 
7798  Register method = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
7799  FeedbackSlot slot = feedback_spec()->AddLoadICSlot();
7800  builder()
7801  ->LoadNamedProperty(iterator, method_name, feedback_index(slot))
7802  .JumpIfUndefinedOrNull(if_notcalled->New())
7803  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(method)
7804  .CallProperty(method, receiver_and_args,
7805  feedback_index(feedback_spec()->AddCallICSlot()))
7806  .Jump(if_called);
7807 }
7808 
7809 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildIteratorClose(const IteratorRecord& iterator,
7810  Expression* expr) {
7811  RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
7812  BytecodeLabels done(zone());
7813  BytecodeLabel if_called;
7814  RegisterList args = RegisterList(iterator.object());
7815  BuildCallIteratorMethod(iterator.object(),
7816  ast_string_constants()->return_string(), args,
7817  &if_called, &done);
7818  builder()->Bind(&if_called);
7819 
7820  if (iterator.type() == IteratorType::kAsync) {
7821  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(expr);
7822  BuildAwait(expr->position());
7823  }
7824 
7825  builder()->JumpIfJSReceiver(done.New());
7826  {
7827  RegisterAllocationScope inner_register_scope(this);
7828  Register return_result = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
7829  builder()
7830  ->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(return_result)
7831  .CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowIteratorResultNotAnObject, return_result);
7832  }
7833 
7834  done.Bind(builder());
7835 }

7837 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitGetTemplateObject(GetTemplateObject* expr) {
7838  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr);
7839  size_t entry = builder()->AllocateDeferredConstantPoolEntry();
7840  template_objects_.push_back(std::make_pair(expr, entry));
7841  FeedbackSlot literal_slot = feedback_spec()->AddLiteralSlot();
7842  builder()->GetTemplateObject(entry, feedback_index(literal_slot));
7843 }
7844 
7845 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitTemplateLiteral(TemplateLiteral* expr) {
7846  const ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>& parts = *expr->string_parts();
7847  const ZonePtrList<Expression>& substitutions = *expr->substitutions();
7848  // Template strings with no substitutions are turned into StringLiterals.
7849  DCHECK_GT(substitutions.length(), 0);
7850  DCHECK_EQ(parts.length(), substitutions.length() + 1);
7851 
7852  // Generate string concatenation
7853  // TODO(caitp): Don't generate feedback slot if it's not used --- introduce
7854  // a simple, concise, reusable mechanism to lazily create reusable slots.
7855  FeedbackSlot slot = feedback_spec()->AddBinaryOpICSlot();
7856  Register last_part = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
7857  bool last_part_valid = false;
7858 
7859  builder()->SetExpressionPosition(expr);
7860  for (int i = 0; i < substitutions.length(); ++i) {
7861  if (i != 0) {
7862  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(last_part);
7863  last_part_valid = true;
7864  }
7865 
7866  if (!parts[i]->IsEmpty()) {
7867  builder()->LoadLiteral(parts[i]);
7868  if (last_part_valid) {
7869  builder()->BinaryOperation(Token::kAdd, last_part,
7870  feedback_index(slot));
7871  }
7872  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(last_part);
7873  last_part_valid = true;
7874  }
7875 
7876  TypeHint type_hint = VisitForAccumulatorValue(substitutions[i]);
7877  if (!IsStringTypeHint(type_hint)) {
7878  builder()->ToString();
7879  }
7880  if (last_part_valid) {
7881  builder()->BinaryOperation(Token::kAdd, last_part, feedback_index(slot));
7882  }
7883  last_part_valid = false;
7884  }
7885 
7886  if (!parts.last()->IsEmpty()) {
7887  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(last_part);
7888  builder()->LoadLiteral(parts.last());
7889  builder()->BinaryOperation(Token::kAdd, last_part, feedback_index(slot));
7890  }
7891 }
7892 
7893 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildThisVariableLoad() {
7894  DeclarationScope* receiver_scope = closure_scope()->GetReceiverScope();
7895  Variable* var = receiver_scope->receiver();
7896  // TODO(littledan): implement 'this' hole check elimination.
7897  HoleCheckMode hole_check_mode =
7898  IsDerivedConstructor(receiver_scope->function_kind())
7899  ? HoleCheckMode::kRequired
7900  : HoleCheckMode::kElided;
7901  BuildVariableLoad(var, hole_check_mode);
7902 }
7903 
7904 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitThisExpression(ThisExpression* expr) {
7905  BuildThisVariableLoad();
7906 }

7920 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitCommaExpression(BinaryOperation* binop) {
7921  VisitForEffect(binop->left());
7922  builder()->SetExpressionAsStatementPosition(binop->right());
7923  Visit(binop->right());
7924 }

7926 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitNaryCommaExpression(NaryOperation* expr) {
7927  DCHECK_GT(expr->subsequent_length(), 0);
7928 
7929  VisitForEffect(expr->first());
7930  for (size_t i = 0; i < expr->subsequent_length() - 1; ++i) {
7931  builder()->SetExpressionAsStatementPosition(expr->subsequent(i));
7932  VisitForEffect(expr->subsequent(i));
7933  }
7934  builder()->SetExpressionAsStatementPosition(
7935  expr->subsequent(expr->subsequent_length() - 1));
7936  Visit(expr->subsequent(expr->subsequent_length() - 1));
7937 }
7938 
7939 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitLogicalTestSubExpression(
7940  Token::Value token, Expression* expr, BytecodeLabels* then_labels,
7941  BytecodeLabels* else_labels, int coverage_slot) {
7942  DCHECK(token == Token::kOr || token == Token::kAnd ||
7943  token == Token::kNullish);
7944 
7945  BytecodeLabels test_next(zone());
7946  if (token == Token::kOr) {
7947  VisitForTest(expr, then_labels, &test_next, TestFallthrough::kElse);
7948  } else if (token == Token::kAnd) {
7949  VisitForTest(expr, &test_next, else_labels, TestFallthrough::kThen);
7950  } else {
7951  DCHECK_EQ(Token::kNullish, token);
7952  VisitForNullishTest(expr, then_labels, &test_next, else_labels);
7953  }
7954  test_next.Bind(builder());
7955 
7956  BuildIncrementBlockCoverageCounterIfEnabled(coverage_slot);
7957 }
7958 
7959 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitLogicalTest(Token::Value token, Expression* left,
7960  Expression* right,
7961  int right_coverage_slot) {
7962  DCHECK(token == Token::kOr || token == Token::kAnd ||
7963  token == Token::kNullish);
7964  TestResultScope* test_result = execution_result()->AsTest();
7965  BytecodeLabels* then_labels = test_result->then_labels();
7966  BytecodeLabels* else_labels = test_result->else_labels();
7967  TestFallthrough fallthrough = test_result->fallthrough();
7968 
7969  VisitLogicalTestSubExpression(token, left, then_labels, else_labels,
7970  right_coverage_slot);
7971  // The last test has the same then, else and fallthrough as the parent test.
7972  HoleCheckElisionScope elider(this);
7973  VisitForTest(right, then_labels, else_labels, fallthrough);
7974 }
7975 
7976 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitNaryLogicalTest(
7977  Token::Value token, NaryOperation* expr,
7978  const NaryCodeCoverageSlots* coverage_slots) {
7979  DCHECK(token == Token::kOr || token == Token::kAnd ||
7980  token == Token::kNullish);
7981  DCHECK_GT(expr->subsequent_length(), 0);
7982 
7983  TestResultScope* test_result = execution_result()->AsTest();
7984  BytecodeLabels* then_labels = test_result->then_labels();
7985  BytecodeLabels* else_labels = test_result->else_labels();
7986  TestFallthrough fallthrough = test_result->fallthrough();
7987 
7988  VisitLogicalTestSubExpression(token, expr->first(), then_labels, else_labels,
7989  coverage_slots->GetSlotFor(0));
7990  HoleCheckElisionScope elider(this);
7991  for (size_t i = 0; i < expr->subsequent_length() - 1; ++i) {
7992  VisitLogicalTestSubExpression(token, expr->subsequent(i), then_labels,
7993  else_labels,
7994  coverage_slots->GetSlotFor(i + 1));
7995  }
7996  // The last test has the same then, else and fallthrough as the parent test.
7997  VisitForTest(expr->subsequent(expr->subsequent_length() - 1), then_labels,
7998  else_labels, fallthrough);
7999 }
8000 
8001 bool BytecodeGenerator::VisitLogicalOrSubExpression(Expression* expr,
8002  BytecodeLabels* end_labels,
8003  int coverage_slot) {
8004  if (expr->ToBooleanIsTrue()) {
8005  VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr);
8006  end_labels->Bind(builder());
8007  return true;
8008  } else if (!expr->ToBooleanIsFalse()) {
8009  TypeHint type_hint = VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr);
8010  builder()->JumpIfTrue(ToBooleanModeFromTypeHint(type_hint),
8011  end_labels->New());
8012  }
8013 
8014  BuildIncrementBlockCoverageCounterIfEnabled(coverage_slot);
8015 
8016  return false;
8017 }
8018 
8019 bool BytecodeGenerator::VisitLogicalAndSubExpression(Expression* expr,
8020  BytecodeLabels* end_labels,
8021  int coverage_slot) {
8022  if (expr->ToBooleanIsFalse()) {
8023  VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr);
8024  end_labels->Bind(builder());
8025  return true;
8026  } else if (!expr->ToBooleanIsTrue()) {
8027  TypeHint type_hint = VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr);
8028  builder()->JumpIfFalse(ToBooleanModeFromTypeHint(type_hint),
8029  end_labels->New());
8030  }
8031 
8032  BuildIncrementBlockCoverageCounterIfEnabled(coverage_slot);
8033 
8034  return false;
8035 }
8036 
8037 bool BytecodeGenerator::VisitNullishSubExpression(Expression* expr,
8038  BytecodeLabels* end_labels,
8039  int coverage_slot) {
8040  if (expr->IsLiteralButNotNullOrUndefined()) {
8041  VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr);
8042  end_labels->Bind(builder());
8043  return true;
8044  } else if (!expr->IsNullOrUndefinedLiteral()) {
8045  VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr);
8046  BytecodeLabel is_null_or_undefined;
8047  builder()
8048  ->JumpIfUndefinedOrNull(&is_null_or_undefined)
8049  .Jump(end_labels->New());
8050  builder()->Bind(&is_null_or_undefined);
8051  }
8052 
8053  BuildIncrementBlockCoverageCounterIfEnabled(coverage_slot);
8054 
8055  return false;
8056 }
8057 
8058 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitLogicalOrExpression(BinaryOperation* binop) {
8059  Expression* left = binop->left();
8060  Expression* right = binop->right();
8061 
8062  int right_coverage_slot =
8063  AllocateBlockCoverageSlotIfEnabled(binop, SourceRangeKind::kRight);
8064 
8065  if (execution_result()->IsTest()) {
8066  TestResultScope* test_result = execution_result()->AsTest();
8067  if (left->ToBooleanIsTrue()) {
8068  builder()->Jump(test_result->NewThenLabel());
8069  } else if (left->ToBooleanIsFalse() && right->ToBooleanIsFalse()) {
8070  BuildIncrementBlockCoverageCounterIfEnabled(right_coverage_slot);
8071  builder()->Jump(test_result->NewElseLabel());
8072  } else {
8073  VisitLogicalTest(Token::kOr, left, right, right_coverage_slot);
8074  }
8075  test_result->SetResultConsumedByTest();
8076  } else {
8077  BytecodeLabels end_labels(zone());
8078  if (VisitLogicalOrSubExpression(left, &end_labels, right_coverage_slot)) {
8079  return;
8080  }
8081  VisitInHoleCheckElisionScopeForAccumulatorValue(right);
8082  end_labels.Bind(builder());
8083  }
8084 }
8085 
8086 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitNaryLogicalOrExpression(NaryOperation* expr) {
8087  Expression* first = expr->first();
8088  DCHECK_GT(expr->subsequent_length(), 0);
8089 
8090  NaryCodeCoverageSlots coverage_slots(this, expr);
8091 
8092  if (execution_result()->IsTest()) {
8093  TestResultScope* test_result = execution_result()->AsTest();
8094  if (first->ToBooleanIsTrue()) {
8095  builder()->Jump(test_result->NewThenLabel());
8096  } else {
8097  VisitNaryLogicalTest(Token::kOr, expr, &coverage_slots);
8098  }
8099  test_result->SetResultConsumedByTest();
8100  } else {
8101  BytecodeLabels end_labels(zone());
8102  if (VisitLogicalOrSubExpression(first, &end_labels,
8103  coverage_slots.GetSlotFor(0))) {
8104  return;
8105  }
8106 
8107  HoleCheckElisionScope elider(this);
8108  for (size_t i = 0; i < expr->subsequent_length() - 1; ++i) {
8109  if (VisitLogicalOrSubExpression(expr->subsequent(i), &end_labels,
8110  coverage_slots.GetSlotFor(i + 1))) {
8111  return;
8112  }
8113  }
8114  // We have to visit the last value even if it's true, because we need its
8115  // actual value.
8116  VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->subsequent(expr->subsequent_length() - 1));
8117  end_labels.Bind(builder());
8118  }
8119 }

8121 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitLogicalAndExpression(BinaryOperation* binop) {
8122  Expression* left = binop->left();
8123  Expression* right = binop->right();
8124 
8125  int right_coverage_slot =
8126  AllocateBlockCoverageSlotIfEnabled(binop, SourceRangeKind::kRight);
8127 
8128  if (execution_result()->IsTest()) {
8129  TestResultScope* test_result = execution_result()->AsTest();
8130  if (left->ToBooleanIsFalse()) {
8131  builder()->Jump(test_result->NewElseLabel());
8132  } else if (left->ToBooleanIsTrue() && right->ToBooleanIsTrue()) {
8133  BuildIncrementBlockCoverageCounterIfEnabled(right_coverage_slot);
8134  builder()->Jump(test_result->NewThenLabel());
8135  } else {
8136  VisitLogicalTest(Token::kAnd, left, right, right_coverage_slot);
8137  }
8138  test_result->SetResultConsumedByTest();
8139  } else {
8140  BytecodeLabels end_labels(zone());
8141  if (VisitLogicalAndSubExpression(left, &end_labels, right_coverage_slot)) {
8142  return;
8143  }
8144  VisitInHoleCheckElisionScopeForAccumulatorValue(right);
8145  end_labels.Bind(builder());
8146  }
8147 }

8155  if (execution_result()->IsTest()) {

8157  if (first->ToBooleanIsFalse()) {
8158  builder()->Jump(test_result->NewElseLabel());
8159  } else {
8160  VisitNaryLogicalTest(Token::kAnd, expr, &coverage_slots);
8161  }
8162  test_result->SetResultConsumedByTest();
8163  } else {
8164  BytecodeLabels end_labels(zone());
8165  if (VisitLogicalAndSubExpression(first, &end_labels,

8171  if (VisitLogicalAndSubExpression(expr->subsequent(i), &end_labels,
8172  coverage_slots.GetSlotFor(i + 1))) {
8173  return;
8174  }
8175  }
8176  // We have to visit the last value even if it's false, because we need its
8177  // actual value.
8178  VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->subsequent(expr->subsequent_length() - 1));

8180  }

8183 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitNullishExpression(BinaryOperation* binop) {
8184  Expression* left = binop->left();
8185  Expression* right = binop->right();
8186 
8187  int right_coverage_slot =
8188  AllocateBlockCoverageSlotIfEnabled(binop, SourceRangeKind::kRight);
8189 
8190  if (execution_result()->IsTest()) {
8191  TestResultScope* test_result = execution_result()->AsTest();
8192  if (left->IsLiteralButNotNullOrUndefined() && left->ToBooleanIsTrue()) {
8193  builder()->Jump(test_result->NewThenLabel());
8194  } else if (left->IsNullOrUndefinedLiteral() &&
8195  right->IsNullOrUndefinedLiteral()) {
8196  BuildIncrementBlockCoverageCounterIfEnabled(right_coverage_slot);
8197  builder()->Jump(test_result->NewElseLabel());
8198  } else {
8199  VisitLogicalTest(Token::kNullish, left, right, right_coverage_slot);
8200  }
8201  test_result->SetResultConsumedByTest();
8202  } else {
8203  BytecodeLabels end_labels(zone());
8204  if (VisitNullishSubExpression(left, &end_labels, right_coverage_slot)) {
8205  return;
8206  }
8207  VisitInHoleCheckElisionScopeForAccumulatorValue(right);
8208  end_labels.Bind(builder());
8209  }
8210 }
8211 
8212 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitNaryNullishExpression(NaryOperation* expr) {
8213  Expression* first = expr->first();
8214  DCHECK_GT(expr->subsequent_length(), 0);
8215 
8216  NaryCodeCoverageSlots coverage_slots(this, expr);
8217 
8218  if (execution_result()->IsTest()) {
8219  TestResultScope* test_result = execution_result()->AsTest();
8220  if (first->IsLiteralButNotNullOrUndefined() && first->ToBooleanIsTrue()) {
8221  builder()->Jump(test_result->NewThenLabel());
8222  } else {
8223  VisitNaryLogicalTest(Token::kNullish, expr, &coverage_slots);
8224  }
8225  test_result->SetResultConsumedByTest();
8226  } else {
8227  BytecodeLabels end_labels(zone());
8228  if (VisitNullishSubExpression(first, &end_labels,
8229  coverage_slots.GetSlotFor(0))) {
8230  return;
8231  }
8232  HoleCheckElisionScope elider(this);
8233  for (size_t i = 0; i < expr->subsequent_length() - 1; ++i) {
8234  if (VisitNullishSubExpression(expr->subsequent(i), &end_labels,
8235  coverage_slots.GetSlotFor(i + 1))) {
8236  return;
8237  }
8238  }
8239  // We have to visit the last value even if it's nullish, because we need its
8240  // actual value.
8241  VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr->subsequent(expr->subsequent_length() - 1));
8242  end_labels.Bind(builder());
8243  }
8244 }
