8246 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildNewLocalActivationContext() {
8247  ValueResultScope value_execution_result(this);
8248  Scope* scope = closure_scope();
8249  DCHECK_EQ(current_scope(), closure_scope());
8250 
8251  // Create the appropriate context.
8252  DCHECK(scope->is_function_scope() || scope->is_eval_scope());
8253  int slot_count = scope->num_heap_slots() - Context::MIN_CONTEXT_SLOTS;
8254  if (slot_count <= ConstructorBuiltins::MaximumFunctionContextSlots()) {
8255  switch (scope->scope_type()) {
8256  case EVAL_SCOPE:
8257  builder()->CreateEvalContext(scope, slot_count);
8258  break;
8259  case FUNCTION_SCOPE:
8260  builder()->CreateFunctionContext(scope, slot_count);
8261  break;
8262  default:
8263  UNREACHABLE();
8264  }
8265  } else {
8266  Register arg = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
8267  builder()->LoadLiteral(scope).StoreAccumulatorInRegister(arg).CallRuntime(
8268  Runtime::kNewFunctionContext, arg);
8269  register_allocator()->ReleaseRegister(arg);
8270  }
8271 }
8272 
8273 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildLocalActivationContextInitialization() {
8274  DeclarationScope* scope = closure_scope();
8275 
8276  if (scope->has_this_declaration() && scope->receiver()->IsContextSlot()) {
8277  Variable* variable = scope->receiver();
8278  Register receiver(builder()->Receiver());
8279  // Context variable (at bottom of the context chain).
8280  DCHECK_EQ(0, scope->ContextChainLength(variable->scope()));
8281  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(receiver).StoreContextSlot(
8282  execution_context()->reg(), variable, 0);
8283  }
8284 
8285  // Copy parameters into context if necessary.
8286  int num_parameters = scope->num_parameters();
8287  for (int i = 0; i < num_parameters; i++) {
8288  Variable* variable = scope->parameter(i);
8289  if (!variable->IsContextSlot()) continue;
8290 
8291  Register parameter(builder()->Parameter(i));
8292  // Context variable (at bottom of the context chain).
8293  DCHECK_EQ(0, scope->ContextChainLength(variable->scope()));
8294  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(parameter).StoreContextSlot(
8295  execution_context()->reg(), variable, 0);
8296  }
8297 }

8302 
8303  builder()->CreateBlockContext(scope);
8304 }

8357 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitThisFunctionVariable(Variable* variable) {
8358  if (variable == nullptr) return;
8359 
8360  // Store the closure we were called with in the given variable.
8361  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(Register::function_closure());
8362  BuildVariableAssignment(variable, Token::kInit, HoleCheckMode::kElided);
8363 }
8364 
8365 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitNewTargetVariable(Variable* variable) {
8366  if (variable == nullptr) return;
8367 
8368  // The generator resume trampoline abuses the new.target register
8369  // to pass in the generator object. In ordinary calls, new.target is always
8370  // undefined because generator functions are non-constructible, so don't
8371  // assign anything to the new.target variable.
8372  if (IsResumableFunction(info()->literal()->kind())) return;
8373 
8374  if (variable->location() == VariableLocation::LOCAL) {
8375  // The new.target register was already assigned by entry trampoline.
8376  DCHECK_EQ(incoming_new_target().index(),
8377  GetRegisterForLocalVariable(variable).index());
8378  return;
8379  }
8380 
8381  // Store the new target we were called with in the given variable.
8382  builder()->LoadAccumulatorWithRegister(incoming_new_target());
8383  BuildVariableAssignment(variable, Token::kInit, HoleCheckMode::kElided);
8384 }
8385 
8386 // Create a generator object if necessary and initialize the
8387 // {.generator_object} variable.
8388 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildGeneratorObjectVariableInitialization() {
8389  DCHECK(IsResumableFunction(info()->literal()->kind()));
8390 
8391  Variable* generator_object_var = closure_scope()->generator_object_var();
8392  RegisterAllocationScope register_scope(this);
8393  RegisterList args = register_allocator()->NewRegisterList(2);
8394  Runtime::FunctionId function_id =
8395  ((IsAsyncFunction(info()->literal()->kind()) &&
8396  !IsAsyncGeneratorFunction(info()->literal()->kind())) ||
8397  IsModuleWithTopLevelAwait(info()->literal()->kind()))
8398  ? Runtime::kInlineAsyncFunctionEnter
8399  : Runtime::kInlineCreateJSGeneratorObject;
8400  builder()
8401  ->MoveRegister(Register::function_closure(), args[0])
8402  .MoveRegister(builder()->Receiver(), args[1])
8403  .CallRuntime(function_id, args)
8404  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(generator_object());
8405 
8406  if (generator_object_var->location() == VariableLocation::LOCAL) {
8407  // The generator object register is already set to the variable's local
8408  // register.
8409  DCHECK_EQ(generator_object().index(),
8410  GetRegisterForLocalVariable(generator_object_var).index());
8411  } else {
8412  BuildVariableAssignment(generator_object_var, Token::kInit,
8413  HoleCheckMode::kElided);
8414  }
8415 }
8416 
8417 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildPushUndefinedIntoRegisterList(
8418  RegisterList* reg_list) {
8419  Register reg = register_allocator()->GrowRegisterList(reg_list);
8420  builder()->LoadUndefined().StoreAccumulatorInRegister(reg);
8421 }

8423 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildLoadPropertyKey(LiteralProperty* property,
8424  Register out_reg) {
8425  if (property->key()->IsStringLiteral()) {
8426  builder()
8427  ->LoadLiteral(property->key()->AsLiteral()->AsRawString())
8428  .StoreAccumulatorInRegister(out_reg);
8429  } else {
8430  VisitForAccumulatorValue(property->key());
8431  builder()->ToName().StoreAccumulatorInRegister(out_reg);
8432  }
8433 }

8436  AstNode* node, SourceRangeKind kind) {

8441 
8442 int BytecodeGenerator::AllocateNaryBlockCoverageSlotIfEnabled(
8443  NaryOperation* node, size_t index) {
8444  return (block_coverage_builder_ == nullptr)
8445  ? BlockCoverageBuilder::kNoCoverageArraySlot
8446  : block_coverage_builder_->AllocateNaryBlockCoverageSlot(node,
8447  index);
8448 }

8486 BytecodeGenerator::TypeHint BytecodeGenerator::VisitForAccumulatorValueImpl(
8487  Expression* expr, ValueResultScope* accumulator_scope) {
8488  Visit(expr);
8489  // Record the type hint for the result of current expression in accumulator.
8490  const TypeHint type_hint = accumulator_scope->type_hint();
8491  BytecodeRegisterOptimizer* optimizer = builder()->GetRegisterOptimizer();
8492  if (optimizer && type_hint != TypeHint::kUnknown) {
8493  optimizer->SetTypeHintForAccumulator(type_hint);
8494  }
8495  return type_hint;
8496 }

8512 // Visits the expression |expr| and returns the register containing
8513 // the expression result.
8514 Register BytecodeGenerator::VisitForRegisterValue(Expression* expr) {
8515  VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr);
8516  Register result = register_allocator()->NewRegister();
8517  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(result);
8518  return result;
8519 }

8521 // Visits the expression |expr| and stores the expression result in
8522 // |destination|.
8523 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitForRegisterValue(Expression* expr,
8524  Register destination) {

8526  Visit(expr);
8527  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(destination);
8528 }
8529 
8530 // Visits the expression |expr| and pushes the result into a new register
8531 // added to the end of |reg_list|.
8532 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitAndPushIntoRegisterList(Expression* expr,
8533  RegisterList* reg_list) {
8534  {
8535  ValueResultScope register_scope(this);
8536  Visit(expr);
8537  }
8538  // Grow the register list after visiting the expression to avoid reserving
8539  // the register across the expression evaluation, which could cause memory
8540  // leaks for deep expressions due to dead objects being kept alive by pointers
8541  // in registers.
8542  Register destination = register_allocator()->GrowRegisterList(reg_list);
8543  builder()->StoreAccumulatorInRegister(destination);
8544 }
8545 
8546 void BytecodeGenerator::BuildTest(ToBooleanMode mode,
8547  BytecodeLabels* then_labels,
8548  BytecodeLabels* else_labels,
8549  TestFallthrough fallthrough) {
8550  switch (fallthrough) {
8551  case TestFallthrough::kThen:
8552  builder()->JumpIfFalse(mode, else_labels->New());
8553  break;
8554  case TestFallthrough::kElse:
8555  builder()->JumpIfTrue(mode, then_labels->New());
8556  break;
8557  case TestFallthrough::kNone:
8558  builder()->JumpIfTrue(mode, then_labels->New());
8559  builder()->Jump(else_labels->New());
8560  break;
8561  }
8562 }
8563 
8564 // Visits the expression |expr| for testing its boolean value and jumping to the
8565 // |then| or |other| label depending on value and short-circuit semantics
8566 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitForTest(Expression* expr,
8567  BytecodeLabels* then_labels,
8568  BytecodeLabels* else_labels,
8569  TestFallthrough fallthrough) {
8570  bool result_consumed;
8571  TypeHint type_hint;
8572  {
8573  // To make sure that all temporary registers are returned before generating
8574  // jumps below, we ensure that the result scope is deleted before doing so.
8575  // Dead registers might be materialized otherwise.
8576  TestResultScope test_result(this, then_labels, else_labels, fallthrough);
8577  Visit(expr);
8578  result_consumed = test_result.result_consumed_by_test();
8579  type_hint = test_result.type_hint();
8580  // Labels and fallthrough might have been mutated, so update based on
8581  // TestResultScope.
8582  then_labels = test_result.then_labels();
8583  else_labels = test_result.else_labels();
8584  fallthrough = test_result.fallthrough();
8585  }
8586  if (!result_consumed) {
8587  BuildTest(ToBooleanModeFromTypeHint(type_hint), then_labels, else_labels,
8588  fallthrough);
8589  }
8590 }
8591 
8592 // Visits the expression |expr| for testing its nullish value and jumping to the
8593 // |then| or |other| label depending on value and short-circuit semantics
8594 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitForNullishTest(Expression* expr,
8595  BytecodeLabels* then_labels,
8596  BytecodeLabels* test_next_labels,
8597  BytecodeLabels* else_labels) {
8598  // Nullish short circuits on undefined or null, otherwise we fall back to
8599  // BuildTest with no fallthrough.
8600  // TODO(joshualitt): We should do this in a TestResultScope.
8601  TypeHint type_hint = VisitForAccumulatorValue(expr);
8602  ToBooleanMode mode = ToBooleanModeFromTypeHint(type_hint);
8603 
8604  // Skip the nullish shortcircuit if we already have a boolean.
8605  if (mode != ToBooleanMode::kAlreadyBoolean) {
8606  builder()->JumpIfUndefinedOrNull(test_next_labels->New());
8607  }
8608  BuildTest(mode, then_labels, else_labels, TestFallthrough::kNone);
8609 }
8610 
8611 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitInSameTestExecutionScope(Expression* expr) {
8612  DCHECK(execution_result()->IsTest());
8613  {
8614  RegisterAllocationScope reg_scope(this);
8615  Visit(expr);
8616  }
8617  if (!execution_result()->AsTest()->result_consumed_by_test()) {
8618  TestResultScope* result_scope = execution_result()->AsTest();
8619  BuildTest(ToBooleanModeFromTypeHint(result_scope->type_hint()),
8620  result_scope->then_labels(), result_scope->else_labels(),
8621  result_scope->fallthrough());
8622  result_scope->SetResultConsumedByTest();
8623  }
8624 }
8625 
8626 void BytecodeGenerator::VisitInScope(Statement* stmt, Scope* scope) {
8627  DCHECK(scope->declarations()->is_empty());
8628  CurrentScope current_scope(this, scope);
8629  ContextScope context_scope(this, scope);
8630  Visit(stmt);
8631 }

8690 FeedbackSlot BytecodeGenerator::GetCachedLoadGlobalICSlot(
8691  TypeofMode typeof_mode, Variable* variable) {
8692  FeedbackSlotCache::SlotKind slot_kind =
8693  typeof_mode == TypeofMode::kInside
8694  ? FeedbackSlotCache::SlotKind::kLoadGlobalInsideTypeof
8695  : FeedbackSlotCache::SlotKind::kLoadGlobalNotInsideTypeof;
8696  FeedbackSlot slot(feedback_slot_cache()->Get(slot_kind, variable));
8697  if (!slot.IsInvalid()) {
8698  return slot;
8699  }
8700  slot = feedback_spec()->AddLoadGlobalICSlot(typeof_mode);
8701  feedback_slot_cache()->Put(slot_kind, variable, feedback_index(slot));
8702  return slot;
8703 }
8704 
8705 FeedbackSlot BytecodeGenerator::GetCachedStoreGlobalICSlot(
8706  LanguageMode language_mode, Variable* variable) {
8707  FeedbackSlotCache::SlotKind slot_kind =
8708  is_strict(language_mode)
8709  ? FeedbackSlotCache::SlotKind::kStoreGlobalStrict
8710  : FeedbackSlotCache::SlotKind::kStoreGlobalSloppy;
8711  FeedbackSlot slot(feedback_slot_cache()->Get(slot_kind, variable));
8712  if (!slot.IsInvalid()) {
8713  return slot;
8714  }
8715  slot = feedback_spec()->AddStoreGlobalICSlot(language_mode);
8716  feedback_slot_cache()->Put(slot_kind, variable, feedback_index(slot));
8717  return slot;
8718 }
8719 
8720 FeedbackSlot BytecodeGenerator::GetCachedLoadICSlot(const Expression* expr,
8721  const AstRawString* name) {
8722  DCHECK(!expr->IsSuperPropertyReference());
8723  if (!v8_flags.ignition_share_named_property_feedback) {
8724  return feedback_spec()->AddLoadICSlot();
8725  }
8726  FeedbackSlotCache::SlotKind slot_kind =
8727  FeedbackSlotCache::SlotKind::kLoadProperty;
8728  if (!expr->IsVariableProxy()) {
8729  return feedback_spec()->AddLoadICSlot();
8730  }
8731  const VariableProxy* proxy = expr->AsVariableProxy();
8732  FeedbackSlot slot(
8733  feedback_slot_cache()->Get(slot_kind, proxy->var()->index(), name));
8734  if (!slot.IsInvalid()) {
8735  return slot;
8736  }
8737  slot = feedback_spec()->AddLoadICSlot();
8738  feedback_slot_cache()->Put(slot_kind, proxy->var()->index(), name,
8739  feedback_index(slot));
8740  return slot;
8741 }
8742 
8743 FeedbackSlot BytecodeGenerator::GetCachedLoadSuperICSlot(
8744  const AstRawString* name) {
8745  if (!v8_flags.ignition_share_named_property_feedback) {
8746  return feedback_spec()->AddLoadICSlot();
8747  }
8748  FeedbackSlotCache::SlotKind slot_kind =
8749  FeedbackSlotCache::SlotKind::kLoadSuperProperty;
8750 
8751  FeedbackSlot slot(feedback_slot_cache()->Get(slot_kind, name));
8752  if (!slot.IsInvalid()) {
8753  return slot;
8754  }
8755  slot = feedback_spec()->AddLoadICSlot();
8756  feedback_slot_cache()->Put(slot_kind, name, feedback_index(slot));
8757  return slot;
8758 }
8759 
8760 FeedbackSlot BytecodeGenerator::GetCachedStoreICSlot(const Expression* expr,
8761  const AstRawString* name) {
8762  if (!v8_flags.ignition_share_named_property_feedback) {
8763  return feedback_spec()->AddStoreICSlot(language_mode());
8764  }
8765  FeedbackSlotCache::SlotKind slot_kind =
8766  is_strict(language_mode()) ? FeedbackSlotCache::SlotKind::kSetNamedStrict
8767  : FeedbackSlotCache::SlotKind::kSetNamedSloppy;
8768  if (!expr->IsVariableProxy()) {
8769  return feedback_spec()->AddStoreICSlot(language_mode());
8770  }
8771  const VariableProxy* proxy = expr->AsVariableProxy();
8772  FeedbackSlot slot(
8773  feedback_slot_cache()->Get(slot_kind, proxy->var()->index(), name));
8774  if (!slot.IsInvalid()) {
8775  return slot;
8776  }
8777  slot = feedback_spec()->AddStoreICSlot(language_mode());
8778  feedback_slot_cache()->Put(slot_kind, proxy->var()->index(), name,
8779  feedback_index(slot));
8780  return slot;
8781 }

8783 int BytecodeGenerator::GetCachedCreateClosureSlot(FunctionLiteral* literal) {
8784  FeedbackSlotCache::SlotKind slot_kind =
8785  FeedbackSlotCache::SlotKind::kClosureFeedbackCell;
8786  int index = feedback_slot_cache()->Get(slot_kind, literal);
8787  if (index != -1) {
8788  return index;
8789  }
8790  index = feedback_spec()->AddCreateClosureParameterCount(
8791  JSParameterCount(literal->parameter_count()));
8792  feedback_slot_cache()->Put(slot_kind, literal, index);
8793  return index;
8794 }
